l be executed upon \r\nsave of the time-card.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nTime Required : Yes/No field with Default Value=Yes. This field \r\ndetermines if a time-card is always required by consumer for every time \r\nperiod. This field can help determine if a time-card is deemed \'missing\'\r\n for a given time period.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nApproval Period: User can select from a smart choice list of repeating \r\ntime periods which can be used as approval periods. This approval period\r\n is the period in which time would be routed for approval once the \r\nperiod has been met. <br><br><br><u><b>Statuses for Time-Card Retrieval Section:</b></u><br>\r\n<br>&nbsp;\r\nTime-cards : Radio button choice<br>\r\n<br>\r\nSaved: If saved radio button is selected, time-card will be transferred to selected time consumer interface table as saved.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nSubmitted: If submitted radio button is selected, time-card will be transferred to selected consumer interface table as in submit status. <br>\r\n<br>\r\nApproval Required By: Check box selection will display the selected time\r\n consumers and None check box. Approval required will not show up if the \r\nTime card retrieval status is saved. By default all the selected \r\nconsumer check boxes will selected and if the user wants select none or unchecked some of the check-boxes. <br><br>\r\n',NULL,'2011-06-08 07:47:16','2011-06-08 08:21:45',0),(133,'Page Action - Save & Save and close',8,'lbo','\'Save\' action will insert rows into the Time Consumer tables and stays in the Create scree.<br><br>\'Save and Close\' action will insert rows into the Time Consumer tables and exits the Create scree. <br>',NULL,'2011-06-08 07:47:33','2011-06-08 09:47:03',0),(135,'Page Action - Cancel',8,'lbo','Cancel action will take the user to Manage Time Consumer Sets page. ',NULL,'2011-06-08 07:47:57','2011-06-08 08:23:44',0),(136,'Setup Interface: Get Bulk Setup Options for Date',9,'lba','<b><u>Input Parameters: </u></b><br><br>* List of setup options to be fetched<br>* Date<br><br><b><u>Output Parameters: </u></b><br><br>The collection of setup options, values for the given date.<br><br><u><b>Note:&nbsp; </b></u><br><br>The query should be designed so that only one round trip to the DB is needed.<br><br>See feature \'Evaluation of Setup Profile Options\' for more details.<br><br><br>',NULL,'2011-06-08 19:27:30','2011-06-08 19:31:59',0),(137,'Workarea: Fetch Setup Options',33,'lba','Fetch setup option values for current user and current date from interface \'Get Bulk Setup Option by Date\'.',NULL,'2011-06-08 19:30:16','2011-06-08 19:33:18',0),(138,'Periods Interface: Get Timecard Period Dates by Date',18,'lba','Return the range of dates for a timecard period that spans the given date.<br>',NULL,'2011-06-08 20:44:52','2011-06-09 20:40:37',0),(139,'Load Interface: Load Timecard',11,'lba','Load in memory time card passed from the UI to the repository.&nbsp; If the time card does not already exist, create a new time card.<br>',NULL,'2011-06-08 21:24:06','2011-06-09 21:13:39',0),(140,'Data Interface: CRUD In-Memory Timecard',17,'lba','Interfaces for creating and updating in memory time card building blocks for create and update time card actions from UI.<br>',NULL,'2011-06-08 21:25:35','2011-06-09 21:14:27',0),(142,'Statuses: Seed Data for All Possible UI Statuses',10,'lba','Needed for Status filter on the Recent Timecards table.<br>',NULL,'2011-06-09 01:34:37','2011-06-09 01:55:05',0),(143,'Data: Read Only Timecard Summary VO',17,'lba','This summary VO needs to contain the following information about the time cards:<br><br>1. Start Date and End Date<br>2. Timecard Status<br>3.     Recorded Hours<br>4. Submission Date<br>',NULL,'2011-06-09 02:06:31','2011-06-09 02:08:47',0),(144,'Data Interface: Check If Timecard Exists on Date',17,'lba','Input Parameters:<br><br>* Date<br>* Resource ID<br><br>Output:<br><br>* Timecard ID if there is already a timecard exists on the given date for given user.<br>* Null if none exists.<br>',NU