ails, we will also have a Comments field for each day for daily comments as well.  Initial prototypes tested at customer feedback sessions in January 2010 had separate icons for Daily Comments and Daily Details, to easily differentiate the two areas of entry.  To consolidate columns, the two areas are being combined into the Daily Details icon.','2011-05-30 06:39:57','2011-05-30 06:41:49',1,'Must Have','',''),(1520,175,'Daily Details Icon Changes to Signify existing Entries','The user or approver knows if there is data contained in this pop-up page, there should be different modes of the icon, one to display when the pop-up page has no data entered, and another to display when the pop-up page does contain data.\r\n','2011-05-30 06:40:28','2011-05-30 06:41:16',1,'Must Have','',''),(1521,170,'Workflow Notification - Approval Actions','RequireApproval Notifications -   Deliver worklist notifications for timecards requiring approval via AMX Approvals Engine to approvers.  Approvers of timecards (who may be managers) would need to be notified of any timecards requiring their approval.\r\n\r\n\r\n----------------------------\r\nAdditional Background Information\r\n\r\n----------------------------\r\nThere are various notifications which revolve around the reporting of time.  Below are some of the notifications.  Additional notifications are noted in Item #20 in Section 2.3.1.1. Should Have Functionality for the Worker Timecard.  These notifications would be triggered by different events of the timecard and would trigger workflow tasks.  The output of the workflow notifications could be email notifications, worklist items or both.  Worklist items would display in the main Worklist on the general Welcome tab as well as the on the Timecards Workarea overview page for Time and Labor.  The configuration of which notification types occurs would be in the workflow setup. ','2011-05-30 20:47:14','2011-05-30 20:48:33',1,'Must Have','','Business Rule'),(1522,160,'General Info','Another option for worklist or email notifications are alerts.  One method for online alerts, are the use of  Watchlist items, which are summaries of items which require attention.  The resulting displays for Watchlists are saved searches.  Watchlist items will be explored further in the Time and Labor Dashboard FDD.\r\n\r\n\r\n----------------------------\r\nAdditional Background Information\r\n\r\n----------------------------\r\nThere are various notifications which revolve around the reporting of time.  Below are some of the notifications.  Additional notifications are noted in Item #20 in Section 2.3.1.1. Should Have Functionality for the Worker Timecard.  These notifications would be triggered by different events of the timecard and would trigger workflow tasks.  The output of the workflow notifications could be email notifications, worklist items or both.  Worklist items would display in the main Worklist on the general Welcome tab as well as the on the Timecards Workarea overview page for Time and Labor.  The configuration of which notification types occurs would be in the workflow setup. ','2011-05-30 20:49:34','2011-05-30 20:49:53',1,'Must Have','','Business Rule'),(1523,170,'Workflow Notification - Rejected Timecard Notification','Rejected Timecards Notifications -   Deliver worklist notifications for timecards which have been rejected in the approval process via the AMX Approvals Engine to those who need to resolve or correct the rejected timecards, such as workers or timekeepers.  \r\n\r\n----------------------------\r\nAdditional Background Information\r\n\r\n----------------------------\r\nThere are various notifications which revolve around the reporting of time.  Below are some of the notifications.  Additional notifications are noted in Item #20 in Section 2.3.1.1. Should Have Functionality for the Worker Timecard.  These notifications would be triggered by different events of the timecard and would trigger workflow tasks.  The output of the workflow notifications could be email notifications, worklist items or both.  Worklist items would display in the main Worklist on the general Welcome tab as well as the on the Timecards Workarea overview page for Time and Labor.  The configuration of which notification types occurs would be in the workflow setup. ','2011-05-30 20:50:38','2011-05-30 20:51:08',1,'Must Have','','Business Rule'),(1524,170,'Workflow Notification - Time Change Notification','Time change Notifications – Provide an option to trigger email notifications when a timecard is modified.  This notification should only be triggered on a submit of  a timecard, not on Save.  Options would include notification to worker, to timekeeper or manager.  The notification would need to communicate to the recipient if the timecard was modified, including  the fields of  “Last Modified By” and “Date of Action”.  Development would need to seed a worklist notification to display for a modified timecard.  Would be beneficial if it can be defined what changes had occurred in the timecard.  If this is not possible, there should be a link to the timecard to view the modified timecard.\r\n\r\n----------------------------\r\nAdditional Background Information\r\n\r\n----------------------------\r\nThere are various notifications which revolve around the reporting of time.  Below are some of the notifications.  Additional notifications are noted in Item #20 in Section 2.3.1.1. Should Have Functionality for the Worker Timecard.  These notifications would be triggered by different events of the timecard and would trigger workflow tasks.  The output of the workflow notifications could be email notifications, worklist items or both.  Worklist items would display in the main Worklist on the general Welcome tab as well as the on the Timecards Workarea overview page for Time and Labor.  The configuration of which notification types occurs would be in the workflow setup. ','2011-05-30 20:51:45','2011-05-30 20:52:06',1,'Must Have','','Business Rule'),(1525,176,'Workflow Notification - TCR Errors req resolution','Timecard for Resolution Notification – Provide a worklist notification to the timekeeper or administrator of timecards which need error resolution which a worker cannot resolve.  This is normally due to setup object changes which are needed such as rules.\r\n\r\n\r\n----------------------------\r\nAdditional Background Information\r\n\r\n----------------------------\r\nThere are various notifications which revolve around the reporting of time.  Below are some of the notifications.  Additional notifications are noted in Item #20 in Section 2.3.1.1. Should Have Functionality for the Worker Timecard.  These notifications would be triggered by different events of the timecard and would trigger workflow tasks.  The output of the workflow notifications could be email notifications, worklist items or both.  Worklist items would display in the main Worklist on the general Welcome tab as well as the on the Timecards Workarea overview page for Time and Labor.  The configuration of which notification types occurs would be in the workflow setup.','2011-05-30 20:53:07','2011-05-30 20:53:38',1,'Must Have','','Business Rule'),(1526,177,'Info on Demand - Timecard Level Comments','Provide more real estate in the timecard page so the user can focus on the timecard matrix for time entry.  As a result, there will be additional pieces of information that a user may want to\r\nreference, but not view at all times. These sections should be \"information on demand\", available to the user when needed.  Such sections include:\r\n\r\na.	Timecard Comments – comments for the overall timecard.  This section is currently displayed in the prototype as an open text field above the timecard matrix, so it is always open.','2011-05-30 21:18:24','2011-05-30 21:20:02',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1527,177,'Info on Demand - Accrual Balances','Provide more real estate in the timecard page so the user can focus on the timecard matrix for time entry.  As a result, there will be additional pieces of information that a user may want to\r\nreference, but not view at all times. These sections should be \"information on demand\", available to the user when needed.  Such sections include:\r\n\r\n\r\nb.	Accrual Balances – listing balances for all leave plans the worker is associated to.  The two options agreed upon were either show:\r\n>>	Accrual Balance display open in the contextual section of the timecard, balance display provided by Absence Management\r\n>>	Open section in local area of the timecard, showing just 2 accrual balances, with a MORE link, to view all accrual balances in a pop-up page.','2011-05-30 21:18:59','2011-05-30 21:20:27',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1528,177,'Info on Demand - Approval Comments','Provide more real estate in the timecard page so the user can focus on the timecard matrix for time entry.  As a result, there will be additional pieces of information that a user may want to\r\nreference, but not view at all times. These sections should be \"information on demand\", available to the user when needed.  Such sections include:\r\n\r\n\r\nd.	Approval Comments – comments from each timecard approver. This section should only be displayed if data exists.  If the timecard has not been routed for approval as of yet, the Approval Comments section or dialog box should not be displayed.  If there are Approval Comments, as the user enters the page, the Approval Comments message listing should pop-up like the Error Message listing does.  It should always be available to the user to re-access if they close the approval comments.','2011-05-30 21:19:34','2011-05-30 21:20:49',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1529,156,'Printable Timecard - Action from View Timecard Page',NULL,'2011-05-30 21:28:41','2011-05-30 21:29:11',1,'Must Have',NULL,NULL),(1530,156,'View Timecard','View \'Read Only\' Timecard from Workers Layout Set\r\n\r\nCannot edit timecard, but displays \'Raw\' entries as well as processed results - based on what was configured in the Layout Set.\r\n\r\nOption to Print Timecard available from Page','2011-05-30 21:29:55','2011-05-30 21:31:25',1,'Must Have','','Business Rule'),(1531,156,'Edit Timecard','Access Timecard to edit IF:\r\n\r\nSetup Options Permit the Worker from accessing the timecard with the timecard status.\r\n\r\nThe Worker can access the timecard by selecting the from - to date range within the table.\r\n\r\n','2011-05-30 21:30:04','2011-05-30 21:32:34',1,'Must Have','','Business Rule'),(1532,156,'Create Timecard - Action List, Icon','Worker Option to Create a New timecard based on Setup Options enabling the functionality.\r\n\r\nIcon plus text (butcon) or Action drop list are all options to create the timecard.\r\n\r\nButton Formats  \r\nhttp://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines5/button.html ','2011-05-30 21:30:14','2011-06-07 00:22:52',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1533,174,'Timecard Add\'l Info Sections Design - Pop up Sections','Provide more real estate in the timecard page so the user can focus on the timecard matrix for time entry.  As a result, there will be additional pieces of information that a user may want to reference, but not view at all times. These sections should be \"information on demand\", available to the user when needed.\r\n\r\nConfiguration Options:   These configuration options were previously discussed for Time Entry Page Composer, please see above options for latest recommendations from UX.\r\n\r\n>>	Pop Up Information sections – These sections of data can be presented via pop up pages from hyperlinks above the timecard matrix.  When the user clicks on the hyperlink, the related section will be in a pop-up page, which should be modeless, so the user can move the pop-up to another part of the timecard page, while being able to edit the timecard matrix.  This is especially important for the Approval Comment section, as the details of this pop-up will guide the user on what to address in the timecard matrix','2011-05-30 21:34:41','2011-05-30 23:15:34',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1534,178,'Basic Search','Assume Single search Design Pattern - where 1 field has options to search on:\r\n\r\n    Layout Set Name: (text field)\r\n    Layout Set Type: Individual / Group Entry\r\n\r\n','2011-05-31 19:04:05','2011-05-31 19:17:48',1,'Must Have','','Miscellaneous'),(1535,178,'Advanced Search','Option to have Saved Searches:\r\n\r\n<br><br>Option to have common operators (Equal, Like, Not equal to, etc)\r\n<br><br>Option to build complex search criteria\r\n\r\nAdvanced Search on the following Fields:\r\n\r\n<br>Layout Set Name\r\n<br>Layout Set Description\r\n<br>Layout Set Tags\r\n<br>Layout Set Type\r\n<br>Applications\r\n<br>Creation Date\r\n<br>Last Updated Date\r\n<br>Last Updated By\r\n<br>Created By\r\n<br>CLA Enabled\r\nLayout <br>Component Used\r\n<br>Contains \'X\' Time Attributes\r\n<br>Contains Alternate Name Layout Componets\r\n<br>Currently Assigned Yes / No\r\n<br>Usage (Specific Setup Options)\r\n<br>Previously Used\r\n<br>CLA Enabled\r\n<br>Template Enabled\r\n<br>Private Template Enabled','2011-05-31 19:04:16','2011-06-08 18:15:26',1,'Must Have','','Miscellaneous'),(1536,179,'Start Page - General Look','Initial Page layout:\r\n\r\n<br><br>Search / Results with table displaying results.\r\n\r\n<br><br>Search is in local panel - with Basic / Advanced search options\r\n<br><br>Table has columns for Layout Set Name, Description, etc,\r\n\r\nTable has toolbar for Table actions : Create, Delete, Edit, Duplicate.  ','2011-05-31 19:08:42','2011-06-08 22:56:15',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1537,180,'Results Table','Table with a Menu Bar and the following <br><b>Columns</b>:\r\n<ul><li>Name</li><li>Description</li><li>Type (Individual - Group Entry)</li><li>Manager Enabled (Yes / No)</li><li>Completion Status</li><li>Created by <br></li><li>Created Date (additional column)&nbsp;</li><li>Last Updated By <br></li><li>Last Updated Date (additional column)&nbsp;</li><li>Preview</li><li>Usage (list of Profiles, where value in column shows Profile...more)</li><li>CLA&nbsp;Enabled (Yes / No) (additional column)</li><li>CLA Default Reason Page Used (Yes / No) (additional column)</li><li>Template Functionality Enabled (additional column)</li><li>Private Template Page Enabled (additional column) | <font color=\"#008000\">-&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#008000\"></font></li></ul>&nbsp;- additional columns are column that will not be enabled by default, but customer could add them in the result table =&gt; Personalization.\r\n- Usage -&gt; will bring a popup window with all the profiles that used this layout set\r\n- <br><br>CLA columns will be displayed only if the customer answered \'Yes\' in the ASM questionnaire to enable Audit in his organization.\r\n','2011-05-31 19:21:08','2011-06-10 21:48:45',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1538,184,'Translation','Name and Description are Translatable, may display in timecard header.','2011-05-31 20:19:20','2011-05-31 20:49:24',1,'Must Have','1','Miscellaneous'),(1540,132,'Search Section','Page Action button = Done  - this will return the user to the Time and Labor setup Tasklist in Functional Setup Manager. <br><br>Search: Repeating Periods\r\n<br><br>Basic Search fields are:\r\n<br>o    Period Name – User name for time period	<br>									\r\no    Period Type – Daily, Weekly, Monthly, Semi-Monthly are the delivered types\r\n\r\n- <br>Saved Searches Box\r\n - <br>Buttons for Search: Search/ Reset/ Save/ \r\n\r\n\r\n<br><br>Advanced Search fields are:<br>&nbsp;Name – User name for  time period	<br>									\r\nPeriod Type – Daily, Weekly, Monthly, Semi-Monthly are the delivered types\r\n<br>\r\nPeriod Description – user entered description of the period with maximum of 2000 characters, should be consistent with all other description field lengths for other setup pages<br><br>&nbsp;o    Operator – this field is coupled with both the Name and Period Types fields, to allow more flexibility to search					\r\nThe options for the operator values to be used with these text fields are:<br>&nbsp;• Starts With  - searches for records where the first characters match the given text string.						\r\n<br>• Equals  - searches for records that match the text string exactly (ignoring case).<br>&nbsp;• Contains  - searches for records that contain the given text string.\r\n\r\n- Saved Searches Box\r\n - Buttons for Search: Search/ Reset/ Save/ Add Fields\r\n','2011-05-31 20:37:01','2011-06-07 21:14:45',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1541,184,'Define Time Period','Name:  Name of the Repeating Time Period.  This is a translatable field, as will be displayed on the timecard header. Required field.<br><br>&nbsp;Period Type:  Daily, Weekly, Semi-Monthly, Monthly.  This is a translatable field, as will be displayed on the Group Time Entry pages for filtering of periods.\r\n<br><br>Description:  User entered description for the repeating time period.  This is a translatable field, associated to the period name','2011-05-31 20:38:12','2011-06-07 21:16:13',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1542,184,'Test Time Period','Test Start Date -						\r\nThis date will be the beginning date the user can select to test their period definition to ensure the generated instances of the period are what is expected.<br><br>&nbsp;Field Help Note displayed in the page:<br>&nbsp;Test Start Date - Beginning date used to preview the period instances based on the period definition						\r\n						\r\n<br><br>Test End Date						\r\nThis date will be the end date the user can select to test their period definition to ensure the generated instances of the period are what is expected.	<br><br>Field Help Note displayed in the page: Test End Date - End date used to preview the period instances based on the period definition.<br><br>&nbsp;Generate Test Period button						\r\nOnce the user selects the button, the system will generate a preview of the time period instances within the Test Start Date and Test End Date selected.<br><br>','2011-05-31 20:38:23','2011-06-07 21:19:31',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1543,184,'View Generated Period Results','						\r\nView Test Time Period Results&nbsp;						\r\n- This subsection will display a preview of each period instance within the selected Test Start and Test End Date.  There will be a default table view and an alternate calendar view.						\r\n<br><br>Show Table button-  Default display of period instances generated from the “Generate Test Period” button.  The two columns displayed in the table are “Period Start Date” and “Period End Date”.  The earliest period instances will be displayed at the top of the table and the future period instances will be displayed at the end of the table.						\r\n<br><br>Show Calendar button– Click for Alternate calendar display which will highlight each period instance in a calendar display format, showing three months at a time.  The user can scroll left and right with the calendar display to see all period instances which are generated from the Generate Test Period button.						\r\n','2011-05-31 20:38:59','2011-06-07 21:19:13',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1544,184,'Define Time Period - Type Additional Questions','1.   Daily\r\nDuration = 1 Day\r\n<br>Duration = More Than One Day\r\n<br>Question:  How Many Days ____&nbsp;&nbsp; *Required Field<br>Reference Date of the Period _______ *Required Field<br><br>2.  Weekly\r\nDuration = 1 week\r\n<br>Start Day of the Week  ______*Required Field<br><br>Duration = Biweekly\r\n<br>Reference Date of the Period ______*Required Field<br><br>\r\nDuration= More than 2 weeks\r\n<br>Question:  How many weeks ___*Required Field<br>&nbsp;Reference Date of the Period ____*Required Field<br><br>3.  Monthly\r\nDuration = Calendar month\r\n<br>\r\nDuration = Quarter\r\n<br>Reference Date of the Period  ____ *Required Field<br><br>&nbsp;Duration = Semi-Year<br>&nbsp;Reference Date of the Period  ____ *Required Field<br><br>\r\nDuration = Year\r\n<br>Reference Date of the Period  ____ *Required Field<br><br>&nbsp;Duration = Multiple Mo