 for access \r\n\r\nBACKGROUND-----\r\n2.3.1.3.1.2.  Description\r\n\r\nA worker may be accessing his information from different navigations, depending on his other tasks he is performing.  The following would be some navigational options for the worker:\r\n\r\nPerson Portrait:  Navigating from Welcome Tab? Person Gallery->Person Portrait?Actions?Report Time?Time Entry page for current timecard period\r\n\r\nTimecard Work Area: Navigating from My Information Time Timecards Work Area; Create or View Timecards options\r\n\r\nWorker Dashboard (post v1):  Timecard Portlet Enter My Timecard Pop-up page of quick time entry\r\n\r\nProject Portfolio Management Team Member Dashboard or Payroll Dashboard could also be options for embedding the timecard for access ','2011-06-06 04:22:22','2011-06-06 04:24:15',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1602,156,'Table Toolbar Actions - Table View - Change to Calendar View','Table Actions\r\n\r\n\r\nCalendar View\r\n\r\nShould be a Icon + Text to change views to Calendar\r\n\r\n\r\nUI:\r\nhttp://apps-ux.us.oracle.com/Prototypes/HCM/V86_TimeAndLabor_PostCFS/_timeAndLabor/pages/login.htm?url=http://apps-ux.us.oracle.com/Prototypes/HCM/V86_TimeAndLabor_PostCFS/_timeAndLabor/pages/02CLA-overviewEmp.htm','2011-06-06 22:26:39','2011-06-06 22:27:38',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1603,169,'Calendar Toolbar Actions - Change to Table View','Table View\r\n\r\nShould be a Icon + Text to change views to Table ','2011-06-06 22:28:38','2011-06-06 22:29:08',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1604,167,'Timecard Period Security Access - From Within the Timecard','Provide ability to restrict access to timecards for prior or future time, by timecard actions,  for workers, managers or timekeepers.   This control will be offered in the Worker and Group Time Entry Time and Labor Setup Profiles, in the Timecard Actions table setup.  \r\n\r\n\r\nIf the user is currently in a timecard and navigates to another timecard , the expected results are:\r\n\r\na.  User can view but not edit the timecard for that period – will be taken to a view-only version of the timecard\r\n\r\nb.  User cannot view or edit the timecard for that period – will be issued a business message that they do not have access to the selected timecard based on current timecard status. If the user does not have view or edit access to that timecard,  that timecard should not be included in any listing of timecards or timecard counts in related analytics.   Additionally, the calendar widget which allows navigation to another timecard period will not enable a timecard period to which the user is not allowed any access (view and edit mode).','2011-06-06 22:36:04','2011-06-06 22:36:57',1,'Must Have','','Business Rule'),(1605,156,'Create Timecard - Button','Worker Option to Create a New timecard based on Setup Options enabling the functionality.\r\n\r\nButton on Toolbar.  \r\n\r\nIcon plus text (butcon) or Action drop list are other options to create the timecard that would be with the button, when enabled\r\n\r\nButton Formats  \r\nhttp://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines5/button.html \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n','2011-06-06 23:36:51','2011-06-07 00:22:20',1,'Should Have','','UI'),(1606,207,'Columns','Columns Submenu<br><br><ul><li>The Columns submenu lists up to 10 columns with check mark toggles. \r\n</li><li>If the table has more than 10 columns, a \'Show More Columns\' menu item \r\nappears at the bottom of the Columns submenu. \r\n</li><li>If the table contains column groups, each column group opens a submenu with \r\nits child columns. </li></ul><br>http://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines5/tblElements.html#menuView<br>','2011-06-07 19:30:53','2011-06-07 20:40:42',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1607,207,'Detach','<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Detach Menu Item</span>\r\n<ul><li>The Detach/Attach action should be available as follows: \r\n<ul><li>Menu: With the View &gt; Detach/Attach command (see <a href=\"tblElements.html#menuView\">View Menu</a> in the Table Elements guideline). \r\n\r\n</li><li>Toolbar: With the Detach toggle button. </li></ul>\r\n</li><li>The View &gt; Detach/Attach commands are dynamic antonyms. The toolbar \r\nbutton is a toggle button. Once the user detaches a table, the Attach command or \r\nDetach toggle button can be used to return the table to the previous size. \r\n</li><li>Detach/Attach is not supported in Master/Detail layouts when the master and \r\ndetail are heterogeneous components that share a single toolbar. </li></ul>\r\n<h6>Usage:</h6>\r\n<ul><li>Consider using Detach/Attach for tables with the following characteristics: \r\n<ul><li>More than 20 rows. \r\n</li><li>Column resizing or reordering is enabled. \r\n</li><li>The table is intended for intermediate to advanced users. </li></ul>\r\n</li><li>Product teams may place a header above the detached table so that users do \r\nnot lose context with the current task. \r\n</li><li>If Detach/Attach is used in a table with a toolbar, it is recommended to \r\ninclude the Detach button on the toolbar, unless space is too limited. \r\n</li></ul>','2011-06-07 20:20:55','2011-06-07 20:34:54',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1608,207,'Sort','<p>Sort Submenu<br></p><p>Allows users to specify the sort order based on the selected column or to \r\nlaunch a dialog box to specify a sort order based on multiple columns.</p><h3><a name=\"sortDisable\">When to Disable Sorting</a> </h3>Sort is not recommended for the following types of fields:\r\n<ul><li>Data types other than text, numbers, and dates, such as: \r\n<ul><li>Fields with data type CLOB (Character Large Objects) that contain very large \r\namounts of text. \r\n</li><li>Fields with data type BLOB (Binary Large Objects) that contain, for example, \r\ndocuments for data processing, CAD program files, spreadsheet files, graphics \r\nand images, videos, music files, and so on. </li></ul>\r\n</li><li>Fields containing multiple values, which are separated using semi-colons. \r\n</li><li>Long text fields containing more than 30 characters, unless they are used to \r\ndisplay object names or key object attributes that may be used to group the \r\nobject with similar objects. \r\n<ul><li>Examples of long text fields that should not be sortable include \r\ndescription, notes, comments, and concatenated addresses (entire address in a \r\nsingle field). \r\n</li><li>Examples of object names that may be sortable include the names of a person, \r\nproduct, or organization. \r\n</li><li>Examples of key object attributes that may be sortable include title, \r\nregion, or shipping method fields. </li></ul></li></ul><p>Note: Allow for Ascending and Descending Sort Order, not Advanced Sort order needed unless we have a lot of columns</p><p><br></p><p>http://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines5/tblElements.html#menuView<br></p>','2011-06-07 20:21:05','2011-06-07 20:46:04',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1609,207,'Reorder Columns','<p>Reorder columns:&nbsp; Reposition columns to focus on different attributes or facilitate actions \r\nwith columns of functional icons.</p><p><br></p><ul><li>The Reorder Columns action should be available as follows: \r\n<ul><li>Direct manipulation: By dragging a column header to any other location in \r\nthe table. \r\n</li><li>Menu: With the View &gt; Reorder Columns command and dialog (see <a href=\"tblElements.html#menuView\">View Menu</a> in the Table Elements guideline). \r\n\r\n</li><li>Keyboard: The accelerator keys Ctrl+Shift+left/right arrow move the active \r\ncolumn in the direction of the arrow key. </li></ul>\r\n</li><li>Direct manipulation interaction for Reorder Columns changes slightly when \r\ncolumn selection and marquee selection are supported. For details, see Actions: \r\nReorder in the <a href=\"tableSpec.pdf\">Tables UI Specification</a>. \r\n</li><li>Frozen columns can be reordered. See <a href=\"#freeze\">Freeze/Unfreeze \r\nColumns</a> above. </li></ul>http://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines5/tblManipulation.html#reorderCol<br><br>','2011-06-07 20:21:24','2011-06-07 20:49:30',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1610,208,'Resize Columns','<ul><li>The Resize Column action should be available as follows: \r\n<ul><li>Direct manipulation: By dragging the column\'s right-hand border (left in \r\nright-to-left languages). \r\n</li><li>Menu: By selecting a column and using the Format: Resize Column command and \r\ndialog (see <a href=\"tblElements.html#menuFormat\">Format Menu</a> in the Table \r\nElements guideline). \r\n</li><li>Context Menu: By right-clicking the column, and using the Resize Column \r\ncommand and dialog. </li></ul></li></ul>http://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines5/tblManipulation.html#resize<br><br>','2011-06-07 20:22:28','2011-06-07 20:47:51',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1611,207,'Freeze','Freeze Columns/ Unfreeze<br><ul><li>The Freeze/Unfreeze action should be available as follows: \r\n<ul><li>Menu: By selecting the column, and using the View &gt; Freeze/Unfreeze \r\ncommand (see <a href=\"tblElements.html#menuView\">View Menu</a> in the Table \r\nElements guideline). \r\n</li><li>Context Menu: By right-clicking the column, and using the Freeze/Unfreeze \r\ncommand. \r\n</li><li>Toolbar: By selecting the column, and clicking the Freeze toggle button. \r\n</li></ul>\r\n</li><li>The menu command is a dynamic antonym: Freeze/Unfreeze. The toolbar button \r\nis a toggle button. Once the user freezes columns, the Unfreeze command or \r\nFreeze toggle button can be used to return the columns to the unfrozen state. \r\n</li><li>If users want to freeze a different column, they must first unfreeze the \r\ncurrent column. \r\n</li><li>The Freeze command locks the selected column along with any columns before \r\nthe selected column. If multiple columns are selected, the last column \r\ndetermines the freeze location. </li></ul><br><br><br>http://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines5/tblManipulation.html#freeze<br>','2011-06-07 20:37:29','2011-06-07 20:43:02',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1612,209,'Query By Example Bar','<h2><a name=\"query\">QBE (Query by Example) Bar</a> </h2>Locates records matching specified criteria.\r\n<h6>Description:</h6>\r\n<ul><li>The QBE bar appears directly above the table column headers. \r\n</li><li>When the QBE bar is used in conjunction with a Search panel: \r\n<ul><li>Data entered into the QBE text fields is appended using the AND operator to \r\ndata entered into any search panel fields. \r\n</li><li>The query is run when the user clicks the Search button in the Search panel, \r\nor presses the Enter key while focus is in one of the search fields. \r\n</li></ul></li></ul>\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n<p class=\"label\">Table with QBE Bar</p>\r\n<h6>Usage:</h6>\r\n<ul><li>The QBE bar is optional and only recommended for advanced users working with \r\ncomplex data sets. \r\n</li><li>The QBE bar is hidden by default until the user clicks show QBE on the menu \r\nbar or toolbar. Product teams may choose to show the QBE bar by default where \r\nfrequency of use is expected to be high. \r\n</li><li>If a table is used in conjunction with a search panel, it is not recommended \r\nto have a QBE filter for a criterion that is already shown in the search panel. \r\n</li></ul>http://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines5/tblElements.html#query<br>','2011-06-07 20:52:48','2011-06-07 20:55:13',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1613,209,'Query By Example Fields','<h2><a name=\"queryFields\">QBE Fields</a> <a href=\"#queryFields\"><img alt=\"Bookmark this Heading\" src=\"../website/bookmark.gif\" align=\"absBottom\" border=\"0\"></a> <a href=\"#top\"><img alt=\"Return to Top\" src=\"../website/returnTop.gif\" align=\"absBottom\" border=\"0\"></a></h2>\r\n<h6>Purpose:</h6>\r\n<p>Specify search parameters for one or more table columns.</p>\r\n<h6>Description:</h6>\r\n<ul><li>Each column that supports query by example may have a QBE text field or date \r\nfield aligned directly above the column header. See the Text Field section in \r\nthe <a href=\"textBox.html\">Input/Output Text</a> guideline and the <a href=\"inputDate.html\">Input/Choose Date</a> guideline for details. \r\n</li><li>If a column does not support QBE, the space in the QBE bar above that column \r\nis left blank, without a field. \r\n</li><li>At least one column must support QBE to display the QBE bar. \r\n</li><li>QBE text fields support the following operators: \r\n<ul><li>Greater than: &gt; \r\n</li><li>Less than:&lt; \r\n</li><li>Great than or equal to: &gt;= \r\n</li><li>Less than or equal to: &lt;= \r\n</li><li>And: and \r\n</li><li>Or: or </li></ul>\r\n</li><li>QBE fields support wildcards. See the Wildcards section of the <a href=\"search.html\">Search and Query</a> guideline for details. \r\n</li><li>QBE searches may be case-sensitive or case-insensitive. However, it is \r\nrecommended that teams make them case-insensitive in order to yield the most \r\nsearch results for a given query. \r\n</li><li>QBE fields are 100% of the width of their associated column. If the user \r\nresizes a column with an associated QBE field, the QBE field adjusts to 100% of \r\nthe column\'s new width. \r\n</li><li>If a user hides, freezes, or reorders a column with an associated QBE field, \r\nthe QBE field hides, freezes or reorders with the column. </li></ul>http://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines5/tblElements.html#query<br>','2011-06-07 20:54:34','2011-06-07 20:55:00',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1614,132,'Create Action','Create&nbsp; - Toolbar and Menubar Actions\r\nCreate - When using the “create” action or “create” button from the\r\nSearch Results grid, a user will be able to add a new repeating period <br>','2011-06-07 21:04:07','2011-06-07 21:09:16',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1615,132,'Edit Action','&nbsp;Edit - Toolbar and Menubar Actions&nbsp;\r\nEdit - Only the name of a repeating period can be edited, the other\r\nfields will be grayed out in read only mode, to protect the period.\r\n<br>','2011-06-07 21:04:14','2011-06-07 21:09:53',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1616,132,'Delete Action','NO DELETE ACTION - repeating periods\r\ncannot be deleted. <br>','2011-06-07 21:04:38','2011-06-07 21:06:32',1,'Must Have','1','Business Rule'),(1617,210,'Auto-Sizing','&nbsp;Use Auto-Sizing on all tables, to eliminate white space below data','2011-06-07 21:08:15','2011-06-07 21:08:39',1,'Must Have','1','Miscellaneous'),(1618,211,'Layout Set - Type ','\r\nType of Layout set - and defines what questions are asked next:<br><ul><li>Group </li><li>\r\nIndividual (both Worker and Manager) </li><li>\r\nWhen set and save, it cannot be changed. </li></ul>','2011-06-07 22:31:30','2011-06-07 23:07:21',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1622,214,'Individual - Different Individual Layout used by Manager than Worker ','Yes / No <br class=\"atl-forced-newline\">\r\n<br>If Yes, then in the time entry layout page we will have 2 tabs: worker view and manager view. <br class=\"atl-forced-newline\">\r\n<br>In the manager view, all the worker time entry configuration will \r\ndisplay in read-only mode, and only addons functionality will be \r\navailable: ','2011-06-07 23:02:44','2011-06-07 23:06:17',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1623,186,'Create Action','Ability to create a new time consumer set, will transition to the Create Time Consumer Set page.<br><br><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: &quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\"><font face=\"Georgia\">This should be an action in the Menu bar under Actions menu, and a toolbar icon</font></span><br>','2011-06-07 23:07:17','2011-06-07 23:19:13',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1624,186,'Edit Action','A<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n <w:WordDocument>\r\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\r\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n  <w:TrackMoves></w:TrackMoves>\r\n  <w:TrackFormatting></w:TrackFormatting>\r\n  <w:PunctuationKerning></w:PunctuationKerning>\r\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas></w:ValidateAgainstSchemas>\r\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n  <w:DoN