,(1655,217,'General Functionality','Based on Selection from Manage Layout Set Page a Questionaire is generated:<br><br>The Questionaire guides the Admin through a set of questions - used to determine which tasks / pages are required to define a layout set.<br><br>UI for Questionaire: <br><br>http://ap6002fui.us.oracle.com:7777/hcm/hcm/time_and_labor/_ConfigUE2/pages/login.htm?url=http://ap6002fui.us.oracle.com:7777/hcm/hcm/time_and_labor/_ConfigUE2/pages/Dashboardv2.html<br><br><br>','2011-06-09 22:45:45','2011-06-10 20:57:44',1,'Must Have','','Miscellaneous'),(1656,218,'Page Level Actions','Page Level Actions - <br><br>Right / Left \"Arrows\" on either side of a drop list to navigate to the next / Previous page (as shown in the task - left arrow takes to previous page, right arrow takes to next page).<br><br>INCLUDED IN LIST - Option to go back to Task list - should be 1st value in the list.<br><br>Save <br>Saves updates to the Page<br><br>Cancel - Cancels Actions - Message if changes not saved (to be sure) - then back to Previous page<br><br>&nbsp;<br>','2011-06-09 23:11:04','2011-06-09 23:15:17',1,'Must Have','','UI'),(1657,218,'Option to Update Applications','Option to Update Applications.<br><br>Questionaire enabled applications that are checked on the Attribute Page (e.g., selecting Payroll and Projects has both selected on this page - and all attributes associated with the application is checked - in the table)<br><br>The selection limits the list of Timecard fields containing that attribute when defining layouts.<br><br>Un checking at the page level will:<br>Display a message - Changes will be reflected in the questionaire AND <br>Uncheck all attributes assocaited with the application.<br><br>Checking will check \'Include\' for all attributes in the table - under that application.&nbsp; Individual lines can then be checked / unchecked.<br><br>Applications selected - Show all Attributes associated with the application in the T&amp;L Data Dictionary<br><br>','2011-06-09 23:15:36','2011-06-09 23:26:07',1,'Must Have','',''),(1658,218,'Table','Table with columns:<br><ul><li>Include</li><ul><li>When checked - Timecard Fields of that Attribute are available in the Layout Pages</li><li>Based on Questionaire and Top level check boxes - checked or not checked</li><ul><li>Checked at page Level - then all under that application are initially checked</li><ul><li>can Un check individual values or sub groups (enable or disabel all below the sub grouping)<br></li></ul><li>Un checked at page level - then all unchecked</li><li>Based on Questionaire and Check boxes above table</li></ul></ul><li>Time Consumer - Time Attribute Field</li><ul><li>Tree structure showing associations</li></ul><li>Description</li><ul><li>Based on Values in Data Dictionary<br></li></ul></ul><br><br><br>','2011-06-09 23:15:51','2011-06-09 23:31:34',1,'Must Have','',''),(1660,198,'Setup Profile Values Trainstop','Upon creating a new profile, the following are the four train stops for every setup profile:<br>&nbsp;Train Stop 1:  Setup Profile Values\r\n<br>Train Stop 2:  Assign Profile to Group\r\n<br>Train Stop 3:  Set Profile Precedence<br>&nbsp;Train Stop 4:   Review Profile Setup\r\n<br><br>Train Stop 1:  Setup Profile Values\r\n<br>Page Name: Define Worker Web Time Entry Profile: Setup Profile Values <br>\r\n\r\nSection:  General Information<br>&nbsp;o   Name – enter name of setup profile, needs to be unique among worker core processing profiles, required field\r\n<br>o  Descriptions – enter description of setup profile\r\n\r\n<br><br>Section: Values\r\n<br>o Instructional Text: The effective start date is defaulted to\r\nJanuary 1, 1990. This is to insure that the setup options are in effect\r\nfor all timecards that the user may have entered or will have entered\r\nfrom this date.\r\n<br>\r\no  Effective Start Date- effective start date of the profile values, required field\r\n\r\n<br>o  Effective End Date – effective end date of the profile values<br>&nbsp;o Effective Date Actions for Edit Mode:\r\nEdit – Update, Correct or Delete effective dated record\r\nHistory – View History, Correct History\r\n\r\n<br><br>Sub-Section:  Time Entry Options\r\n\r\n<br>•  Worker Timecard Layout Set – choicelist of Layout Sets defined in Time and Labor\r\n\r\n<br>•  Timecard Actions - A hierarchical table displaying the following:\r\n\r\nTwo Tabs: Worker View  and Manager View<br>&nbsp;Each\r\ntab should display the same table\r\nToolbar/Menubar Actions- no rows should be deleted, added or changed.\r\nDon\'t think toolbar or menubar actions are required. The user should\r\nonly be able to select or deselect checkboxes in Enable column, or\r\nenter a number for Number of Days Before or After\r\nLeft column: <br> Timecard Actions:\r\n<br>o	Create<br>&nbsp;o	Delete<br>&nbsp;o	Edit\r\n<br>o View Only\r\nThe create function simply offers the option of “enable” or not. This\r\nmeans either the user can create or not create new timecards. No\r\ntimecard status is needed for definition.\r\n<br><br>For the other timecard actions, (delete, edit, view only) ;\r\nthere is a row for each timecard status, so the administrator can\r\ndetermine if the timecard user can take these actions on any or all of\r\nthe following timecard statuses (which are subnodes of each timecard\r\naction:\r\n<br><ul><li>&nbsp;Saved   \r\n</li><li>&nbsp;Submitted\r\n</li><li>&nbsp;Rejected</li><li>&nbsp;	Approved\r\n</li><li>&nbsp;Transferred \r\n\r\n</li><li>In Error</li><li>Pending Resolution</li></ul><br>Additional Columns in Table:\r\n  - <br>Enable - editable checkbox \r\n  <br>- Number of Days Before  - number field\r\n<br>  - Number of Days After - number field\r\n\r\n1.  <br>Enable - column with checkboxes for each timecard status row or Create<br><br>&nbsp;For\r\neach timecard status row, there are fields for “Number of Days Before”\r\nand “Number of Days After”. These fields allow for the administrator to\r\ndefine the number of days before or after System Date that a timecard\r\nuser can access a given timecard.<br><br>&nbsp;If the number of days falls\r\nin the middle of a timecard period, the user should be able to take the\r\nassigned actions for the whole timecard. If Number of Days Before or\r\nNumber of Days After fields are not populated with a number of days,\r\nthen the user will have unlimited access to take selected actions on\r\nthe current timecard.<br><br>&nbsp;SubSection:  Template Options\r\n<br>\r\n• Public Template Set – choice list of all public template sets\r\n<br><br>Train Page Actions: The user can click the \"Save\" from the same\r\nbutton at any time to ensure they do not lose any work, or click \"Save\r\nand Close\" to save work done so far and exit the guided process without\r\nfinishing. <br><br>The other buttons available are Next and Cancel.\r\n\r\nPage Actions:  Back (Grayed Out); Next, Save (Save and Close in dropdown); Submit (Grayed Out)and Cancel 					\r\n\r\n\r\n<br>','2011-06-09 23:26:34','2011-06-09 23:29:01',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1661,198,'Assign Profile to Group Trainstop','<br>Train Stop 2:  \r\nPage Name: Define Worker Web Time Entry Profile: Assign Profile to Group <br><br>Profile Name – read-only name of the current <br>Profile\r\nGroups Table – in this table, the user can assign the current profile\r\nto one or more HCM groups. Each of these associations are date enabled.\r\n<br>\r\nThe actions in the Actions menu and toolbar buttons for this table is\r\nto add or delete a row. The following are the fields in the table:\r\nGroup Name – choicelist of HCM Groups\r\n<br>	From Date<br>&nbsp;To Date\r\n\r\n<br><br>Section : Group Detail\r\nThis is a master/detail design pattern, when the user selects one of\r\nthe rows in the Groups Table, this section will display read-only\r\ndetail about the structure of the group. It will list the Group header\r\ndetail information, along with tabs for : Group Criteria, Group Members\r\nand SQL Statement. This read-only information is meant to assist the\r\nuser in ensuring he is assigning the correct groups to this profile.\r\nNote: the exact content of the read-only group information will be\r\nfinalized when the HCM Common Group model is designed.\r\n<br><br>Train Page Actions:\r\nBack ; Next, Save (Save and Close in dropdown); Submit (Grayed Out)and\r\nCancel The user can click the \"Save\" from the same button at any time\r\nto ensure they do not lose any work, or click \"Save and Close\" to save\r\nwork done so far and exit the guided process without finishing.<br>&nbsp;The other buttons available are Back,  Next and Cancel.\r\n','2011-06-09 23:26:53','2011-06-09 23:29:42',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1662,198,'Set Profile Precedence Trainstop','Train Stop 3:  \r\nPage Name: Define Worker Web Time Entry Profile: Set Profile Precedence\r\n<br><br>Profile Name – read-only name of the current Profile\r\n<br><br>Section:  Precedence\r\n<br>Set Profile Precedence instructional text - \"Where a person is\r\neligible for more than a single Setup Profile, precedence is used to\r\ndecide which Setup Profile is assigned. A person can be eligible for\r\nmore than one Setup profile when they are a member of two or more\r\nGroups that have been assigned Setup Profiles. In the table shown below\r\nProfiles at the top of the table take precedence over those at the\r\nbottom. Position the Setup Profile \'xxxxx\' in the table to take\r\nprecedence over the appropriate Profiles. You can highlight up to 6\r\nprofiles in the search result table for comparison: \"Compare\" button\"\r\n<br><br>Precedence Table – This table will list all of the setup\r\nprofiles of this type in a read-only precedence order, based on the\r\norder which they were created. The lower the precedence number, the\r\nhigher the precedence. There will be default seeded profiles for\r\nPayroll and Projects entry which will be listed as Precedence 1 and 2\r\nrespectively. The reason for this table is if a person is eligible for\r\nmore than one group, and thus more than one setup profile, the\r\nprecedence table will determine which of the valid setup profiles\r\nshould take precedence over the other. As this new profile is added to\r\nthe precedence table, the administrator may change the precedence order\r\nwith the up and down arrows icons on the toolbar. The user can select\r\nany row in the table and use the up or down arrow to move that row up\r\nor down in the table, thus changing the precedence order.<br><br>&nbsp;There\r\nis also a Compare button on the toolbar. A user can select from one to\r\n6 profiles in the table and select the Compare button. This will\r\ntrigger a pop-up display page of the Setup Profile Values for each of\r\nthe selected profiles. This is done to assist the administrator in\r\nensuring he recalls the content of the Setup Profiles as he reviews the\r\nprecedence order. <br><br>Each row has the ability to expand with a\r\n“+” button, which will provide more information about the selected\r\nprofile. In the first column of the expanded region, will be a listing\r\nof the Setup Profile Values. In the second column of the expanded\r\nregion will be the listing of groups to which this profile is attached.\r\nThe third column will list people who are assigned to the profile\r\nindividually, and not from group eligibility.\r\n<br>Train Page Actions:\r\nBack ; Next, Save (Save and Close in dropdown); Submit (Grayed Out)and Cancel 	\r\n \r\n<br>The user can click the \"Save\" from the same button at any time to\r\nensure they do not lose any work, or click \"Save and Close\" to save\r\nwork done so far and exit the guided process without finishing. The\r\nother buttons available are Back, Next and Cancel.<br><br>','2011-06-09 23:27:06','2011-06-09 23:30:05',1,'Must Have','1','UI'),(1663,198,'Review Profile Setup Trainstop','&nbsp;Train Stop 4:   Review Profile Setup\r\nPage Name: Define Worker Web Time Entry Profile: Review Profile Setup\r\n<br><br>This train stop is a read-only page whi