INSERT INTO `issues` VALUES (1,'UI Design Issues ',1374,'Feature','>> Option A - 	Open design issue:   need to determine if a new tab is opened when a new timecard period is selected, or refresh the existing timecard with the new time  period, warning the user that their changes need to be saved before navigating away from the timecard period.\r\n\r\nDesign Note:  This use of the Calendar widget requires enhancements from ADF on this component to support the highlighting of a time period based on a selected date.  Also noted that it would be nice to see the timecard period date range displayed in the calendar widget header based on the period highlighted.\r\n','Open','2011-05-30 22:28:47','2011-05-30 22:28:47'),(2,'Save Button Label',1461,'Feature','Open Design Issue:  Save button, whether the label can be “Save as Draft”. UX noted it should be Save to be consistent with other HCM applications.\r\n','Open','2011-05-30 22:35:50','2011-05-30 22:35:50'),(3,'Attribute Differences between Worker / Manager',1550,'Feature','To be defined in more detail - controls the mismatch of entries on different layouts - Manager  and Worker.\r\n\r\n ','Open','2011-05-31 21:45:02','2011-05-31 21:45:02'),(4,'Attached to Timecard Validation',1560,'Feature','o	During the TDD phase, it will be determined if the \"attached to a timecard\" check could be implemented (if too costly or not), but we surely need to consider it, as it will cause lot of problem if we have a timecard stamped with a \r\ntime consumer configuration set that does not exist anymore.\r\n','Open','2011-06-01 06:35:19','2011-06-01 06:35:19'),(5,'Save and Close',1461,'Feature','When executing the Save and Close - want a banner message on overview tab that the timecard has been saved.\r\n\r\nOverview Page - \r\nWant the page table to refresh to reflect the new timecard without the worker having to execute a refresh action.','Open','2011-06-09 21:37:36','2011-06-09 21:37:36');
