ress\\r\\n\\\n  11.\\tBirthDate\\r\\n\\\n  12.\\tMailingAddress\\r\\n\\\n  13.\\tEnterpriseStartDate\\r\\n\\\n  14.\\tStartDate\\r\\n\\\n  15.\\tLegalEmployerSeniorityDate\\r\\n\\\n  16.\\tWorkingAtHome\\r\\n\\\n  17.\\tWorkingHours\\r\\n\\\n  18.\\tStartTime\\r\\n\\\n  19.\\tEndTime\\r\\n\\\n  20.\\tAssignmentCategory\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s Picture - Although the header is delivered with the default to have the section open for a worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s picture to be imported, Time and Labor can hide the picture on the page.  If a picture is to be displayed, it is maintained in two places:  1.  Manage Personal Information - the HR Specialist can upload the picture. 2.  My Portrait - the Worker can upload the picture themselves.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-04-29 19:55:14'),(4255,'Feature',42,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Use of Employement Header - Primary Assignment\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 00:20:53 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-29 19:55:14 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 42\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 31\ndescription: \"Since the eligibility is based on primary assignment only, the Assignment label should denote in the header that this is the \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cprimary assignment\\xE2\\x80\\x9D header information.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-04-29 20:03:06'),(4256,'BusinessArea',198,'create','1',NULL,'2011-04-29 20:58:19'),(4257,'FunctionalWorkUnit',142,'create','1',NULL,'2011-04-29 20:58:28'),(4258,'BusinessArea',199,'create','1',NULL,'2011-04-29 22:31:37'),(4259,'Feature',1452,'create','1',NULL,'2011-04-29 23:34:26'),(4260,'Feature',1452,'destroy','1','--- \nscope: \nname: New node\ncreated_at: 2011-04-29 23:34:26 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-29 23:34:26 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1452\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 142\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-04-29 23:34:40'),(4261,'FunctionalWorkUnit',142,'destroy','1','--- \nname: test\ncreated_at: 2011-04-29 20:58:28 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-29 20:58:28 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 198\nid: 142\nparent_id: \n