ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1310\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide more real estate in the timecard page so the user can\\n focus on the timecard matrix for time entry.  As a result, there\\n will be additional pieces of information that a user may want to\\n reference, but not view at all times. These sections should be \\\"information\\n on demand\\\", available to the user when needed.  Such sections include:\\n\\\n  a.\\tTimecard Comments - comments for the overall timecard\\n\\\n  b.\\tAccrual Balances - listing balances for all leave plans the worker\\n is associated to\\n\\\n  c.\\tApproval Comments - comments from each timecard approver. This\\n section should only be displayed if data exists.  If the timecard\\n has not been routed for approval as of yet, the Approval Comments\\n section or dialog box should not be displayed.\\n\\\n  Note : These sections can be either displayed as Pop Up Information\\n Sections or Expandable Sections based on the settings in Time Entry\\n Page Composer.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 12:51:22'),(4287,'Feature',1310,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Additional Information Sections\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 12:51:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1310\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide more real estate in the timecard page so the user can\\n focus on the timecard matrix for time entry.  As a result, there\\n will be additional pieces of information that a user may want to\\n reference, but not view at all times. These sections should be \\\"information\\n on demand\\\", available to the user when needed.  Such sections include:\\n\\\n  a.\\tTimecard Comments - comments for the overall timecard\\n\\\n  b.\\tAccrual Balances - listing balances for all leave plans the worker\\n is associated to\\n\\\n  c.\\tApproval Comments - comments from each timecard approver. This\\n section should only be displayed if data exists.  If the timecard\\n has not been routed for approval as of yet, the Approval Comments\\n section or dialog box should not be displayed.\\n\\\n  Note : These sections can be either displayed as Pop Up Information\\n Sections or Expandable Sections based on the settings in Time Entry\\n Page Composer.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 12:51:38'),(4288,'Feature',1463,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-02 12:52:18'),(4289,'Feature',1463,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Additional Information Sections\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:52:18 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 12:52:18 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1463\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 12:52:49'),(4290,'Feature',1311,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Accrual Balance Configurable Display\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1311\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Allow for configuration by customer to determine what is displayed\\n in the View Accrual Balance section.  This content display will be\\n determined in conjunction with the Absence Management team. \\n\\\n  The location of the accrual balance display on the timecard will be\\n part of the timecard layout set configuration.  Two of the configuration\\n options for placement of the information is as a section in the contextual\\n area of the timecard entry page, and also in the local area of the\\n page above the timecard matrix.  We will offer an expanded section\\n showing View Accrual Balances with two pre-selected balances displayed,\\n with a \\\"More\\\"  link for the user to click on to view all available\\n balances to be displayed in the timecard.  The \\\"More\\\" link will trigger\\n a pop-up page showing the additional balances if any exist.  If there\\n are no additional balances, no \\\"More\\\" link will be displayed.\\n Some of the configurable items discussed with customers include:\\n\\\n  o\\tDisplay As of Date in Accrual Balance pop up page or expandable section\\n\\\n  o\\tDisplay balances in Units, to allow for balances in hours or days \\n\\\n  o\\tDisplay link to view Accrual Balances, does not resolve balance\\n when open the Timecard page \\n\\\n  o\\t Allow ability to select which balances are displayed in the Timecard\\n\\\n  o\\tAllow for display of beginning balance as of time period, along\\n with any additional unprocessed leave entries in the period, along\\n with ending balance, to give the user the full picture of what leave\\n time remains.  Unprocessed hours would include recorded leave time\\n which is not yet approved or processed in payroll.  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 12:54:25'),(4291,'Feature',1312,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Populated By\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1312\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>This field will be displayed above the timecard matrix to alert\\n the user if a default template has pre-populated a new timecard.\\n  The field will be populated with a read-only text of the Template\\n name.  If the default template could not be used to populate the\\n timecard because the layout set or timecard period of the current\\n timecard do not match the template, next to the template name, there\\n should be an icon, with a hover over explaining the default template\\n does not match the current layout set and timecard period.  There\\n should also be a global message displayed to the user in the Message\\n section of the timecard to alert the user that the default template\\n ccould not be used and to select an alternate default Template on\\n Timecard Options of their Workarea.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 12:54:55'),(4292,'Feature',1464,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-02 12:55:51'),(4293,'Feature',1464,'destroy','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Timecard Flow\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:55:51 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 12:55:51 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1464\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 12:56:07'),(4294,'FunctionalWorkUnit',145,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-02 12:57:41'),(4295,'FunctionalWorkUnit',146,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-02 12:57:52'),(4296,'Feature',1317,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Change and Late Audit Timecard Flow\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1317\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide ability to enter change and late audit reasons in the\\n defined Audit Entry page for a Change and Late Audit Layout Set,\\n as well as incorporate all of the change and late audit reasons and\\n comments, and show changed time in the Audit Review page.  The flow\\n would be Timecard Entry page, the Audit Entry page, the Timecard\\n Review page, with ability to submit the timecard.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 12:58:05'),(4297,'BusinessArea',200,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-02 13:01:18'),(4298,'FunctionalWorkUnit',147,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-02 13:02:19'),(4299,'Feature',1293,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Manager Timecard Search page-Manage Timecards\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1293\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> This is the manager\'s timecard search page converted to use \\n        the Oracle Applications Fusion middleware.  This replaces the View Recent \\n        Timecards in EBS Time and Labor R12. This is the search page to access \\n        timecards of  the manager\'s direct reports, with a default display of \\n        status on their most recent timecards.</pre>\\n        \\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:02:50'),(4300,'Feature',1390,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Individual Timecard: Line Manager Navigation Options\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1390\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>A manager may be accessing his information from different navigations,\\n depending on his other tasks he is performing.  The following would\\n be some navigational options for the manager:\\n\\n\\\n  1.     Person Portrait:  Navigating from Welcome Tab: Person Gallery->Person\\n Portrait:Actions:Report Time:Time Entry page for current timecard\\n period\\n\\n\\\n  2.     Portait Gallery - >Organization Chart:Actions.-->Report Time:Timecard\\n Entry page for default timecard period\\n\\n\\\n  3.     Timecard Work Area: Navigating from Manager Resources:Time\\n Management:Timecards Work Area; Create or View Timecards options\\n\\n\\\n  4.     Manager Dashboard: Manager Resources:My Organization:Actions:Report\\n Time:Time Entry page for current timecard period</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:03:16'),(4301,'Feature',1393,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Summary Display: Timecards in Progress Portlet\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1393\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>This portlet allows the manager  to view his workers\' timecards\\n in timecard period descending order.\\n\\n\\\n  Filter\\n\\n\\\n  o     Timecards in Progress-add this as a filter, with a multi-checkbox\\n selection, for the user to define what timecard statuses make up\\n \\\"in progress\\\"        \\n\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Status options:  Draft, Submitted, In Error, Pending\\n Resolution, Rejected, Approved\\n\\n\\\n  Columns Displayed:\\n\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Period - display of the start and end date of the timecard\\n period\\n\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Status - status of the timecard (working, saved, submitted,\\n approved, rejected, in error, etc)\\n\\n\\\n  o     Approval Chain - icon displayed if the timecard has entered\\n the approval workflow process, the user can click on the icon and\\n see a display of where the timecard is in the approval process by\\n which approvers have acted on the timecard and which approvers remain.\\n  This section will be using existing AMX UI display for showing approval\\n status/history.\\n\\n\\\n  o     Reported Hours - a total of all hours reported on the timecard.\\n  The display would be in hours and minutes, as there are no rounding\\n rules in effect.\\n\\n\\\n  o     Submission Date - the date the timecard has been submitted for\\n approval\\n\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Due Date - (new for Fusion)  would be nice to show\\n the due date of the timecard, especially if it is not submitted as\\n of yet\\n\\n\\\n  o     Audit Data - this column will display an icon if the timecard\\n contains change and late audit data (reason codes for why time was\\n changed or was entered late)\\n\\n\\\n  o     View Timecard - this column will display an icon to allow the\\n user to view the timecard (will display the \\\"View Timecard\\\" layout\\n page per the associated layout set.  This is a read only version\\n of the timecard which is similar to the Timecard Review page, containing\\n time entry detail, rule results, time summary information, change\\n and late audit summary information,  and audit details.  Additionally,\\n there will be a print function from this page,\\n\\n\\\n  o     Delete - this column will display an \\\"X\\\" to the user to allow\\n delete of the timecard if the user has access to perform this function,\\n based on his Time and Labor Setup Profile options.\\n\\n\\\n  Toolbar and Menu Options for Table\\n\\n\\\n  o     Create Timecard action - manager must select a worker (choice\\n list of available direct reports in the table)  and then select a\\n date from a calendar widget, to create for the correct timecard period,\\n then be taken to the Create Timecard page for that worker.\\n\\n\\\n  o     View Menu - to allow hiding of columns were are optional such\\n as:  Audit Data, Recorded Hours, Submission Date, Approval Chain\\n\\n\\\n  o     Enable QBE - so user can filter on any column in the search\\n results table\\n\\n\\\n  o     Gantt Chart View (open issue) - this component needs a lot of\\n space, and should be on its own tab\\n\\n\\\n  o     Gantt View - when use search results on page, just show the\\n people that match the search results, but show all timecards When\\n doing a search, if there are multiple timecards which match the search\\n criteria, change the time focus display by zooming in or zooming\\n out to show the right view (by 3 months, month, week) to show the\\n timecards that match the search.  Do not gray out the timecards which\\n do not match the search criteria\\n\\n\\\n  o     \\n\\n\\\n  (New for Fusion)  Alternate Gantt chart display - As in the Manage\\n Timecards search results table, this table listing will also allow\\n for an alternate view of the timecard search results in a Gantt chart\\n display.  This display would allow the user to scroll through time\\n to find timecards for any of his workers.  There would be additional\\n detail about each timecard as the manager clicks on the timecard\\n cell.  There would also be a color coded legend to define what timecard\\n status each timecard block represents.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:03:32'),(4302,'Feature',1304,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Use of Employment Header\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1304\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> The following are fields which are delivered by default by Core\\n HR:\\n\\n\\\n  Shown By default\\n\\n\\\n  o     Display Name\\n\\n\\\n  o     Person Number\\n\\n\\\n  o     Assignment Number\\n\\n\\\n  o     Job\\n\\n\\\n  o     Position\\n\\n\\\n  o     Department\\n\\n\\\n  o     Location\\n\\n\\\n  o     Manager\\n\\n\\\n  Hidden Fields\\n\\n\\\n  1.     WorkPhoneNumber\\n\\n\\\n  2.     Home Phone Number\\n\\n\\\n  3.     MobilePhoneNumber\\n\\n\\\n  4.     HomeAddress\\n\\n\\\n  5.     NationalIdentifier\\n\\n\\\n  6.     LegalEmployer\\n\\n\\\n  7.     Country\\n\\n\\\n  8.     WorkRelationshipStatus\\n\\n\\\n  9.     WorkEmailAddress\\n\\n\\\n  10.     PersonalEmailAddress\\n\\n\\\n  11.     BirthDate\\n\\n\\\n  12.     MailingAddress\\n\\n\\\n  13.     EnterpriseStartDate\\n\\n\\\n  14.     StartDate\\n\\n\\\n  15.     LegalEmployerSeniorityDate\\n\\n\\\n  16.     WorkingAtHome\\n\\n\\\n  17.     WorkingHours\\n\\n\\\n  18.     StartTime\\n\\n\\\n  19.     EndTime\\n\\n\\\n  20.     AssignmentCategory\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Worker\'s Picture - Although the header is delivered with the default\\n to have the section open for a worker\'s picture to be imported, Time\\n and Labor can hide the picture on the page.  If a picture is to be\\n displayed, it is maintained in two places:  1.  Manage Personal Information\\n - the HR Specialist can upload the picture. 2.  My Portrait - the\\n Worker can upload the picture themselves.  \\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Primary Assignment - The display of the timecard page will be derived\\n from the layout set and timecard period associated to a worker on\\n his Worker Web Time Entry Setup Profile.  This Profile will be assigned\\n to a worker via Group, based on the common component Group functionality.\\n  The connection between the Worker Web Time Entry Setup Profile and\\n group eligibility will be based on the worker\'s primary assignment.\\n  Since the eligibility is based on primary assignment only, the Assignment\\n label should denote in the header that this is the \\\"primary assignment\\\"\\n header information.\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  In this way, the person accessing the timecard will understand from\\n which assignment the employment header is based, and also not to\\n expect display of additional employment header information from other\\n assignments.  The entry of time (entries in the timecard matrix)\\n does support multiple assignments and allows the user to report time\\n against any assignment.\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Contextual Data - Time and Labor Data fields: display additional fields\\n which are relevant to the timecard for the worker, below the existing\\n employment header fields.\\n\\n\\\n  1.     Timecard period name\\n\\n\\\n  2.     Layout Set\\n\\n\\\n  Reference:  HCM Person Header TUD - http://files.oraclecorp.com/content/AllPu\\n\\\n  blic/SharedFolders/Fusion%20Deliverables-Public/HCM/Core%20HR/TUD/HCM_PER_Pe\\n\\\n  rsonHeader_TUD.doc<pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:04:36'),(4303,'Feature',1304,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Use of Employment Header - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:04:36 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1304\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> The following are fields which are delivered by default by Core\\n HR:\\n\\n\\\n  Shown By default\\n\\n\\\n  o     Display Name\\n\\n\\\n  o     Person Number\\n\\n\\\n  o     Assignment Number\\n\\n\\\n  o     Job\\n\\n\\\n  o     Position\\n\\n\\\n  o     Department\\n\\n\\\n  o     Location\\n\\n\\\n  o     Manager\\n\\n\\\n  Hidden Fields\\n\\n\\\n  1.     WorkPhoneNumber\\n\\n\\\n  2.     Home Phone Number\\n\\n\\\n  3.     MobilePhoneNumber\\n\\n\\\n  4.     HomeAddress\\n\\n\\\n  5.     NationalIdentifier\\n\\n\\\n  6.     LegalEmployer\\n\\n\\\n  7.     Country\\n\\n\\\n  8.     WorkRelationshipStatus\\n\\n\\\n  9.     WorkEmailAddress\\n\\n\\\n  10.     PersonalEmailAddress\\n\\n\\\n  11.     BirthDate\\n\\n\\\n  12.     MailingAddress\\n\\n\\\n  13.     EnterpriseStartDate\\n\\n\\\n  14.     StartDate\\n\\n\\\n  15.     LegalEmployerSeniorityDate\\n\\n\\\n  16.     WorkingAtHome\\n\\n\\\n  17.     WorkingHours\\n\\n\\\n  18.     StartTime\\n\\n\\\n  19.     EndTime\\n\\n\\\n  20.     AssignmentCategory\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Worker\'s Picture - Although the header is delivered with the default\\n to have the section open for a worker\'s picture to be imported, Time\\n and Labor can hide the picture on the page.  If a picture is to be\\n displayed, it is maintained in two places:  1.  Manage Personal Information\\n - the HR Specialist can upload the picture. 2.  My Portrait - the\\n Worker can upload the picture themselves.  \\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Primary Assignment - The display of the timecard page will be derived\\n from the layout set and timecard period associated to a worker on\\n his Worker Web Time Entry Setup Profile.  This Profile will be assigned\\n to a worker via Group, based on the common component Group functionality.\\n  The connection between the Worker Web Time Entry Setup Profile and\\n group eligibility will be based on the worker\'s primary assignment.\\n  Since the eligibility is based on primary assignment only, the Assignment\\n label should denote in the header that this is the \\\"primary assignment\\\"\\n header information.\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  In this way, the person accessing the timecard will understand from\\n which assignment the employment header is based, and also not to\\n expect display of additional employment header information from other\\n assignments.  The entry of time (entries in the timecard matrix)\\n does support multiple assignments and allows the user to report time\\n against any assignment.\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Contextual Data - Time and Labor Data fields: display additional fields\\n which are relevant to the timecard for the worker, below the existing\\n employment header fields.\\n\\n\\\n  1.     Timecard period name\\n\\n\\\n  2.     Layout Set\\n\\n\\\n  Reference:  HCM Person Header TUD - http://files.oraclecorp.com/content/AllPu\\n\\\n  blic/SharedFolders/Fusion%20Deliverables-Public/HCM/Core%20HR/TUD/HCM_PER_Pe\\n\\\n  rsonHeader_TUD.doc<pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:04:47'),(4304,'Feature',1305,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Status\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1305\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Shows the status of the Timecard. Saved and Submitted are the\\n timestore statuses, but there are additional derived statuses which\\n can be used for providing additional data to the user:\\n\\n\\\n  \\tNew -  Upon entering into a newly created timecard, the status would\\n be displayed\\n\\\n  \\tDraft - Upon save of the timecard, the status would be displayed.\\n\\\n  \\tSubmitted- Upon submitting of the timecard, the status would be submitted\\n\\\n  \\tPending Resolution - new status to denote administrator intervention\\n is needed to resolve errors before timecard can be routed for approval\\n\\\n  \\tApproved - Upon approval of all time entries in the timecard, the\\n status would be approved\\n\\\n  \\tRejected - Upon rejection of 1 time entry, the status would be rejected\\n\\\n  \\tIn Error - Upon 1 hard error in timecard, the status would be in error.\\n  This would occur if there is an offline batch processing of time\\n rules in Group Time Entry or import processing.  Otherwise, for all\\n application validations and time rules, the timecard errors need\\n to be resolved before saving or submitting the timecard.\\n\\\n  \\tTransferred -  Upon successful response reply from the integrating\\n application, the timecard is considered transferred.  The two integrating\\n applications to transfer timecards to include: Payroll, Projects  \\n\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue 1:  To be determined in Time Entry LBA, if will\\n implement the \\\"Transfer To\\\" column information which was implemented\\n in EBS OTL R12.1.2. which states if the timecard has been transferred\\n to \\\"Projects, Payroll, None\\\".  This would separate the Transfer information\\n out of the Timecard Status field into its own Transfer To field. \\n\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue 2:  To be determined if we will add another timecard\\n status of \\\"Pending Resolution\\\" which denote timecards which have\\n errors needing resolution by an administrator or timekeeper before\\n they can be routed for approval.  This is incorporated into the Validations\\n of Processed Time design section.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:05:07'),(4305,'Feature',1306,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"HR Person Contextual Action \"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1306\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Uptake the use of the HR Person Contextual Action for any display\\n of the worker\'s name, especially in the Person Header section of\\n the timecard.  Upon clicking on the orange icon to the left of the\\n person\'s name, a pop up dialog box will offer additional information\\n about Leslie for further communication.  Upon clicking the Close\\n button, the dialog box will close.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:05:16'),(4306,'Feature',1305,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Status - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:05:07 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1305\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Shows the status of the Timecard. Saved and Submitted are the\\n timestore statuses, but there are additional derived statuses which\\n can be used for providing additional data to the user:\\n\\n\\\n  \\tNew -  Upon entering into a newly created timecard, the status would\\n be displayed\\n\\\n  \\tDraft - Upon save of the timecard, the status would be displayed.\\n\\\n  \\tSubmitted- Upon submitting of the timecard, the status would be submitted\\n\\\n  \\tPending Resolution - new status to denote administrator intervention\\n is needed to resolve errors before timecard can be routed for approval\\n\\\n  \\tApproved - Upon approval of all time entries in the timecard, the\\n status would be approved\\n\\\n  \\tRejected - Upon rejection of 1 time entry, the status would be rejected\\n\\\n  \\tIn Error - Upon 1 hard error in timecard, the status would be in error.\\n  This would occur if there is an offline batch processing of time\\n rules in Group Time Entry or import processing.  Otherwise, for all\\n application validations and time rules, the timecard errors need\\n to be resolved before saving or submitting the timecard.\\n\\\n  \\tTransferred -  Upon successful response reply from the integrating\\n application, the timecard is considered transferred.  The two integrating\\n applications to transfer timecards to include: Payroll, Projects  \\n\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue 1:  To be determined in Time Entry LBA, if will\\n implement the \\\"Transfer To\\\" column information which was implemented\\n in EBS OTL R12.1.2. which states if the timecard has been transferred\\n to \\\"Projects, Payroll, None\\\".  This would separate the Transfer information\\n out of the Timecard Status field into its own Transfer To field. \\n\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue 2:  To be determined if we will add another timecard\\n status of \\\"Pending Resolution\\\" which denote timecards which have\\n errors needing resolution by an administrator or timekeeper before\\n they can be routed for approval.  This is incorporated into the Validations\\n of Processed Time design section.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:05:29'),(4307,'Feature',1307,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Message Display\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1307\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Messaging to User - Allow for ability to configure and display\\n messages to the timecard user.   This may be done via the output\\n of Time Interaction Rules.\\n \\n\\\n  a. Tip of the Day - a message type that is offered by some users,\\n which can have different messages displayed to the timecard user\\n on dynamic basis.\\n\\\n  b. Message Section - a section of the timecard needs to be offered\\n to display messages to the timecard user, below the employment header\\n section.  No more than 3 messages can be displayed in the message\\n display area.  Global messages pertaining to the entire timecard\\n should be displayed in this area, if there is no time entry context.\\n\\\n  c. Time Interaction Rules - these types of rules would allow the user\\n to define any conditions to trigger the output of messages to the\\n timecard user and could be assigned to any groups of workers via\\n Worker Core Processing Time and Labor Setup Profile.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:06:30'),(4308,'Feature',1307,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Message Display - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:06:30 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1307\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Messaging to User - Allow for ability to configure and display\\n messages to the timecard user.   This may be done via the output\\n of Time Interaction Rules.\\n \\n\\\n  a. Tip of the Day - a message type that is offered by some users,\\n which can have different messages displayed to the timecard user\\n on dynamic basis.\\n\\\n  b. Message Section - a section of the timecard needs to be offered\\n to display messages to the timecard user, below the employment header\\n section.  No more than 3 messages can be displayed in the message\\n display area.  Global messages pertaining to the entire timecard\\n should be displayed in this area, if there is no time entry context.\\n\\\n  c. Time Interaction Rules - these types of rules would allow the user\\n to define any conditions to trigger the output of messages to the\\n timecard user and could be assigned to any groups of workers via\\n Worker Core Processing Time and Labor Setup Profile.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:06:38'),(4309,'Feature',1308,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Timecard Page Actions \"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1308\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>a.  Next button - takes user to the Timecard Review page, from\\n the Timecard Entry page\\n\\\n  b.  Save button - offers Save and Save and Close options\\n\\\n  c.  Cancel - cancels user out of timecard and returns them to prior\\n navigation\\n\\\n  d.  Submit button - enabled on the Timecard Review page, it  will\\n allow the user to submit the timecard.  Validations and rules will\\n be applied upon submission of the timecard.  If there are any resulting\\n errors, the user will be kept on the Timecard Entry page, will have\\n highlighted errors and will need to resolve the errors before successfully\\n resubmitting the timecard.  Once the timecard is successfully submitted,\\n the user will get a confirmation pop-up that the timecard has been\\n successfully submitted and will have an option to print (a read-only\\n review page of the timecard) or click OK.\\n\\\n  e.  Send Timecard for Resolution button (new) - If the user cannot\\n successfully resolve the errors, he should be able to select an action\\n \\\"Send Timecard for Resolution\\\" and this will save the timecard data\\n and route the timecard to an administrator for error resolution.\\n  Upon resolving the errors, the timecard can be resubmitted.  \\n\\\n  \\t\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue:  Save button, whether the label can be \\\"Save as\\n Draft\\\". UX to determine\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue:  Additional button for \\\"Send Timecard for Resolution\\\"\\n to transfer the timecard to an administrator or timekeeper for resolution\\n of errors which the worker cannot resolve (i.e. setup object changes)\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:06:52'),(4310,'Feature',1306,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: HR Person Contextual Action -FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:05:16 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1306\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Uptake the use of the HR Person Contextual Action for any display\\n of the worker\'s name, especially in the Person Header section of\\n the timecard.  Upon clicking on the orange icon to the left of the\\n person\'s name, a pop up dialog box will offer additional information\\n about Leslie for further communication.  Upon clicking the Close\\n button, the dialog box will close.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:07:01'),(4311,'Feature',1308,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Page Actions -FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:06:52 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1308\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>a.  Next button - takes user to the Timecard Review page, from\\n the Timecard Entry page\\n\\\n  b.  Save button - offers Save and Save and Close options\\n\\\n  c.  Cancel - cancels user out of timecard and returns them to prior\\n navigation\\n\\\n  d.  Submit button - enabled on the Timecard Review page, it  will\\n allow the user to submit the timecard.  Validations and rules will\\n be applied upon submission of the timecard.  If there are any resulting\\n errors, the user will be kept on the Timecard Entry page, will have\\n highlighted errors and will need to resolve the errors before successfully\\n resubmitting the timecard.  Once the timecard is successfully submitted,\\n the user will get a confirmation pop-up that the timecard has been\\n successfully submitted and will have an option to print (a read-only\\n review page of the timecard) or click OK.\\n\\\n  e.  Send Timecard for Resolution button (new) - If the user cannot\\n successfully resolve the errors, he should be able to select an action\\n \\\"Send Timecard for Resolution\\\" and this will save the timecard data\\n and route the timecard to an administrator for error resolution.\\n  Upon resolving the errors, the timecard can be resubmitted.  \\n\\\n  \\t\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue:  Save button, whether the label can be \\\"Save as\\n Draft\\\". UX to determine\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue:  Additional button for \\\"Send Timecard for Resolution\\\"\\n to transfer the timecard to an administrator or timekeeper for resolution\\n of errors which the worker cannot resolve (i.e. setup object changes)\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:07:30'),(4312,'Feature',1325,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Actions - Add\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1325\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide ability to add  one or more rows in timecard matrix for\\n time entry.  The rows may need to be inserted between existing rows\\n or would be new rows for additional entry.   The row needs to be\\n added where the user expects, either in between existing rows or\\n as the last row.   \\n\\\n  In prior versions of Enterprise Time and Labor and EBS Time and Labor,\\n new rows were added at the end of existing rows.  Rows could also\\n be inserted between existing rows.  Additionally, users could tab\\n to a + (plus) sign on existing row to add a new row below it.  This\\n action worked well for users who are used to tabbing through their\\n timecard fields for quick entry of time.\\n\\\n  The Fusion table design pattern is to add a new row at the top of\\n a table using the add action button.  To allow flexibility for users,\\n we need to offer configuration which allows \\\"add row\\\" to add to the\\n bottom of the table, or to the top of the table.  Adding a row to\\n the bottom of the table is important for clock time users to see\\n the clock times displayed in ascending order.  It is also a general\\n expectation of timecard users to add rows to the bottom of their\\n timecard.  Additionally, we need to allow for an add row icon at\\n the row level, for users to tab to the field and click enter to add\\n a new row below.  This is important for those reporting many rows\\n in a single timecard or timekeepers entering many entries per worker\\n or workers.   The need for this flexibility arose from strong customer\\n feedback,  registered in the HCM_Time&Labor_Usability_Feedback_Report_FINAL.\\n\\\n  doc\\n (3/26/2010)\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:07:55'),(4313,'Feature',1326,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Actions - Delete\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1326\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide ability to select a row in the timecard matrix and select\\n the action of deleting a line to delete highlighted row.  User should\\n be able to delete one or more rows at once, based on rows selected.\\n  Once the user selects the action to delete, a warning message will\\n be issued to the user.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:08:03'),(4314,'Feature',1327,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Actions - Clear Hours\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1327\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>This new timecard action was tested with customers and accepted\\n in the HCM_Time&Labor_Usability_Feedback_Report_FINAL.doc.  This\\n allows the user to select any or all rows in the timecard and clear\\n out the hours.  The usefulness of this action is the user can retain\\n attributes from prior timecards and just change the hours.  \\n\\\n  For the user who wants to clear one row, he should select the row\\n and use the timecard menu action of \\\"Clear Hours\\\", or use the toolbar\\n icon.  If the user wants to clear all hours for the timecard,  he\\n should be able to select all rows of the timecard and use the Clear\\n Hours action.  A message should pop-up to the user to alert them\\n to the fact that all hour entries will be reset to zero.  Please\\n refer to the Select All Fusion Guideline for selecting all rows whether\\n visible or not:\\n\\\n  http://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines4/tblInteraction.html#selectAll\\n\\\n  From the Guideline:  When both row and column selection are implemented,\\n clicking the intersection of the row and column headers selects all\\n rows in the table\'s entire data set, regardless of whether they are\\n in view or not. However, there may be a design limitation if the\\n number of rows in the timecard exceed 300 rows: Note: In order to\\n turn on the Select All functionality, the SQL statement must include\\n an OrderBy and the table must have less than 300 rows.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:08:11'),(4315,'Feature',1328,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Actions - Duplicate\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1328\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>To allow the user to select a line to copy.  The user selects\\n the line to duplicate, and selects the action of duplicate.  A line\\n will be inserted below the selected line, with the same attributes\\n and hours and a new line number.  Would also like to be able to highlight\\n multiple rows and select duplicate to be able to copy down multiple\\n rows.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:08:18'),(4316,'Feature',1329,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Actions - Save As Template\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1329\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Existing Timecard Action in EBS R12.  Allow user to save time\\n entries as a private template which can be applied in future.  User\\n just has to save a name against the private template.  If the user\\n is utilizing a semi-monthly or monthly timecard and saves that timecard\\n as a private template, only the attributes will be saved for use,\\n as the hours cannot be applied correctly from one period to the next.\\n  A business message will be displayed to the user, upon clicking\\n OK,  that \\\"Only atrributes will be saved for this template based\\n on timecard period length\\\".</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:08:28'),(4317,'Feature',1330,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Actions - Apply Template\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1330\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Existing Timecard Action in EBS R12.  Allows user to select a\\n private, public or dynamic timecard template and apply to the timecard.\\n  The public templates are created by a Time and Labor administrator\\n and are assigned to workers via a Setup Options Profile.  Private\\n templates are created by the worker for his exclusive use.  This\\n action will be a menu-action, as well as a button on the toolbar\\n which will trigger a pop-up display.  The reason to offer as a button\\n is it is a regularly used function on the timecard.\\n\\n\\\n  The Apply Template pop-up will have the following actions for the\\n user to take:\\n\\\n  1.\\tSelect a template (private, public or dynamic)\\n\\\n  2.\\tSelect Apply Only Attributes - When selecting a template which\\n contains time attributes and hours, this option allows the user to\\n just apply the attributes displayed on the template, and not apply\\n the hours.\\n\\n\\\n  3.\\tSelect Append , Replace or Cancel as actions\\t\\n\\\n  o\\tAppend  (Add to Entries):  When a user selects this option for applying\\n the template, the content of the template will be added to existing\\n data which is in the timecard matrix.  The new data from the template\\n should be added below the existing data, as per behavior in EBS R12.\\n\\\n  o\\tReplace: When a user selects this option for applying the template,\\n they are replacing all existing data in the timecard matrix and adding\\n the data from the selected template.\\n\\\n  o\\tCancel: Cancel out of the pop-up and close the pop-up\\n\\n\\\n  The private and public templates displayed for use will be derived\\n from the layout set and timecard period assigned to the employee.\\n  If the timecard period associated to the worker does not match private\\n or public templates, they will not be made available in the template\\n selection.   Dynamic templates are not dependent on timecard periods.  \\n\\\n  The timecard user can also navigate to Manage Templates page and create\\n a new private template from scratch.  Dynamic timecard templates\\n which come delivered with the product are:\\n\\\n  1 Work Schedule - This template generates time and labor entries from\\n the worker\'s\\n\\\n  Schedule.  The schedule will now be derived from the person schedule\\n assignment in Core HR, so we need to ensure holidays as well as scheduled\\n work and off days are properly displayed in the timecard.\\n\\\n  2  Last Period Timecard - This template uses the previous time entry\\n data. You\\n\\\n  typically use this template when an employee is working on the same\\n projects week after week, eliminating the need for repetitive entry\\n of project and task numbers.\\n\\\n  3 Project Assignments - This template generates time and labor entries\\n from the\\n\\\n  project, type, and hours information held in Oracle Project Resource\\n Management for the worker\'s assignments. \\n\\\n  \\tIn addition to the ability to choose from private, public or dynamic\\n timecard templates, there are other actions a \\tuser can take.  \\n\\\n  ??\\tSet As Default:  User can select one of the timecard templates as\\n the default template.  This action allows the user to have that template\\n automatically prepopulate the timecard for every future timecard\\n created, unless the default is changed or no longer selected.  The\\n selection of the default template will be an action on the worker\\n Timecards Workarea landing page, in a Timecard Options portlet. \\n See Analytics FDD for Workarea functionality.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:08:36'),(4318,'Feature',1331,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: View Menu Options - Freeze, Sort, Detach\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1331\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Enable the following view menu actions for the timecard matrix- \\n\\n\\\n  Freeze - Allow the user the ability to freeze columns within the timecard\\n matrix and for that display to persist from session to session. \\n There would be a menu action and toolbar action to allow the user\\n to enable the freezing of columns.  The user will highlight the column\\n he wants to freeze on, and selects the Freeze action from the toolbar\\n or menu action.  All columns to the right of that frozen column can\\n be scrolled across horizontally, while the columns to the left  of\\n the frozen column will remain static.  This is the same concept if\\n you used \\\"Window, Freeze Panes\\\" action in an excel spreadsheet.\\n\\\n  For this timecard example below, the user could freeze the Hours Type\\n column, so that all the days to the right of the Hours Type column\\n could be scrolled to the left, while the user could still see the\\n Project, Task, Expenditure Type and Hours Type he entered on that\\n row.  This functionality would allow the user to keep the context\\n of what he is entering for each day.\\n\\n\\\n  Sort - Allow user to sort the columns in the timecard matrix in ascending\\n or descending manner.  Each column heading would have a sort indicator\\n to note that the column can be sorted in an ascending or descending\\n manner.  Example of sort display can be seen in the display of the\\n column \\\"Contract Number\\\" below, in which when the column is highlighted,\\n a black arrow pointing down is displayed, and 2 white arrows are\\n shown to the right of the column header to allow the user to sort\\n ascending (up arrow) or descending order (Down arrow).  Note: Not\\n all fields will be sortable in the timecard, the ability to sort\\n the field will be configured in the layout component and  layout\\n set in the Time Entry Page Composer.\\n\\n\\\n  Detach - this viewing function supports the ADF table component to\\n allow a user to click on a Detach action from the Timecard Matrix\\n toolbar.  This will maximize the table display to enhance the viewing\\n of the timecard columns.  This action is available from the View\\n drop down menu as well as the toolbar.  This table action is formerly\\n known as Maximize.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:08:49'),(4319,'Feature',1332,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Line Numbers\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1332\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Display line numbers in the timecard matrix which would assist\\n in identifying lines for error messages, as well as easy reference\\n to a line in question for review or troubleshooting.  If a user inserts\\n a new row in between existing rows, then the new row and subsequent\\n rows would need to be renumbered accordingly. </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:08:57'),(4320,'Feature',1333,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Inline Error Messages\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1333\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Allow for easy inline error messages for invalid time, with indications\\n on the reported cells.  The inline error messaging should allow for\\n the highlighting of any field in the timecard matrix, including a\\n particular entry of hours or Start and Stop times.\\n\\\n  Offer a \\\"Show Messages\\\" button as a way to get the \\\"error message\\n list\\\" dialog . Also, the user will have the dialog box open when\\n they access the timecard entry page if there are existing errors.\\n  Will also have the dialog expanded when selecting the  Next button,\\n if error messages still exist.\\n\\\n  If the user clicks on the message link and is taken to the line in\\n error, he should always be able to access the error message listing\\n dialog, to view all messages again.\\n\\\n  Message Summary: Including columns for Line Number, Description, Message\\n Type and Source of Error  along with the Error Message Listing. The\\n contents of the Error Message listing should include the following:\\n\\\n  o\\tline number of the error message, displayed in the timecard matrix\\n\\\n  o\\tmessage type (error, warning, informational, other)\\n\\\n  o\\tsource of the error message (application),\\n\\\n  o\\tdate of the error if applicable.  \\n\\\n  o\\trecommended action for the error condition, if applicable\\n\\\n  o\\tcounter of number of error/warning/information messages\\n\\\n  o\\tability to navigate to each message from the dialog box\\n\\\n  o\\tAs the user views each message per line, he should be able to select\\n that message and be transferred to the relevant line in the timecard\\n matrix.  This pertains to line level messages only.  If global level\\n messages are displayed, no line navigation would be available.  The\\n navigation to the applicable line in the timecard matrix could occur\\n by either highlighting that row in the error message display or have\\n the message hyperlinked.  If the message is hyperlinked, once the\\n user clicks on the link, the cursor should move to that line in the\\n timecard matrix.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:09:15'),(4321,'Feature',1309,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Default Timecard Templates\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1309\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide ability to auto populate timecard with dynamic, private\\n or public timecard templates which are assigned to the worker.  The\\n dynamic templates in scope for Fusion v2 (Work Schedule,  Last Timecard\\n  and Project Resource Management template).  The assignment of templates\\n  will occur in the Worker Web Time Entry Setup Profile (formerly\\n Preferences).\\n\\\n  The worker will be able to change their default template on their\\n Timecard Options in the Timecards Workarea landing page.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:09:22'),(4322,'Feature',1313,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Period Message\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1313\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide indication or message to timecard user they are in a\\n prior or future time period.  This needs to be offered in the central\\n messaging section in the Timecard header.  This is a reminder to\\n the user in case they are updating the wrong timecard period.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:09:29'),(4323,'Feature',1314,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Submission Due Date\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1314\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Allow for the association of a timecard submission due date and\\n time  to a timecard, so users can be made aware of when they need\\n to submit their timecards.  These due dates can be attached to the\\n repeating period definitions which are associated to the worker in\\n their Setup Options Profile.  \\n\\\n  This Due Date can be used to display in the timecard header.  It can\\n also be used for reminder notifications to workers or timekeepers,\\n and can be used for analytics to determine who are repeatedly late\\n in submitting timecards.  Some users just use timecard due dates,\\n some also associate a time to that date, to ensure that the payroll\\n processing department can plan on when to begin their payroll processes.\\n  If a time is defined along with the date, a time zone may need to\\n be supplied, unless the time is assumed to be the local time or the\\n time zone is derived from the user regional Preferences.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:09:38'),(4324,'Feature',1315,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Mid period display of  Changed Employment Information\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1315\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> Provide ability to see different person information for mid\\n timecard period changes.   This would cover changes that can occur\\n as a result of workers changing paygroups, departments jobs or positions\\n which can occur during a time period .  The user wants to see the\\n old and new data for this change.  \\n\\\n  As we are only displaying employment header data from Primary Assignment\\n in Fusion v2, this would only be applicable for changes to the primary\\n assignment during the timecard period.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:09:45'),(4325,'Feature',1316,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Review Page\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1316\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide a table display view of one week at a time.  The days\\n will be displayed vertically on the left hand column and all attributes\\n will be displayed to the right of the days.  Daily detail and comments\\n will be separate columns in the grid.  All data from pop-up pages\\n on attributes and details will be concatenated in an Attributes and\\n Details column.\\n\\\n  If there is more than one week in the review, there should be the\\n ability to collapse each week display, so the vertical scroll of\\n the page is lessened and the user an focus on the detail of one week\\n at a time.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:09:53'),(4326,'Feature',1318,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Configurable Sections for Timecard Entry, Review and Confirmation Pages \"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1318\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Refer to Time Entry Page Composer FDD for full details.  Some\\n of the requested configurations include:\\n\\\n  a.\\tAbility to collapse by default some sections\\n\\\n  b.\\tAbility to retain order of rows entered by line number in Time\\n Detail section \\n\\\n  c.\\tRule Results - ability to show the hours type against the correct\\n rows \\n\\\n  d.\\tRule Results - ability to have flexibility to show any hour types \\n\\\n  e.\\tTime Summary - would like to see this section on top of the page\\n for Confirmation page\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:10:04'),(4327,'Feature',1319,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Printable Timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1319\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> Provide ability to print timecard upon timecard submission.\\n  Customers would prefer to see the time detail in the matrix as you\\n have it normal time entry page, as opposed to vertical columns. \\n All drill down detail sections need to be flattened so they all appear\\n on the printable page.  (Note: UX design in progress, similar to\\n Timecard Review page)\\n\\\n  The printable version of the timecard can be initiated from two places:\\n  1. from the confirmation pop-up displayed upon submission of the\\n timecard 2.  from the Viewable version of the timecard available\\n at any time.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:10:10'),(4328,'Feature',1320,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Configurable fields in timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1320\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide ability to display appropriate fields in timecard matrix\\n based on delivered layout.  The use of delivered layouts will depend\\n on the configurability offered in the Layout Editor FDD for Timecard.\\n  ( See Appendix A for existing delivered layouts from R12.)  The\\n ability to configure the display of each section of the timecard\\n online is new for Fusion.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:10:17'),(4329,'Feature',1321,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Time Attribute Storage and Pre-population of values\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1321\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>We will have the ability to offer entry in the timecard to perform\\n any of the following functions:\\n\\\n  o\\tcontain a single attribute with a related value set, which contains\\n a where clause to filter the displayed values as needed\\n\\\n  o\\tcan link a single attribute to another single attribute on a layout\\n set (these linked attributes can be displayed or hidden on the timecard).\\n  As these attributes are linked, the entry of one attribute value\\n can default the value of the 2nd or related attribute\\n\\\n  o\\tcontain an attribute which is displayed on the timecard, which can\\n store but not display values for related attributes \\n\\\n  o\\tcan have an attribute automatically populated with a default value,\\n upon entry into the timecard based on the person\'s information\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:10:26'),(4330,'Feature',1322,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Override Default Regional Preferences\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1322\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>As per setup in the Timecard Layout Sets, allow for users to\\n be able to enter time in different formats  and decimal precisions\\n for dates, time, numbers, timezone and currencies.  The default regional\\n preferences are delivered by ApplCore from the main Preferences menu\\n link.  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:10:34'),(4331,'Feature',1323,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Smart choice lists\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1323\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>All time attributes which previously used LOVs must have values\\n displayed with smart choice lists, including all descriptive flexfields.\\n  This is a Fusion requirement for UI.  These smart choice lists will\\n list values such as Most Recently Used values before showing a search\\n link to search for more entries.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:10:43'),(4332,'Feature',1324,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Display hours and clock times\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1324\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Must Have Justification :  Support Existing EBS OTL R12 functionality\\n of clock and hours display\\n\\\n  Provide ability to support a mixture of reporting hours and start/stop\\n times with the correct related totals for the day.  For each entry\\n there should either be a set of times or hours displayed.  Format\\n of time should support military or civilian display.\\n\\\n  If the set of times (Start and Stop Time) is entered, then we need\\n to allow that entry of time,  can be used as a Stop Time for a Start\\n Time as well as be used as a Start time for the next set of Start\\n and Stop Times.  For example: \\n\\\n  8:00 am\\t\\tStart\\n\\\n  10:00 am\\tStop\\n\\\n  10:00 am\\tStart\\n\\\n  12:00 pm\\tStop\\n\\\n  In this example, 10:00am is used as a Stop time for one set of times,\\n and a Start time for the next set of times reported..\\n\\\n  If the user does enter Start and Stop Time for a time entry, they\\n should not be entering hours for that same entry.  The entry of hours\\n or times are mutually exclusive.  As a result, if times are entered\\n we could gray out the hours field for that entry to ensure the user\\n does not enter both.  The same is true for entering hours, we could\\n gray out the Start and Stop Times field for that entry.  If this\\n is not feasible, then we need to ensure we have time entry rules\\n to generate an error message when a user enters both times and hours\\n for the same time entry.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 13:10:52'),(4333,'Feature',1323,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Smart choice lists - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:10:43 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1323\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>All time attributes which previously used LOVs must have values\\n displayed with smart choice lists, including all descriptive flexfields.\\n  This is a Fusion requirement for UI.  These smart choice lists will\\n list values such as Most Recently Used values before showing a search\\n link to search for more entries.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:11:12'),(4334,'Feature',1325,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Actions - Add - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:07:55 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1325\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide ability to add  one or more rows in timecard matrix for\\n time entry.  The rows may need to be inserted between existing rows\\n or would be new rows for additional entry.   The row needs to be\\n added where the user expects, either in between existing rows or\\n as the last row.   \\n\\\n  In prior versions of Enterprise Time and Labor and EBS Time and Labor,\\n new rows were added at the end of existing rows.  Rows could also\\n be inserted between existing rows.  Additionally, users could tab\\n to a + (plus) sign on existing row to add a new row below it.  This\\n action worked well for users who are used to tabbing through their\\n timecard fields for quick entry of time.\\n\\\n  The Fusion table design pattern is to add a new row at the top of\\n a table using the add action button.  To allow flexibility for users,\\n we need to offer configuration which allows \\\"add row\\\" to add to the\\n bottom of the table, or to the top of the table.  Adding a row to\\n the bottom of the table is important for clock time users to see\\n the clock times displayed in ascending order.  It is also a general\\n expectation of timecard users to add rows to the bottom of their\\n timecard.  Additionally, we need to allow for an add row icon at\\n the row level, for users to tab to the field and click enter to add\\n a new row below.  This is important for those reporting many rows\\n in a single timecard or timekeepers entering many entries per worker\\n or workers.   The need for this flexibility arose from strong customer\\n feedback,  registered in the HCM_Time&Labor_Usability_Feedback_Report_FINAL.\\n\\\n  doc\\n (3/26/2010)\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:11:33'),(4335,'Feature',1309,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Default Timecard Templates - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:09:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1309\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide ability to auto populate timecard with dynamic, private\\n or public timecard templates which are assigned to the worker.  The\\n dynamic templates in scope for Fusion v2 (Work Schedule,  Last Timecard\\n  and Project Resource Management template).  The assignment of templates\\n  will occur in the Worker Web Time Entry Setup Profile (formerly\\n Preferences).\\n\\\n  The worker will be able to change their default template on their\\n Timecard Options in the Timecards Workarea landing page.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:11:58'),(4336,'Feature',1324,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Display hours and clock times - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:10:52 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1324\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Must Have Justification :  Support Existing EBS OTL R12 functionality\\n of clock and hours display\\n\\\n  Provide ability to support a mixture of reporting hours and start/stop\\n times with the correct related totals for the day.  For each entry\\n there should either be a set of times or hours displayed.  Format\\n of time should support military or civilian display.\\n\\\n  If the set of times (Start and Stop Time) is entered, then we need\\n to allow that entry of time,  can be used as a Stop Time for a Start\\n Time as well as be used as a Start time for the next set of Start\\n and Stop Times.  For example: \\n\\\n  8:00 am\\t\\tStart\\n\\\n  10:00 am\\tStop\\n\\\n  10:00 am\\tStart\\n\\\n  12:00 pm\\tStop\\n\\\n  In this example, 10:00am is used as a Stop time for one set of times,\\n and a Start time for the next set of times reported..\\n\\\n  If the user does enter Start and Stop Time for a time entry, they\\n should not be entering hours for that same entry.  The entry of hours\\n or times are mutually exclusive.  As a result, if times are entered\\n we could gray out the hours field for that entry to ensure the user\\n does not enter both.  The same is true for entering hours, we could\\n gray out the Start and Stop Times field for that entry.  If this\\n is not feasible, then we need to ensure we have time entry rules\\n to generate an error message when a user enters both times and hours\\n for the same time entry.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:12:16'),(4337,'Feature',1319,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Printable Timecard - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:10:10 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1319\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> Provide ability to print timecard upon timecard submission.\\n  Customers would prefer to see the time detail in the matrix as you\\n have it normal time entry page, as opposed to vertical columns. \\n All drill down detail sections need to be flattened so they all appear\\n on the printable page.  (Note: UX design in progress, similar to\\n Timecard Review page)\\n\\\n  The printable version of the timecard can be initiated from two places:\\n  1. from the confirmation pop-up displayed upon submission of the\\n timecard 2.  from the Viewable version of the timecard available\\n at any time.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:12:36'),(4338,'Feature',1332,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Line Numbers - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:08:57 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1332\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Display line numbers in the timecard matrix which would assist\\n in identifying lines for error messages, as well as easy reference\\n to a line in question for review or troubleshooting.  If a user inserts\\n a new row in between existing rows, then the new row and subsequent\\n rows would need to be renumbered accordingly. </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:12:57'),(4339,'Feature',1326,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Actions - Delete - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:08:03 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1326\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide ability to select a row in the timecard matrix and select\\n the action of deleting a line to delete highlighted row.  User should\\n be able to delete one or more rows at once, based on rows selected.\\n  Once the user selects the action to delete, a warning message will\\n be issued to the user.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 13:13:24'),(4340,'Feature',1334,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Daily Details  Icon and Pop Up Page\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1334\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide ability to drill down into daily details for the Timecard\\n to enter additional fields required by retrieving applications (DFFs).\\n  The display will be on a daily basis, to allow the user to have\\n different entries for each day listed on the timecard matrix row.\\n  This can be done with a Daily Details icon at the end of each row.\\n   Only the days which contain hours or time entries should be displayed\\n on the Daily Details pop-up for display.  That will make it easier\\n for the user to only enter detail for the days which are required. \\n\\\n  In the Daily Details, we will also have a Comments field for each\\n day for daily comments as well.  Initial prototypes tested at customer\\n feedback sessions in January 2010 had separate icons for Daily Comments\\n and Daily Details, to easily differentiate the two areas of entry.\\n  To consolidate columns, the two areas are being combined into the\\n Daily Details icon.\\n\\\n  Additionally, there should be a hover over the icon for the user to\\n see the attributes which are contained inside the pop-up page for\\n entry as an easy reference.  \\n\\\n  Finally, so the user or approver knows if there is data contained\\n in this pop-up page, there should be different modes of the icon,\\n one to display when the pop-up page has no data entered, and another\\n to display when the pop-up page does contain data.\\n\\\n  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:02:52'),(4341,'Feature',1335,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Additional Attributes Icon and Pop Up Page\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1335\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Allow for configurable option to display one  pop-up page in\\n the matrix to display dependent fields of a previously entered time\\n attribute or additional optional attributes which the user did not\\n want placed on the main timecard matrix.  This information is at\\n a row level, pertaining to all hours entered on that row.  Examples\\n of dependent fields are input types for Elements or \\\"estimate to\\n complete\\\" for a Project ID.\\n\\\n  Additionally, there should be a hover over the icon for the user to\\n see the attributes which are contained inside the pop-up page for\\n entry as an easy reference.  \\n\\\n  Finally, so the user or approver knows if there is data contained\\n in this pop-up page, there should be different modes of the icon,\\n one to display when the pop-up page has no data entered, and another\\n to display when the pop-up page does contain data.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:03:01'),(4342,'Feature',1336,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Work Location Attribute\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1336\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>For Payroll use, we will offer a Work Location layout component,\\n which will offer a smart choice listing of concatenated values: city,\\n state, county and zip code.  The reason for the concatenated values\\n is for easy entry, so that the user does not need to enter 4 separate\\n fields.  Additionally, we should see if we can add \\\"smart filtering\\\"\\n in which not all work location combinations have to be shown to each\\n employee, if there is a way to filter that list per person.  \\n\\n\\\n  These values will be stored separately as City, State, County and\\n Zip Code in Time and Labor.  When they are transferred to Fusion\\n Payroll, they will be transferred into the appropriate fields: Area1,\\n Area2, Area3 and Area4. \\n\\n\\\n  This combination of values  is specifically for use by the US Localization\\n for Payroll.  Other localizations will use this functionality as\\n well, with ability to use different input values based on the localization,\\n but always utilizing Area1 - Area4 fields.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:03:10'),(4343,'Feature',1337,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Report Absences\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1337\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>If not integrating with Absence Management, should be able to\\n report an absence by using Hours Types of Absence values and enter\\n a number of hours against that absence in the Timecard Matrix.  If\\n integrating with Fusion Absence Maangement, the absence display,\\n entry, validation,  approval  and retrieval of absences will be determined\\n further in Time & Labor and Absence Integration FDD.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:03:17'),(4344,'Feature',1336,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Work Location Attribute - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 14:03:10 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1336\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>For Payroll use, we will offer a Work Location layout component,\\n which will offer a smart choice listing of concatenated values: city,\\n state, county and zip code.  The reason for the concatenated values\\n is for easy entry, so that the user does not need to enter 4 separate\\n fields.  Additionally, we should see if we can add \\\"smart filtering\\\"\\n in which not all work location combinations have to be shown to each\\n employee, if there is a way to filter that list per person.  \\n\\n\\\n  These values will be stored separately as City, State, County and\\n Zip Code in Time and Labor.  When they are transferred to Fusion\\n Payroll, they will be transferred into the appropriate fields: Area1,\\n Area2, Area3 and Area4. \\n\\n\\\n  This combination of values  is specifically for use by the US Localization\\n for Payroll.  Other localizations will use this functionality as\\n well, with ability to use different input values based on the localization,\\n but always utilizing Area1 - Area4 fields.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 14:03:37'),(4345,'Feature',1337,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Report Absences - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 14:03:17 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1337\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>If not integrating with Absence Management, should be able to\\n report an absence by using Hours Types of Absence values and enter\\n a number of hours against that absence in the Timecard Matrix.  If\\n integrating with Fusion Absence Maangement, the absence display,\\n entry, validation,  approval  and retrieval of absences will be determined\\n further in Time & Labor and Absence Integration FDD.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 14:04:26'),(4346,'Feature',1303,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Gantt legends\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1303\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \" \\n      <ol>\\n      <dt>The following are the timecard status colors which will be offered for display:<dt>\\n        <dd>\\tDraft</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tIn Error</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tSubmitted</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tApproved</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tRejected</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tTransferred</dd>\\n        <p>Nice to have:  Not Started Box: to indicate timecards which have not \\n        yet been created</p>\\n\\n      \\n        \\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:04:42'),(4347,'Feature',1302,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Transfer to field\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1302\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> \\n      ability to see to which time consumers the timecard has been transferred,\\n as a column in the Search Results - Transferred to Payroll, Project\\n Portfolio Management, both, etc.  This is enhancement in 12.1.1.\\n Release to be brought into Fusion.  \\n      </pre>\\n        \\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:04:50'),(4348,'Feature',1301,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Approval Data Flow\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1301\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> \\n      Have a column related to the Approval Data Flow of the timecard, with\\n further drill down detail as to where the timecard is in the approval\\n chain\\n        </pre>\\n        \\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:04:59'),(4349,'Feature',1300,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Saved searches\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1300\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> \\n        a user will have the ability to save his basic and/or advanced searches\\n for future use.\\n        </pre>\\n        \\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:05:09'),(4350,'Feature',1299,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Sort fields\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1299\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> \\n        Display the most recent timecards on top of the grid.  Ensure the\\n columns are sortable on the grid\\n        </pre>\\n        \\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:05:17'),(4351,'Feature',1298,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Manager Timecard Search page-Create Timecard Action\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1298\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> Manager must select a worker (choice list of available direct\\n reports in the table)  and then select a date from a calendar widget,\\n to create for the correct timecard period, then be taken to the Create\\n Timecard page for that worker.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:05:26'),(4352,'Feature',1297,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Manage Timecards- Create Timecard\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1297\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Create Timecard action - transfers user to a new timecard  \\n        (also a button on toolbar)</pre>\\n        \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:05:35'),(4353,'Feature',1296,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Manage Timecards- Advanced search\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1296\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"\\n                    <p>\\tAllows the user the ability to string multiple lines of search attributes together with \\\"and\\\" and \\\"or\\\" statements, using the following search fields and operators, with the ability to configure additional search fields based on added time entry fields.  </p>                     \\n                    <dt>Search can be executed using the following parameters</dt>\\n                    <dd>Detail Comment : Comment of a timecard</dd>\\n                    <dd>Reported Hours: hours reported againts a timecard</dd>\\n                    <dd>Timecard Period: timecard\'s start and end dates</dd>\\n                    <dd>Project: Project information</dd>\\n                    <dd>Timecard Submission Date: submission date</dd>                    \\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Timecard Due Date (new for Fusion): timecards validity date.</dd>                    \\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Task: Task information of the project selected</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Timecard Comment: Comment against a timecard.</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dt>Operators for search</dt>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Less than</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Less Than or Equal to</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Not Equal To</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Equal To</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Greater Than</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Greater Than or Equal To</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Like</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Not Like</dd>\\n\\n                    \\n                   \\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:09:28'),(4354,'Feature',1295,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Manage Timecards- Basic search\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1295\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> Basic search is performed using \'From date\', \'to date\', \'Timecard\\n        Status\' and \'Person Name\'.  Based on the user input system will run\\n a query\\n        to the tables and display the timecards in the gantt chart.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:09:38'),(4355,'Feature',1294,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page-Manage Timecards: Gantt Display\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1294\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre> \\n        Allows for an alternate view of the timecard search results in a Gantt\\n chart display.   The user can toggle between the table and Gantt\\n chart view.  This Gantt chart display would allow the user to scroll\\n through time to find timecards for any period of time for which he\\n has access.  There would be additional detail about each timecard\\n as the user clicks on the timecard cell.  There would also be a color\\n coded legend to define what timecard status each timecard block represents. \\n\\\n  The search fields that a user enters in the Search section of the\\n page should reflect the same results on the table or Gantt chart\\n view.  However, the Gantt view can show extended view over a greater\\n period of time, whereas the table view will need a From and To Date\\n defined to narrow the results.\\n\\\n  There will also be the ability to overlay icons on the color blocks\\n to show additional information like \\\"late timecards\\\".\\n\\\n  In the weekly view of the gantt chart, the start and end date of the\\n period can be displayed on the color block for the user to easily\\n see which timecard period the color block pertains to.  There will\\n also be a hover over on each timecard color block with information\\n on the timecard period, the submission date, number of total hours,\\n and approvers.  If the user clicks on a color block once, they will\\n be navigated directly to the selected timecard.</p>  \\n\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:09:46'),(4356,'Feature',1303,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Gantt legends - FDD\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 14:04:42 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1303\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \" \\n      <ol>\\n      <dt>The following are the timecard status colors which will be offered for display:<dt>\\n        <dd>\\tDraft</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tIn Error</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tSubmitted</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tApproved</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tRejected</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tTransferred</dd>\\n        <p>Nice to have:  Not Started Box: to indicate timecards which have not \\n        yet been created</p>\\n\\n      \\n        \\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-02 14:10:09'),(4357,'Feature',1398,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Private Template Page\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1398\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>This page facilitates Time and Labor workers pre-populating new\\n or existing timecards with sets of commonly used timecard entries. \\n\\n\\\n  The template contains the timecard matrix information, derived from\\n the worker\'s currently assigned layout set and timecard period associated\\n to their Worker Web Time Entry Setup Profile.   The worker is also\\n able to name the template and populate the timecard matrix for reuse\\n in other timecards.\\n\\n\\\n  There are four delivered repeating period types: daily, weekly, semi-monthly\\n and monthly which can be used as timecard periods.  We will support\\n daily, weekly and biweekly timecard periods for a worker to enter\\n both hours (times) and time attribute values.  If the worker is creating\\n a private template for a semi-monthly or monthly timecard period,\\n the template will just show attributes as editable with no display\\n of days , with a business message displayed  upon creation that \\\"Only\\n attribute values can be defined for this timecard period type.\\\"\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  A. Create Template page\\n\\n\\\n  The following are the fields to be displayed when creating a new private\\n template:\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Section: Template Detail\\n\\n\\\n  o     Template Name: user defined name for the private template\\n\\n\\\n  o     Status:  Active/Inactive  \\n\\n\\\n  A worker can inactivate a private template if it is no longer usable\\n for their current layout or timecard period.  The default value is\\n active.\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Section: Template Entry\\n\\n\\\n  o     Timecard matrix for entering hours/ Start/Stop Times and additional\\n time attribution such as  Hours Type, Work Location, Cost Center.\\n\\n\\\n  o     Days of the week will be displayed without dates for those timecard\\n periods which can have pre-populated hours (daily, weekly, biweekly).\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Page Actions:   Save  - user saves the page and remains on page\\n\\n\\\n  Save and Close - user saves the page and page closes\\n\\n\\\n  Cancel - user cancels out of the page\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  B. Edit Template page\\n\\n\\\n  All template entry fields are editable on the private template as\\n well as the page name.\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Page Actions:   Save \\n\\n\\\n  Save and Close\\n\\n\\\n  Cancel</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:10:21'),(4358,'Feature',1397,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Manage Templates\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1397\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>This page facilitates Time and Labor workers managing their own\\n pre-populated timecard templates which can be applied for future\\n timecard entry use.  They can search, create, view or delete or export\\n templates from the search/search results page.\\n        These are the search fields for finding a private template:\\n\\n\\\n  o     Basic/Advanced Search page for Repeating Time Periods which\\n contain the following fields:\\n\\n\\\n  Basic Search\\n\\n\\\n  o     Name - User name for private template\\n\\n\\\n  Advanced Search\\n\\n\\\n  o     Name - User name for private template\\n\\n\\\n  o     Status - Inactive or Active\\n\\n\\\n  o     Operator - this field is coupled with both the Name field, to\\n allow more flexibility to search\\n\\n\\\n  The options for the operator values are: \\n\\n\\\n  o     Greater than\\n\\n\\\n  o     Equals\\n\\n\\\n  o     Does Not Equal\\n\\n\\\n  o     Less Than\\n\\n\\\n  o     Greater Than\\n\\n\\\n  o     Between\\n\\n\\\n  o     Not Between\\n\\n\\\n  o     Is Blank\\n\\n\\\n  o     Is Not Blank\\n\\n\\\n  Also allow for wildcard search in each field.\\n\\\n  Search Results Section\\n\\n\\\n  o     Search Results Grid : displays the user created private templates,\\n and also provides actions which can be applied to private templates.\\n  The columns listed in the search results are the following:\\n\\n\\\n  o     Name - User name for private template\\n\\n\\\n  o     Status - Inactive or Active\\n\\n\\\n  o     Total Hours- Total number of hours for created template\\n\\n\\\n  There will not be seeded private templates, since these are specific\\n to the user..\\n\\\n  Actions for Manage Templates\\n\\n\\\n  o     Create Template\\n\\n\\\n  When using the \\\"create\\\" action or \\\"create\\\" button from the Search\\n Results grid, a user will be able to create a new private template\\n\\n\\\n  o     Edit Template\\n\\n\\\n  When user selects the \\\"edit\\\" action or \\\"edit\\\" button from the Search\\n Results grid, a user will be able to edit an existing private template.\\n\\n\\\n  o     Delete Template\\n\\n\\\n  When user selects the \\\"delete\\\" action or \\\"delete\\\" button from the\\n Search Results grid, a user will be able to delete an existing private\\n template.\\n\\n\\\n  o     Download Template\\n\\n\\\n  When user selects the \\\"Download Template\\\" menu action or \\\"Download\\n template\\\" toolbar button from the Search Results grid, a user will\\n be able to export the template and related choice list values to\\n an excel spreadsheet via ADFdi integration.  See Section 2.3.7 for\\n more information on the ADFdi flow to support disconnected or offline\\n entry mode.  </pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-02 14:10:36'),(4359,'Feature',1310,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Additional Information Sections - FDD\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 14:10:29 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1310\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 134\ndescription: \"<pre>Provide more real estate in the timecard page so the user can\\n focus on the timecard matrix for time entry.  As a result, there\\n will be additional pieces of information that a user may want to\\n reference, but not view at all times. These sections should be \\\"information\\n on demand\\\", available to the user when needed.  Such sections include:\\n\\\n  a.\\tTimecard Comments - comments for the overall timecard\\n\\\n  b.\\tAccrua