270,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4820,'Flow',271,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4821,'Flow',272,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4822,'Flow',273,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4823,'Flow',274,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4824,'Flow',275,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4825,'Flow',276,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4826,'Flow',277,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4827,'Flow',278,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4828,'Flow',279,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4829,'Flow',280,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-06 00:24:06'),(4830,'Path',26,'create','4',NULL,'2011-05-06 12:50:49'),(4831,'Step',133,'create','2',NULL,'2011-05-06 16:39:55'),(4832,'Step',134,'create','2',NULL,'2011-05-06 16:39:59'),(4833,'Step',135,'create','2',NULL,'2011-05-06 16:40:03'),(4834,'Feature',1388,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Individual Timecard: RequiredFunctionality for Line Manager - FDD\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 16:10:57 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1388\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \"<pre>The following are the requirements for the manager\'s use of timecards:\\n\\n\\\n  1.     All requirements covered in the Individual Timecard: Worker\\n  for Must Have , Should Have and Nice to Have\\n\\n\\\n  2.     Provide ability to easily report time or view time for manager\'s\\n direct reports\\n\\n\\\n  3.     Person navigation- Use of Mini My Organization in Regional\\n Area of timecard page for manager to select other workers.\\n\\n\\\n  4.     Allow manager to access his own timecard in the listing of\\n timecards from his Manage Timecards navigation, to avoid navigating\\n to a different task for reporting time for his own timecard\\n\\n\\\n  5.     Easy to find navigation for managers to report time, such as\\n from Manager Dashboard Actions, My Organization and Employee\'s Portrait,\\n as well as the Timecard Work Area\\n\\n\\\n  6.     Allowance for additional fields for manager entry which their\\n workers\' may not have security access to view</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:01:09'),(4835,'Feature',1389,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Individual Timecard: Should Have Functionality for Line Manager - FDD\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 16:11:02 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1389\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \"<pre>Messaging Rules for Flexible Page Header - Use Message Rules\\n to generate output at the top of the timecard to indicate someone\\n other than the worker is reporting time for him/her.  This allows\\n for the use of the same time entry page for all users - timekeeper,\\n manager or worker.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:01:47'),(4836,'Feature',1475,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-08 02:03:44'),(4837,'Feature',1475,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: \"Individual Timecard: Line Manager Navigation Options - Portrait Gallery - jf\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-08 02:03:44 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-08 02:03:44 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1475\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:04:29'),(4838,'Feature',1390,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Individual Timecard: Line Manager Navigation Options - Person Portrait - jf\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-08 02:03:18 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1390\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \"<pre>A manager may be accessing his information from different navigations,\\n depending on his other tasks he is performing.  The following would\\n be some navigational options for the manager:\\n\\n\\\n  1.     Person Portrait:  Navigating from Welcome Tab: Person Gallery->Person\\n Portrait:Actions:Report Time:Time Entry page for current timecard\\n period\\n\\n\\\n  2.     Portait Gallery - >Organization Chart:Actions.-->Report Time:Timecard\\n Entry page for default timecard period\\n\\n\\\n  3.     Timecard Work Area: Navigating from Manager Resources:Time\\n Management:Timecards Work Area; Create or View Timecards options\\n\\n\\\n  4.     Manager Dashboard: Manager Resources:My Organization:Actions:Report\\n Time:Time Entry page for current timecard period</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:05:02'),(4839,'Feature',1476,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-08 02:05:55'),(4840,'Feature',1476,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: \"Individual Timecard: Line Manager Navigation Options - Timecard Workarea - jf\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-08 02:05:55 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-08 02:05:55 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1476\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:06:31'),(4841,'Feature',1477,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-08 02:06:49'),(4842,'Feature',1477,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: \"Individual Timecard: Line Manager Navigation Options - 4.\\tManager Dashboard: Manager Resources - jf\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-08 02:06:49 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-08 02:07:12 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1477\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:07:38'),(4843,'Feature',1293,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Manager Timecard Search page-Manage Timecards\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 13:02:50 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1293\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \"<pre> This is the manager\'s timecard search page converted to use \\n        the Oracle Applications Fusion middleware.  This replaces the View Recent \\n        Timecards in EBS Time and Labor R12. This is the search page to access \\n        timecards of  the manager\'s direct reports, with a default display of \\n        status on their most recent timecards.</pre>\\n        \\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:13:06'),(4844,'Feature',1295,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Manage Timecards- Basic search - FDD\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 14:12:45 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1295\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \"<pre> Basic search is performed using \'From date\', \'to date\', \'Timecard\\n        Status\' and \'Person Name\'.  Based on the user input system will run\\n a query\\n        to the tables and display the timecards in the gantt chart.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:13:54'),(4845,'Feature',1293,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Manager Timecard Search page-Manage Timecards  - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-08 02:13:20 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1293\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \"\\tThis page facilitates Time and Labor self service users searching for timecards.\\r\\n\\\n  \\tIn R12 there was a separate navigation link for Timecard Search and another link to Time Entry, which displayed a Recent Timecard search.\\r\\n\\\n  \\tIn Fusion, there will just be one search navigation which will bring the user to the Manage Timecards page.  In the Regional pane, there will be a \\xE2\\x80\\x9CSearch: Timecards\\xE2\\x80\\x9D pane which will be the Basic Search for timecards.  The fields for searching for the worker will be timecard period or From and To Date.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\t The Manage Timecards page will also offer the basic and advanced search functionality for a user to narrow their search to date ranges, etc.  Additionally, there will be two views of the timecards search results: table and Gantt chart view.   The default table view can show all timecards for the worker, with the most recent timecard periods sorted to the top of the table.  All columns in the search results should be sortable and allow the user to retain a different sort order if he chooses.  As the user enters fields for search, the search results will be replaced with the relevant results.  There should be a refresh default option to bring back the default view of the timecard results.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n        \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:14:43'),(4846,'Feature',1296,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Manage Timecards- Advanced search - FDD\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 14:13:44 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1296\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \"\\n                    <p>\\tAllows the user the ability to string multiple lines of search attributes together with \\\"and\\\" and \\\"or\\\" statements, using the following search fields and operators, with the ability to configure additional search fields based on added time entry fields.  </p>                     \\n                    <dt>Search can be executed using the following parameters</dt>\\n                    <dd>Detail Comment : Comment of a timecard</dd>\\n                    <dd>Reported Hours: hours reported againts a timecard</dd>\\n                    <dd>Timecard Period: timecard\'s start and end dates</dd>\\n                    <dd>Project: Project information</dd>\\n                    <dd>Timecard Submission Date: submission date</dd>                    \\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Timecard Due Date (new for Fusion): timecards validity date.</dd>                    \\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Task: Task information of the project selected</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Timecard Comment: Comment against a timecard.</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dt>Operators for search</dt>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Less than</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Less Than or Equal to</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Not Equal To</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Equal To</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Greater Than</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Greater Than or Equal To</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Like</dd>\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<dd>Not Like</dd>\\n\\n                    \\n                   \\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:15:16'),(4847,'Feature',1392,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Worker Timecards Display: Timecards Portlet - FDD\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 16:36:44 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1392\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: \"<pre>This page allows the worker to view his timecards in timecard\\n period descending order, with the most recent timecards listed on\\n top of the table.\\n\\n\\\n  o     Add filter with options    Show: Timecards in Progress; All Timecards\\n\\n\\\n  o     For  \\\"Timecards in Progress\\\" - let the worker select the timecard\\n statuses they want to see for this filtered view in a drop down list\\n of multi-select checkboxes\\n\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Status options:  Draft, Submitted, In Error, Pending\\n Resolution, Rejected, Approved\\n\\n\\\n  o     Enable QBE for the table, for sorting on any column, with ability\\n to default back to the delivered view\\n\\n\\\n  o     Show Table View or Calendar View\\n\\n\\\n  o     Add View Menu, so user can hide any optional columns in table:\\n Audit Data, Recorded Hours, Submission Date, Approval Chain\\n\\n\\\n  Columns Displayed:\\n\\n\\\n  v     Timecard Period - display of the start and end date of the timecard\\n period, with a hyperlink to allow editable access to this timecard.\\n  If the user does not have edit access to the timecard, the link\\n will be disabled, with a hover over message to alert the user \\\"You\\n do not have edit access to this timecard.\\\"\\n\\n\\\n  v     Timecard Status - status of the timecard (working, saved, submitted,\\n approved, rejected, in error, etc)\\n\\n\\\n  v     Approval Chain - icon displayed if the timecard has entered\\n the approval workflow process, the user can click on the icon and\\n see a display of where the timecard is in the approval process by\\n which approvers have acted on the timecard and which approvers remain.\\n  This section will be using existing AMX UI display for showing approval\\n status/history.\\n\\n\\\n  v     Recorded Hours - a total of all hours reported on the timecard.\\n  The display would be in hours and minutes, as there are no rounding\\n rules in effect.\\n\\n\\\n  v     Submission Date - the date the timecard has been submitted for\\n approval\\n\\n\\\n  v     Timecard Due Date - (new for Fusion)  would be nice to show\\n the due date of the timecard, especially if it is not submitted as\\n of yet\\n\\n\\\n  v     Audit Data - this column will display an icon if the timecard\\n contains change and late audit data (reason codes for why time was\\n changed or was entered late)\\n\\n\\\n  v     View Summary- this column will display an icon to allow the\\n user to view the timecard (will display the \\\"View Timecard\\\" layout\\n page per the associated layout set.  This is a read only version\\n of the timecard which is similar to the Timecard Review page, containing\\n time entry detail, rule results, time summary information, change\\n and late audit summary information,  and audit details.  Additionally,\\n there will be a print function from this page,\\n\\n\\\n  v     Delete - this column will display an \\\"X\\\" to the user to allow\\n delete of the timecard if the user has access to perform this function,\\n based on his Time and Labor Setup Profile options.  If the user attempts\\n to delete a timecard, a warning message will be issued to ask \\\"Delete\\n selected timecard\\\"?\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Table Actions\\n\\n\\\n  v     Create Timecard-  when clicking on this action, a calendar widget\\n will pop up for the worker to select a date, which will select the\\n timecard period which intersects with that date,   then be taken\\n to the Create Timecard page for that worker.\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Calendar View\\n\\n\\\n  There will be a view of timecards for the user to view and access\\n his timecards from a calendar display.  There will be three months\\n displayed at a time, with the ability to scroll to the next three\\n or prior three months. Each timecard period will be highlighted on\\n the calendar, and the user just needs to click on any date in that\\n timecard period, and will be transferred to that timecard.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:17:31'),(4848,'Feature',1293,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Manager Timecard Search page-Manage Timecards  - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-08 02:14:43 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1293\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \"\\tThis page facilitates Time and Labor self service users searching for timecards.\\r\\n\\\n  \\tIn R12 there was a separate navigation link for Timecard Search and another link to Time Entry, which displayed a Recent Timecard search.\\r\\n\\\n  \\tIn Fusion, there will just be one search navigation which will bring the user to the Manage Timecards page.  In the Regional pane, there will be a \\xE2\\x80\\x9CSearch: Timecards\\xE2\\x80\\x9D pane which will be the Basic Search for timecards.  The fields for searching for the worker will be timecard period or From and To Date.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\t The Manage Timecards page will also offer the basic and advanced search functionality for a user to narrow their search to date ranges, etc.  Additionally, there will be two views of the timecards search results: table and Gantt chart view.   The default table view can show all timecards for the worker, with the most recent timecard periods sorted to the top of the table.  All columns in the search results should be sortable and allow the user to retain a different sort order if he chooses.  As the user enters fields for search, the search results will be replaced with the relevant results.  There should be a refresh default option to bring back the default view of the timecard results.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Columns in Search Results Table\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tTimecard Period \\xE2\\x80\\x93 display of the start and end date of the timecard period, with a hyperlink to allow editable access to this timecard.  If the user does not have edit access to the timecard, the link will be disabled, with a hover over message to alert the user \\xE2\\x80\\x9CYou do not have edit access to this timecard.\\xE2\\x80\\x9D\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tTimecard Status \\xE2\\x80\\x93 status of the timecard (working, saved, submitted, approved, rejected, in error, etc)\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tApproval Flow Data \\xE2\\x80\\x93 icon displayed if the timecard has entered the approval workflow process, the user can click on the icon and see a display of where the timecard is in the approval process by which approvers have acted on the timecard and which approvers remain.  This section will be using existing AMX UI display for showing approval status/history.\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tRecorded Hours \\xE2\\x80\\x93 a total of all hours reported on the timecard.  The display would be in hours and minutes, as there are no rounding rules in effect.\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tSubmission Date \\xE2\\x80\\x93 the date the timecard has been submitted for approval\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tTimecard Due Date \\xE2\\x80\\x93 (new for Fusion)  would be nice to show the due date of the timecard, especially if it is not submitted as of yet \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tAudit Data \\xE2\\x80\\x93 this column will display an icon if the timecard contains change and late audit data (reason codes for why time was changed or was entered late)\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tView Summary\\xE2\\x80\\x93 this column will display an icon to allow the user to view the timecard (will display the \\xE2\\x80\\x9CView Timecard\\xE2\\x80\\x9D layout page per the associated layout set.  This is a read only version of the timecard which is similar to the Timecard Review page, containing time entry detail, rule results, time summary information, change and late audit summary information,  and audit details.  Additionally, there will be a print function from this page,\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tDelete \\xE2\\x80\\x93 this column will display an \\xE2\\x80\\x9CX\\xE2\\x80\\x9D to the user to allow delete of the timecard if the user has access to perform this function, based on his Time and Labor Setup Profile options.  If the user attempts to delete a timecard, a warning message will be issued to ask \\xE2\\x80\\x9CDelete selected timecard\\xE2\\x80\\x9D?\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Toolbar and Menu Options for Search Results Table\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tCreate Timecard action \\xE2\\x80\\x93 transfers user to a new timecard  (also a button on toolbar\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tView Menu \\xE2\\x80\\x93 to allow hiding of columns were are optional such as:  Audit Data, Recorded Hours, Submission Date, Approval Chain\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tEnable QBE \\xE2\\x80\\x93 so user can filter on any column in the search results table\\r\\n\\\n  Fusion additional functionality\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tSaved Searches \\xE2\\x80\\x93 a user will have the ability to save his basic and/or advanced searches for future use.\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tApproval Flow Data \\xE2\\x80\\x93 (New for Fusion)  have a column related to the approval flow data of the timecard, with further drill down detail as to where the timecard is in the approval chain\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tTransfer To -   (New for Fusion)  ability to see to which time consumers the timecard has been transferred, as a column in the Search Results - Transferred to Payroll, Project Portfolio Management, both, etc.  This is enhancement in 12.1.1. Release to be brought into Fusion.  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tCalendar View\\r\\n\\\n  There will be a view of timecards for the user to view and access his timecards from a calendar display.  There will be three months displayed at a time, with the ability to scroll to the next three or prior three months. Each timecard period will be highlighted on the calendar, and the user just needs to click on any date in that timecard period, and will be transferred to that timecard.\\r\\n \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:22:44'),(4849,'Feature',1302,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Transfer to field- FDD\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 14:17:24 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1302\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \"<pre> \\n      ability to see to which time consumers the timecard has been transferred,\\n as a column in the Search Results - Transferred to Payroll, Project\\n Portfolio Management, both, etc.  This is enhancement in 12.1.1.\\n Release to be brought into Fusion.  \\n      </pre>\\n        \\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:24:58'),(4850,'Feature',1294,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page-Manage Timecards: Gantt Display - FDD\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 14:11:38 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1294\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \"<pre> \\n        Allows for an alternate view of the timecard search results in a Gantt\\n chart display.   The user can toggle between the table and Gantt\\n chart view.  This Gantt chart display would allow the user to scroll\\n through time to find timecards for any period of time for which he\\n has access.  There would be additional detail about each timecard\\n as the user clicks on the timecard cell.  There would also be a color\\n coded legend to define what timecard status each timecard block represents. \\n\\\n  The search fields that a user enters in the Search section of the\\n page should reflect the same results on the table or Gantt chart\\n view.  However, the Gantt view can show extended view over a greater\\n period of time, whereas the table view will need a From and To Date\\n defined to narrow the results.\\n\\\n  There will also be the ability to overlay icons on the color blocks\\n to show additional information like \\\"late timecards\\\".\\n\\\n  In the weekly view of the gantt chart, the start and end date of the\\n period can be displayed on the color block for the user to easily\\n see which timecard period the color block pertains to.  There will\\n also be a hover over on each timecard color block with information\\n on the timecard period, the submission date, number of total hours,\\n and approvers.  If the user clicks on a color block once, they will\\n be navigated directly to the selected timecard.</p>  \\n\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:26:01'),(4851,'Feature',1303,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Manager Timecard Search page: Gantt legends - FDD\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 14:10:09 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1303\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 147\ndescription: \" \\n      <ol>\\n      <dt>The following are the timecard status colors which will be offered for display:<dt>\\n        <dd>\\tDraft</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tIn Error</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tSubmitted</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tApproved</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tRejected</dd>\\n        <dd>\\tTransferred</dd>\\n        <p>Nice to have:  Not Started Box: to indicate timecards which have not \\n        yet been created</p>\\n\\n      \\n        \\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-08 02:26:21'),(4852,'BusinessProcess',21,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4853,'BusinessProcessElement',368,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4854,'BusinessProcessElement',369,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4855,'BusinessProcessElement',370,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4856,'BusinessProcessElement',371,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4857,'BusinessProcessElement',372,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4858,'BusinessProcessElement',373,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4859,'BusinessProcessElement',374,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4860,'BusinessProcessElement',375,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4861,'BusinessProcessElement',376,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4862,'BusinessProcessElement',377,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4863,'BusinessProcessElement',378,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4864,'BusinessProcessElement',379,'create','1',NULL,'2011-05-09 19:09:12'),(4865,'Bu