d is in the approval process by\r\n   which approvers have acted on the timecard and which approvers remain.\r\n    This section will be using existing AMX UI display for showing approval\r\n   status/history.\r\n  \r\n  v     Recorded Hours - a total of all hours reported on the timecard.\r\n    The display would be in hours and minutes, as there are no rounding\r\n   rules in effect.\r\n  \r\n  v     Submission Date - the date the timecard has been submitted for\r\n   approval\r\n  \r\n  v     Timecard Due Date - (new for Fusion)  would be nice to show\r\n   the due date of the timecard, especially if it is not submitted as\r\n   of yet\r\n  \r\n  v     Audit Data - this column will display an icon if the timecard\r\n   contains change and late audit data (reason codes for why time was\r\n   changed or was entered late)\r\n  \r\n  v     View Summary- this column will display an icon to allow the\r\n   user to view the timecard (will display the \"View Timecard\" layout\r\n   page per the associated layout set.  This is a read only version\r\n   of the timecard which is similar to the Timecard Review page, containing\r\n   time entry detail, rule results, time summary information, change\r\n   and late audit summary information,  and audit details.  Additionally,\r\n   there will be a print function from this page,\r\n  \r\n  v     Delete - this column will display an \"X\" to the user to allow\r\n   delete of the timecard if the user has access to perform this function,\r\n   based on his Time and Labor Setup Profile options.  If the user attempts\r\n   to delete a timecard, a warning message will be issued to ask \"Delete\r\n   selected timecard\"?\r\n  \r\n   \r\n  \r\n  \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:29:02'),(6409,'Feature',1491,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-25 18:29:38'),(6410,'Feature',1491,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Table Functionality\ncreated_at: 2011-05-25 18:29:38 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 18:29:38 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1491\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 156\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:29:55'),(6411,'BusinessProcess',32,'create','11',NULL,'2011-05-25 18:30:04'),(6412,'Path',47,'create','11',NULL,'2011-05-25 18:30:45'),(6413,'Feature',1478,'destroy','3','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Toolbar - Create Timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-05-16 21:08:51 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 18:25:36 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1478\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 156\ndescription: |-\n  Create Icon + text \r\n  \r\n  Create opens a dialog to select the timecard period using a calendar to select a date.\r\n  \r\n  The dates high lighted are for the next timecard period based on a business rule.\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  \r\n  \r\n  UI:\r\n  http://apps-ux.us.oracle.com/Prototypes/HCM/V86_TimeAndLabor_PostCFS/_timeAndLabor/pages/login.htm?url=http://apps-ux.us.oracle.com/Prototypes/HCM/V86_TimeAndLabor_PostCFS/_timeAndLabor/pages/02CLA-overviewEmp.htm\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:32:02'),(6414,'Feature',1489,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Table Toolbar Actions\ncreated_at: 2011-05-25 18:20:30 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 18:31:18 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1489\nfeature_type: Miscellaneous\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 156\ndescription: |-\n  Table Actions\r\n  \r\n  Create Timecard-  when clicking on this action, a calendar widget\r\n   will pop up for the worker to select a date, which will select the\r\n   timecard period which intersects with that date,   then be taken\r\n   to the Create Timecard page for that worker.\r\n  \r\n  Calendar View\r\n  There will be a view of timecards for the user to view and access his timecards from a calendar display.  There will be three months displayed at a time, with the ability to scroll to the next three or prior three months. Each timecard period will be highlighted on the calendar, and the user just needs to click on any date in that timecard period, and will be transferred to that timecard.\r\n  \r\n  Should be a Icon + Text to change views to Calendar\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:34:26'),(6415,'Feature',1480,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Create Timecard Business Rule\ncreated_at: 2011-05-23 17:26:47 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-23 21:45:25 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1480\nfeature_type: Business Rule\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 156\ndescription: |-\n  Selecting any day in a timecard period opens that timecard period.\r\n  \r\n  For example - Calendar displayed\r\n  Select Monday Feb 1, Opens timecard that contains Monday Feb 1.\r\n  \r\n  Select Wednesday Feb 3, opens the timecard that contains Feb 3, which may be the same as the timecard that contains Feb 1.\r\n  \r\n  UI:\r\n  http://apps-ux.us.oracle.com/Prototypes/HCM/V86_TimeAndLabor_PostCFS/_timeAndLabor/pages/login.htm?url=http://apps-ux.us.oracle.com/Prototypes/HCM/V86_TimeAndLabor_PostCFS/_timeAndLabor/pages/02CLA-overviewEmp.htm\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:37:58'),(6416,'Feature',1481,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Create Timecard Default Peiod Business Rule\ncreated_at: 2011-05-23 17:27:16 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-24 23:07:42 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1481\nfeature_type: Business Rule\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 156\ndescription: \"Highlight the timecard period when opening the calendar to one of the following options to:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  EBS OTL R12.1 Enhancement Options: \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tPeriod On or After System Date- Sets the open timecard period from current date for a new timecard\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tEarlier Period Prior to System Date-Sets the earliest not entered timecard period prior to system date for a new timecard.  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tClosest Period Prior to System date-Sets the closest not entered timecard period prior to system date for a new timecard. We may need to offer a window of how far back to go, as the last timecard period may be very far in the past.  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tExample of each of these options:\\r\\n\\\n  Assuming the system date is 15-Mar-2008\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tPeriod on or after System Date: Current timecard for March 17-March 23 would be opened as Timecard for March 15 is already entered.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tClosest Period Prior to System Date:  Would backtrack from system date and open the timecard period which is not yet entered, like Feb 11 to Feb 17.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tEarliest Period Prior to System Date: Would start from the first timecard period and open the timecard period which is not entered. In this case assuming all timecards for year 2007 have been entered excepting the last period, it would default to Dev 31 to Jan 06 period.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:38:01'),(6417,'FunctionalWorkUnit',150,'update','3','--- \nname: General Workarea Features / Rules\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 16:31:29 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-24 23:10:37 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 205\nid: 150\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:40:19'),(6418,'FunctionalWorkUnit',150,'update','3','--- \nname: General Workarea Features / Rules\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 16:31:29 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 18:40:19 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 207\nid: 150\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:51:23'),(6419,'Feature',1358,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Evaluation of Setup Profile Options\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-24 23:11:06 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1358\nfeature_type: Miscellaneous\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support application of Time and Labor Setup Profile options in timecard\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to work in conjunction with Time and Labor Setup Profiles (formerly Preferences) assigned to the worker for timecard display and functions. (See Appendix B for listing of R12 default Preferences).  These setup options will be effective dated, causing possible changes in the timecard over a time period.  This includes the display of fields, timecard sections, timecard process flow, application of rules, timecard access privileges and available templates.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  If there are changes over a timecard period, due to a worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s eligibility changes, the following behaviors would occur for the timecard display:\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTime Audit Rule Set - We will evaluate this option day by day of the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTime Calculation Rule Set - We will evaluate this option day by day of the timecard\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTime Entry Rule Set - We will evaluate this option day by day of the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTime Interaction Rule Set - We will evaluate this option day by day of the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTime Consumer Set - We will evaluate this option day by day of the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tPublic Template Set \\xE2\\x80\\x93 We will display the superset of public templates available for the worker during the timecard period\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tLayout Set \\xE2\\x80\\x93 When a layout set change in the profile for a timecard period, we will split the timecard period and use the layout set relevant to the timecard period.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTimecard Period \\xE2\\x80\\x93 When a timecard period changes for the worker, we will split the timecard period into the valid period instances before and after the effective date of the change.  When the worker navigates to the timecard, he will only have the days displayed which are valid for that timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tAttribute choice lists values change over timecard period-  we will show the superset of values for the period and employ validations to ensure the values are valid for the reported days.\\r\\n\\\n  \\tReference:  http://hcmwiki.us.oracle.com:8880/display/HCM/setupOptions+-+List+of+Setup+Options\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:53:03'),(6420,'FunctionalWorkUnit',167,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-25 18:53:46'),(6421,'Feature',1358,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Evaluation of Setup Profile Options\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 18:53:03 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1358\nfeature_type: Miscellaneous\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support application of Time and Labor Setup Profile options in timecard\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to work in conjunction with Time and Labor Setup Profiles (formerly Preferences) assigned to the worker for timecard display and functions. (See Appendix B for listing of R12 default Preferences).  These setup options will be effective dated, causing possible changes in the timecard over a time period.  This includes the display of fields, timecard sections, timecard process flow, application of rules, timecard access privileges and available templates.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  If there are changes over a timecard period, due to a worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s eligibility changes, the following behaviors would occur for the timecard display:\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTime Audit Rule Set - We will evaluate this option day by day of the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTime Calculation Rule Set - We will evaluate this option day by day of the timecard\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTime Entry Rule Set - We will evaluate this option day by day of the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTime Interaction Rule Set - We will evaluate this option day by day of the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTime Consumer Set - We will evaluate this option day by day of the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tPublic Template Set \\xE2\\x80\\x93 We will display the superset of public templates available for the worker during the timecard period\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tLayout Set \\xE2\\x80\\x93 When a layout set change in the profile for a timecard period, we will split the timecard period and use the layout set relevant to the timecard period.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTimecard Period \\xE2\\x80\\x93 When a timecard period changes for the worker, we will split the timecard period into the valid period instances before and after the effective date of the change.  When the worker navigates to the timecard, he will only have the days displayed which are valid for that timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tAttribute choice lists values change over timecard period-  we will show the superset of values for the period and employ validations to ensure the values are valid for the reported days.\\r\\n\\\n  \\t\\r\\n\\\n  Reference:  http://hcmwiki.us.oracle.com:8880/display/HCM/setupOptions+-+List+of+Setup+Options\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:53:52'),(6422,'FunctionalWorkUnit',150,'update','3','--- \nname: General Workarea Features / Rules\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 16:31:29 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 18:51:23 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 205\nid: 150\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 18:53:57'),(6423,'Feature',1488,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1.0\"\nname: Access to Timecards by Worker\ncreated_at: 2011-05-24 23:46:59 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-24 23:47:14 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1488\nfeature_type: Miscellaneous\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: \"2.3.1.3.1.2.  Description\\r\\n\\\n  \\tA worker may be accessing his information from different navigations, depending on his other tasks he is performing.  The following would be some navigational options for the worker:\\r\\n\\\n  ?\\tPerson Portrait:  Navigating from Welcome Tab? Person Gallery->Person Portrait?Actions?Report Time?Time Entry page for current timecard period\\r\\n\\\n  ?\\tTimecard Work Area: Navigating from My Information?Time?Timecards Work Area; Create or View Timecards options\\r\\n\\\n  ?\\tWorker Dashboard (post v1):  Timecard Portlet? Enter My Timecard?Pop-up page of quick time entry\\r\\n\\\n  ?\\tProject Portfolio Management Team Member Dashboard or Payroll Dashboard could also be options for embedding the timecard for access \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:04:27'),(6424,'Feature',1376,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Period Security Access\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-24 23:12:17 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1376\nfeature_type: Business Rule\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification:    Support Existing EBS Time and Labor R12 Status Allowing Edit functionality \\twith Enhancements\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to restrict access to timecards for prior or future time, by timecard actions,  for workers, managers or timekeepers.   This control will be offered in the Worker and Group Time Entry Time and Labor Setup Profiles, in the Timecard Actions table setup.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  The idea is that for each timecard action (create, edit, delete, view) there will be the ability to define for which timecard statuses the user could take this action.  In addition, there would be the ability to define how many days in the future or past that these actions can take place.  This is an enhancement to design on \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cstatus allowing edits\\xE2\\x80\\x9D preferences in EBS Time and Labor R12.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  If the user is not allowed to take the following Timecard Actions, the following are the expected results: \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Delete Timecard \\xE2\\x80\\x93 will disable the Delete icon in the Recent Timecards table in Timecards Work Area and in Manage Timecards search results page\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Edit Timecard \\xE2\\x80\\x93 the timecard period link will be disabled in the Recent Timecards table in Timecards Work Area and in Manage Timecards search results page.  There will also be a hover over the disabled hyperlink to explain to the user, \\xE2\\x80\\x9CYou do not have edit access to this timecard based on current timecard status\\xE2\\x80\\x9D.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  View Timecard \\xE2\\x80\\x93 if the user cannot view a timecard for a selected timecard period , the view timecard icon will be disabled in the Recent Timecards table in Timecards Work Area and in Manage Timecards search results page.  There will also be a hover over the disabled hyperlink to explain to the user, \\xE2\\x80\\x9CYou do not have view access to this timecard based on current timecard status\\xE2\\x80\\x9D.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  If the user is currently in a timecard and navigates to another timecard , the expected results are:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  a.  User can view but not edit the timecard for that period \\xE2\\x80\\x93 will be taken to a view-only version of the timecard\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  b.  User cannot view or edit the timecard for that period \\xE2\\x80\\x93 will be issued a business message that they do not have access to the selected timecard based on current timecard status. If the user does not have view or edit access to that timecard,  that timecard should not be included in any listing of timecards or timecard counts in related analytics.   Additionally, the calendar widget which allows navigation to another timecard period will not enable a timecard period to which the user is not allowed any access (view and edit mode).\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:07:02'),(6425,'Feature',1488,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1.0\"\nname: Access to Timecards by Worker\ncreated_at: 2011-05-24 23:46:59 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 19:04:27 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1488\nfeature_type: Miscellaneous\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 167\ndescription: \"2.3.1.3.1.2.  Description\\r\\n\\\n  \\tA worker may be accessing his information from different navigations, depending on his other tasks he is performing.  The following would be some navigational options for the worker:\\r\\n\\\n  ?\\tPerson Portrait:  Navigating from Welcome Tab? Person Gallery->Person Portrait?Actions?Report Time?Time Entry page for current timecard period\\r\\n\\\n  ?\\tTimecard Work Area: Navigating from My Information?Time?Timecards Work Area; Create or View Timecards options\\r\\n\\\n  ?\\tWorker Dashboard (post v1):  Timecard Portlet? Enter My Timecard?Pop-up page of quick time entry\\r\\n\\\n  ?\\tProject Portfolio Management Team Member Dashboard or Payroll Dashboard could also be options for embedding the timecard for access \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:10:52'),(6426,'FunctionalWorkUnit',168,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-25 19:12:04'),(6427,'Feature',1492,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-25 19:12:19'),(6428,'Feature',1493,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-25 19:12:29'),(6429,'Feature',1494,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-25 19:13:02'),(6430,'FunctionalWorkUnit',159,'update','3','--- \nname: \"Timecard Search - Regional \"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-23 21:46:37 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 19:11:45 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 213\nid: 159\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:33:47'),(6431,'Feature',1391,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Individual Timecard Search: For Worker\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-24 23:31:26 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1391\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 159\ndescription: \"This page facilitates Time and Labor self service users searching for timecards.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  In R12 there was a separate navigation link for Timecard Search and another link to Time Entry, which displayed a Recent Timecard search.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  In Fusion, there will just be one search navigation which will bring the user to the Manage Timecards page. In the Regional pane, there\\r\\n will be a \\\"Search: Timecards\\\" pane which will be the Basic Search\\r\\n for timecards.  The fields for searching for the worker will be timecard\\r\\n period or From and To Date. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Regional Search will open a Search Tab - where the Basic and Advanced Search options are displayed in the local panel  - Added May 2011.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  The Manage Timecards page will also offer the basic and advanced search\\r\\n functionality for a user to narrow their search to date ranges, etc.\\r\\n  Additionally, there will be two views of the timecards search results:\\r\\n table and Gantt chart view.   The default table view can show all\\r\\n timecards for the worker, with the most recent timecard periods sorted\\r\\n to the top of the table.  All columns in the search results should\\r\\n be sortable and allow the user to retain a different sort order if\\r\\n he chooses.  As the user enters fields for search, the search results\\r\\n will be replaced with the relevant results.  There should be a refresh\\r\\n default option to bring back the default view of the timecard results.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Advanced Search:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Allows the user the ability to string multiple lines of search attributes\\r\\n together with \\\"and\\\" and \\\"or\\\" statements, using the following search\\r\\n fields and operators, with the ability to configure additional search\\r\\n fields based on added timecard fields, which are made available in\\r\\n layout sets.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Fields:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Detail Comment\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Reported Hours\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Period\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Project\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Status\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Submission Date\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Due Date (new for Fusion)\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Task\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Comment\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Operators for Search\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Less Than\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Less Than or Equal to\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Not Equal To\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Equal To\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Greater Than\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Greater Than or Equal To\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Like\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Not Like\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Basic Search\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     From Date\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     To Date\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Period\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Create Timecard button -  when clicking on this action, a calendar\\r\\n widget will pop up for the worker to select a date, which will select\\r\\n the timecard period which intersects with that date,   then be taken\\r\\n to the Create Timecard page for that worker.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Columns in Search Results Table\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Period - display of the start and end date of the timecard\\r\\n period, with a hyperlink to allow editable access to this timecard.\\r\\n  If the user does not have edit access to the timecard, the link\\r\\n will be disabled, with a hover over message to alert the user \\\"You\\r\\n do not have edit access to this timecard.\\\"\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Status - status of the timecard (working, saved, submitted,\\r\\n approved, rejected, in error, etc)\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Approval Flow Data - icon displayed if the timecard has entered\\r\\n the approval workflow process, the user can click on the icon and\\r\\n see a display of where the timecard is in the approval process by\\r\\n which approvers have acted on the timecard and which approvers remain.\\r\\n  This section will be using existing AMX UI display for showing approval\\r\\n status/history.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Recorded Hours - a total of all hours reported on the timecard.\\r\\n  The display would be in hours and minutes, as there are no rounding\\r\\n rules in effect.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Submission Date - the date the timecard has been submitted for\\r\\n approval\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Timecard Due Date - (new for Fusion)  would be nice to show\\r\\n the due date of the timecard, especially if it is not submitted as\\r\\n of yet\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     Audit Data - this column will display an icon if the timecard\\r\\n contains change and late audit data (reason codes for why time was\\r\\n changed or was entered late)\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o     View Summary- this column will display an icon to allow the\\r\\n user to view the timecard (will display the \\\"View Timecard\\\" layo