Feature',1359,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Access for Terminated Workers - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 21:20:19 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1359\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support time consumer needs to stop processing on terminated worker timecards\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  There will be different processing rules which users have with regards to viewing and updating timecards for terminated employees.  In most cases, workers cannot view, update, create or delete any timecards as of their last day of employment. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  For timekeepers, managers or administrators who need to do further processing of timecards for terminated employees, they may have different dates up to which they can do any processing on terminated worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s timecards. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Feedback from payroll localization teams note that administrators (and sometimes his/her managers) should have timecard access up to Final Closing Date. Administrator access should be cut off once the final payment to the employee has been done but it should be dependent on internal regulations of employer, the final payment may be done even during 1 year after termination.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Core Pay will support the following three dates for the termination of a Payroll Relationship, Work Term or Assignment: \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tLast Standard Earning Date (LSED) \\xE2\\x80\\x93 the date on which standard earnings are no longer accumulated. Typically in terminations the Actual Termination Date entered by HR. After the LSED, users can still pay someone a recurring element up to LSPD. \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tLast Standard Process Date (LSPD) \\xE2\\x80\\x93 The last date on which the object (Payroll Relationship, Term, Assignment) is consider for normal processing in the Payroll Run. This date is defaulted from the LSED mentioned above but it can be overridden.  After the LSPD, users can only pay someone that has a non-recurring element. \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tFinal Close Date (FCD) \\xE2\\x80\\x93 The date from which the object is no longer considered for processing, thus is datetrack ended. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Currently in Projects (PPM) setup, there is a profile option which is \\xE2\\x80\\x9CSpecify Number of Days to Display People with Terminated Assignments\\xE2\\x80\\x9D which controls the display of people in various  PPM pages. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  However, there is open discussion if Projects would want to use a final processing date which is available in Core HR.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  The ability to offer flexible setup options for different access needs is an open design issue being discussed with the Payroll and Projects (PPM) team.    This is an open design issue for setup in the Worker Core Processing Setup Profile\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:58:14'),(6449,'Feature',1379,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Audit Trail on Time Cards Report - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 19:39:14 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1379\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification: Support EBS R12.1 Enhancement \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  This report provides the complete history of timecards from its timecard submission to approval stages.  The report displays details such as the number of times a particular timecard is submitted, modified, or deleted, and various actions done by various employees, approvers on a particular timecard.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Reference:  (OTL_TC_Changes_Audit_Report_FDD_6675298_12.1.doc) design document for the design.\\r\\n\\\n  An alternate design option is to display an audit trail at the bottom of each timecard, listing the user, role, action taken and action date .  However, this type of audit cannot account for the deletion of timecards.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:58:18'),(6450,'Feature',1381,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Transfer of partial timecard to other applications - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:30:02 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1381\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: \"Nice to Have Justification:  Customer Request during Customer Feedback Sessions; Current Enterprise TL functionality of being able to pay what is valid\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Allow for option to transfer timecards differently for different worker groups.   For example, if one day is in error for a whole timecard period, user would want days which are correct to be transferred for exempt employees, but for biweekly staff they might want to hold all time in an errored timecard, since there are dependent rules that would execute.  This would be a change in the approval rules, in which only a portion of the timecard would be approved related to the non-errored time, whereas the errored time would not yet be approved.  Therefore a partially approved timecard would be transferred to one or more applications.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:58:22'),(6451,'Feature',1386,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Embedded Timecard in other Applications - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:47:15 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1386\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: |\n  Nice to Have Justification:  Requested Feature from Projects (PPM)\r\n  \r\n  Allow for the timecard to be embedded as a portlet in other applications such as the Project Team Member page in Project \r\n  \r\n  Portfolio Management, or other application dashboards which require time entry.  The related application validations will need to be associated to the portlet, as well as services to store the timecard updates and run relevant time-related rules. \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:58:26'),(6452,'Feature',1392,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Worker Timecards Display: Timecards Portlet - Calendar - 3 months view\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-24 23:07:09 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1392\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: \"Calendar View\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  There will be a view of timecards for the user to view and access\\r\\n his timecards from a calendar display.  There will be three months\\r\\n displayed at a time, with the ability to scroll to the next three\\r\\n or prior three months. Each timecard period will be highlighted on\\r\\n the calendar, and the user just needs to click on any date in that\\r\\n timecard period, and will be transferred to that timecard.\\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:58:29'),(6453,'Feature',1394,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Adoption of 3 Tier Levels of Fusion Employment Model - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-08 02:29:17 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1394\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 150\ndescription: \"<pre>To provide the ability to report time at any of the 3 levels\\n of employment: Work Relationship, Employment terms or Assignments,\\n we need to provide these as components for the users to choose to\\n select for display on their timecard layouts.  Even if the user decides\\n to not to report to the assignment level, it is critical to know\\n that we will always store the reported time in the primary assignment\\n level.\\n\\n\\\n  In our retrieval processes with existing applications such as Project\\n Portfolio Management and Payroll, we need to provide the levels of\\n time reporting that the customer needs, so we need to derive the\\n highest to lowest level of detail when transferring the time data.\\n\\n\\\n  In our timecard validation processes, we also need to validate to\\n the correct employment levels as well, depending on what has been\\n allowed for in the application validation rules.</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:58:33'),(6454,'FunctionalWorkUnit',150,'destroy','3','--- \nname: General Workarea Features / Rules\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 16:31:29 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 18:53:57 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 207\nid: 150\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 19:58:41'),(6455,'Step',346,'update','8','--- \ncomment: \"Tom is navigated to the Manage Time and Labor Setup Profiles UI, to see three tabs for each setup profile types. \"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-25 05:39:23 Z\nbusiness_process_element_id: 513\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 06:01:38 Z\npath_id: 46\nid: 346\nstatus: not_mapped\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 23:26:35'),(6456,'Step',347,'update','8','--- \ncomment: Tom decides to create a new Worker Core Processing Setup Profile.\ncreated_at: 2011-05-25 05:40:44 Z\nbusiness_process_element_id: 526\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 06:01:38 Z\npath_id: 46\nid: 347\nstatus: not_mapped\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 23:26:35'),(6457,'Step',348,'update','8','--- \ncomment: \"\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-25 05:41:17 Z\nbusiness_process_element_id: 515\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 05:41:17 Z\npath_id: 46\nid: 348\nstatus: not_mapped\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 23:40:05'),(6458,'Step',348,'update','8','--- \ncomment: Name=Simple Processing Profile; Description=Profile used for 1st three worker timecard use cases. Effective Start Date= 1/1/2000; Timecard Period=\ncreated_at: 2011-05-25 05:41:17 Z\nbusiness_process_element_id: 515\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 23:40:05 Z\npath_id: 46\nid: 348\nstatus: not_mapped\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 23:57:31'),(6459,'Step',349,'update','8','--- \ncomment: \"\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-25 05:41:25 Z\nbusiness_process_element_id: 528\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 05:41:25 Z\npath_id: 46\nid: 349\nstatus: not_mapped\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 23:57:31'),(6460,'Step',350,'update','8','--- \ncomment: \"\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-25 05:41:36 Z\nbusiness_process_element_id: 519\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 05:41:36 Z\npath_id: 46\nid: 350\nstatus: not_mapped\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 23:57:31'),(6461,'Step',351,'update','8','--- \ncomment: \"\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-25 05:41:46 Z\nbusiness_process_element_id: 527\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 05:41:46 Z\npath_id: 46\nid: 351\nstatus: not_mapped\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-25 23:57:31'),(6462,'Path',46,'update','8','--- \nname: \"UC1: Worker Core Processing Profile\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-25 05:24:52 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 05:24:52 Z\npriority: \"1\"\nid: 46\ndescription: \"Tom Fulbright creates a simple Worker Core Processing Profile \"\nstatus: not_mapped\niteration_id: 1\nbusiness_process_id: 29\n','2011-05-25 23:57:31'),(6463,'FunctionalWorkUnit',151,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Basic Search\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 19:32:08 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 19:48:20 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 202\nid: 151\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:08:02'),(6464,'FunctionalWorkUnit',152,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Advanced Search\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 19:48:51 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 19:48:51 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 202\nid: 152\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:08:02'),(6465,'BusinessArea',202,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Search\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 19:40:03 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 19:40:03 Z\nid: 202\nparent_id: 167\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:08:02'),(6466,'FunctionalWorkUnit',153,'destroy','3','--- \nname: \" Overview Tab - Table\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-16 20:58:20 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-16 20:58:39 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 167\nid: 153\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:08:49'),(6467,'FunctionalWorkUnit',154,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Overview Tab - Calendar\ncreated_at: 2011-05-16 20:58:48 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-16 20:59:02 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 167\nid: 154\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:08:53'),(6468,'BusinessArea',214,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 16:22:35'),(6469,'FunctionalWorkUnit',159,'update','3','--- \nname: \"Timecard Search - Regional \"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-23 21:46:37 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-25 19:33:47 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 207\nid: 159\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:22:45'),(6470,'Feature',1360,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Worker Timecard Personalization Options - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:24:42 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1360\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 148\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support Existing EBS OTL R12 Preference functionality\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to work in conjunction with worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s Timecard Options, a portlet displayed on the worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s Timecards Workarea landing page, which include number of blank timecard rows to be displayed in the timecard and default template to pre-populate the timecard.   Prior to Fusion these were Preferences defined in EBS Time and Labor R12.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Blank timecard rows retained while saving timecard (OTL R12.1 Enhancement HRMS-OTL-21) -This allows timecard users to retain timecard row(s) without any hour values when saving the timecard.  Such rows are available when you want to update the saved timecard at later point of time.  Design concern raised on submission of timecard,  retaining extra blank rows could add up and impact performance online and also not see the use of maintaining blank rows and sending for approval.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Default Template \\xE2\\x80\\x93 If a default timecard template is defined by an administrator or worker, this timecard template will automatically populate a new timecard as it is opened.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:23:22'),(6471,'Feature',1387,'destroy','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Worker Navigation Options - Person Portrait - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:51:10 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1387\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 148\ndescription: |\n  A worker may be accessing his information from different navigations,\r\n   depending on his other tasks he is performing.  The following would\r\n   be some navigational options for the worker:\r\n  \r\n       Person Portrait:  Navigating from Welcome Tab: Person Gallery->Person\r\n   Portrait:Actions:Report Time:Time Entry page for current timecard\r\n   period\r\n  \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:36:16'),(6472,'Feature',1472,'destroy','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Worker Navigation Options - Timecard Work Area - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-05-05 21:48:33 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:51:48 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1472\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 148\ndescription: \"A worker may be accessing his information from different navigations,\\r\\n depending on his other tasks he is performing.  The following would\\r\\n be some navigational options for the worker:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  v     Timecard Work Area: Navigating from My Information:Time:Timecards\\r\\n Work Area; Create or View Timecards options\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:36:19'),(6473,'Feature',1473,'destroy','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Worker Navigation Options - Worker Dashboard - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-05-05 21:48:52 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:51:57 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1473\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 148\ndescription: |\n  A worker may be accessing his information from different navigations,\r\n   depending on his other tasks he is performing.  The following would\r\n   be some navigational options for the worker:\r\n  \r\n  v     Worker Dashboard (post v1):  Timecard Portlet: Enter My Timecard:Pop-up\r\n   page of quick time entry\r\n  \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:36:22'),(6474,'Feature',1474,'destroy','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Worker Navigation Options - Project Portfolio Management - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-05-05 21:49:09 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:52:04 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1474\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 148\ndescription: |-\n  A worker may be accessing his information from different navigations,\r\n   depending on his other tasks he is performing.  The following would\r\n   be some navigational options for the worker:\r\n  \r\n  v     Project Portfolio Management Team Member Dashboard or Payroll\r\n   Dashboard could also be options for embedding the timecard for access</pre>\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:36:27'),(6475,'Feature',1385,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Calendar Time Entry - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:44:42 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1385\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 23\ndescription: \"Nice to Have Justification:  Enhanced calendar ability to update time \\r\\n Provide ability to report time via the use of a calendar.  The calendar can be used to display reported hours, scheduled hours, calculated hours (results from time calculation rules), as well as a method to report time.  The calendar could be color-coded to show the different types of time or the user could change the display type by a choice list.  A user could report time in a variety of ways:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tClick on a day, a pop-up page is display, enter hours and time attributes and upon close of the pop-up, the time will be saved for the day\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tHighlight a range of dates in the calendar, and enter number of hours and time attributes which should be associated to each day in that highlighted range, via a pop up page.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:37:15'),(6476,'Feature',1471,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Calendar Display of Missing Time  - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-05-05 21:45:43 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:46:29 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1471\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 23\ndescription: |\n  Nice to Have Justification:  Recurring Feature in Competitor Functionality\r\n  \r\n  Provide the ability to highlight a calendar view of which days within a timecard period are missing time entry.  This will be helpful to compare for workers who are required to enter time daily on scheduled days, in order to get paid.\r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:37:38'),(6477,'FunctionalWorkUnit',23,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Calendar\ncreated_at: 2011-04-08 00:23:52 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:43:48 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 167\nid: 23\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:37:49'),(6478,'FunctionalWorkUnit',170,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 16:38:27'),(6479,'Feature',1368,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Workflow Notifications - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 22:54:27 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1368\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 148\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support Existing EBS OTL R12 notification functionality and add notifications to complete proper processing of timecards\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  There are various notifications which revolve around the reporting of time.  Below are some of the notifications.  Additional notifications are noted in Item #20 in Section 2.3.1.1. Should Have Functionality for the Worker Timecard.  These notifications would be triggered by different events of the timecard and would trigger workflow tasks.  The output of the workflow notifications could be email notifications, worklist items or both.  Worklist items would display in the main Worklist on the general Welcome tab as well as the on the Timecards Workarea overview page for Time and Labor.  The configuration of which notification types occurs would be in the workflow setup. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Currently in EBS R12, there is a notification to the manager or employee if a timekeeper has made changes to a timecard or has entered late time.  This notification relates to users who are using the Change and Late Audit functionality for tracking changes to time or late time entries.  There is configuration in Time and Labor to determine which role gets the notification and if the worklist item is actionable or just for their information.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  In Fusion, the determination of who gets the notifications should be handled in the AMX or workflow setup, assuming that roles are supported for routing rules.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Another option for worklist or email notifications are alerts.  One method for online alerts, are the use of  Watchlist items, which are summaries of items which require attention.  The resulting displays for Watchlists are saved searches.  Watchlist items will be explored further in the Time and Labor Dashboard FDD.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  1.\\tRequireApproval Notifications -   Deliver worklist notifications for timecards requiring approval via AMX Approvals Engine to approvers.  Approvers of timecards (who may be managers) would need to be notified of any timecards requiring their approval.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  2.\\tRejected Timecards Notifications -   Deliver worklist notifications for timecards which have been rejected in the approval process via the AMX Approvals Engine to those who need to resolve or correct the rejected timecards, such as workers or timekeepers.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  3.\\tTime change Notifications \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Provide an option to trigger email notifications when a timecard is modified.  This notification should only be triggered on a submit of  a timecard, not on Save.  Options would include notification to worker, to timekeeper or manager.  The notification would need to communicate to the recipient if the timecard was modified, including  the fields of  \\xE2\\x80\\x9CLast Modified By\\xE2\\x80\\x9D and \\xE2\\x80\\x9CDate of Action\\xE2\\x80\\x9D.  Development would need to seed a worklist notification to display for a modified timecard.  Would be beneficial if it can be defined what changes had occurred in the timecard.  If this is not possible, there should be a link to the timecard to view the modified timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  4.\\tTimecard for Resolution Notification \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Provide a worklist notification to the timekeeper or administrator of timecards which need error resolution which a worker cannot resolve.  This is normally due to setup object changes which are needed such as rules.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:38:31'),(6480,'FunctionalWorkUnit',148,'destroy','3','--- \nname: General Workarea Functionality\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 16:21:30 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 16:21:30 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 167\nid: 148\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:38:39'),(6481,'BusinessArea',167,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Workarea\ncreated_at: 2011-04-08 00:23:00 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-16 21:01:08 Z\nid: 167\nparent_id: 164\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:38:43'),(6482,'BusinessArea',204,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Report Time\ncreated_at: 2011-05-05 19:40:00 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-16 21:01:05 Z\nid: 204\nparent_id: 164\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:39:20'),(6483,'BusinessArea',201,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Web Entry - General Requirements\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 16:30:50 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-16 21:01:02 Z\nid: 201\nparent_id: 164\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:39:24'),(6484,'BusinessArea',200,'update','3','--- \nname: Web Entry Manager\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 13:01:18 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-16 21:00:57 Z\nid: 200\nparent_id: 164\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:40:16'),(6485,'BusinessArea',190,'update','3','--- \nname: Timecard Flows - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 21:36:14 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 16:40:56 Z\nid: 190\nparent_id: 164\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:41:08'),(6486,'BusinessArea',171,'update','3','--- \nname: Timecard  - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-08 00:25:35 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 16:41:47 Z\nid: 171\nparent_id: 164\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:41:53'),(6487,'BusinessArea',164,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Web Entry - Worker - SO\ncreated_at: 2011-04-07 23:54:10 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-16 21:00:24 Z\nid: 164\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 16:42:00'),(6488,'Feature',1333,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Inline Error Messages - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 21:26:09 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1333\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: |\n  Must Have Justification :  Support Fusion error messaging UX guidelines\r\n  \r\n  Allow for easy inline error messages for invalid time, with indications on the reported cells.  The inline error messaging should allow for the highlighting of any field in the timecard matrix, including a particular entry of hours or Start/Stop times.  \r\n  \r\n  Offer a \"Show Messages\" button as a way to get the \"error message list\" dialog . Also, the user will have the dialog box open when they access the timecard entry page if there are existing errors.   We may not need the Show Messages button, if user clicks on each highlighted field the message display will pop-up again.   Will also have the dialog expanded when selecting the  Next button, if error messages still exist.\r\n  \r\n  If the user clicks on the message link and is taken to the line in error, he should always be able to access the error message listing dialog, to view all messages again.\r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 18:05:16'),(6489,'FunctionalWorkUnit',171,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 18:32:22'),(6490,'Feature',1496,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 18:32:36'),(6491,'Feature',1496,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Inline Messages\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 18:32:36 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 18:32:36 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1496\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 171\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 18:32:56'),(6492,'Feature',1496,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1.0\"\nname: Inline Messages\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 18:32:36 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 18:32:56 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1496\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 171\ndescription: \"\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 18:37:27'),(6493,'Feature',1497,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 18:38:37'),(6494,'Feature',1497,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Display Error Listing Dialog\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 18:38:37 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 18:38:37 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1497\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 171\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 18:38:54'),(6495,'Feature',1378,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Email notifications - Deleted Timecard - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 19:27:58 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1378\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification: Customer Requested Enhancements during Customer Feedback Sessions\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  These are additional email notifications which would be triggered in relation to timecards:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  a.\\tDeleted Timecards \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Allow an email notification to be triggered to the manager via workflow if a timecard has been deleted by the worker.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:24:21'),(6496,'Feature',1498,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 19:32:20'),(6497,'Feature',1467,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Display Message Dialog - Message Summary\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 23:28:18 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:36:16 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1467\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: |\n  Message Summary: Including columns for Line Number, Description, Message Type and Source of Error, the format of the error message listing will look like the format for the General Ledger error message listing below:\r\n  \r\n   \r\n  \r\n  The contents of the Error Message listing should include the following:\r\n  o	line number of the error message, displayed in the timecard matrix\r\n  o	message type (error, warning, informational, other)\r\n  o	source of the error message (application),\r\n  o	date of the error if applicable.  \r\n  o	recommended action for the error condition, if applicable\r\n  o	counter of number of error/warning/information messages\r\n  o	ability to navigate to each message from the dialog box\r\n  o	As the user views each message per line, he should be able to select that message and be transferred to the relevant line in the timecard matrix.  This pertains to line level messages only.  If global level messages are displayed, no line navigation would be available.  The navigation to the applicable line in the timecard matrix could occur by either highlighting that row in the error message display or have the message hyperlinked.  If the message is hyperlinked, once the user clicks on the link, the cursor should move to that line in the timecard matrix.\r\n  \r\n  Note:  Message listing need to include all errors (error, warning, informational) which are triggered from within the timecard matrix or from any of the pop-up pages for Daily Details or Additional Attributes.\r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:36:25'),(6498,'Feature',1469,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Timecard Due Date - Email Notification to Worker\ncreated_at: 2011-05-05 19:24:57 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:41:15 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1469\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification: Customer Requested Enhancements during Customer Feedback Sessions\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  These are additional email notifications which would be triggered in relation to timecards:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  b.\\tTimecard Submission Due Date Reminder \\xE2\\x80\\x93 to remind the worker that a timecard is coming due for submission.  This notification is dependent on the existence of a timecard submission due date and time defined for the worker.  Configuration would be required for the user to determine when the reminders need to go out before the due date, such as the day before due date,  or 2 hours before due date/time.  The user may want to setup multiple times for the notification to be transmitted.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:41:28'),(6499,'Feature',1470,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Worker Attestation - Email Notification\ncreated_at: 2011-05-05 19:25:41 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:43:04 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1470\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification: Customer Requested Enhancements during Customer Feedback Sessions\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  These are additional email notifications which would be triggered in relation to timecards:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  c.\\tAttestation Notification \\xE2\\x80\\x93 If time or changes to time have been submitted on behalf of a worker, some companies require the worker to attest to the fact that the time he sees in the timecard was what he had worked.  The attestation process allows the worker to agree or disagree with the time in his timecard.  There would be a notification to the worker to agree or disagree with the time entered on his behalf.  The response from the worker would then need to be routed to a payroll manager or person responsible for monitoring the attestations.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:43:12'),(6500,'Feature',1470,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Worker Attestation - Email Notification\ncreated_at: 2011-05-05 19:25:41 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:43:12 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1470\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 171\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification: Customer Requested Enhancements during Customer Feedback Sessions\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  These are additional email notifications which would be triggered in relation to timecards:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  c.\\tAttestation Notification \\xE2\\x80\\x93 If time or changes to time have been submitted on behalf of a worker, some companies require the worker to attest to the fact that the time he sees in the timecard was what he had worked.  The attestation process allows the worker to agree or disagree with the time in his timecard.  There would be a notification to the worker to agree or disagree with the time entered on his behalf.  The response from the worker would then need to be routed to a payroll manager or person responsible for monitoring the attestations.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:43:33'),(6501,'Feature',1460,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: TIR - Messags Triggered by Rules\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:29:45 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:45:05 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1460\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"c.\\tTime Interaction Rules \\xE2\\x80\\x93 these types of rules would allow the user to define any conditions to trigger the output of messages to the timecard user and could be assigned to any groups of workers via Worker Web Time Entry Time and Labor Setup Profile.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:45:12'),(6502,'Feature',1460,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: TIR - Messags Triggered by Rules\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:29:45 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:45:12 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1460\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"Time Interaction Rules \\xE2\\x80\\x93 these types of rules would allow the user to define any conditions to trigger the output of messages to the timecard user and could be assigned to any groups of workers via Worker Web Time Entry Time and Labor Setup Profile.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:45:20'),(6503,'Feature',1460,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: TIR - Messags Triggered by Rules\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:29:45 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:45:20 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1460\nfeature_type: Business Rule\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"Time Interaction Rules \\xE2\\x80\\x93 these types of rules would allow the user to define any conditions to trigger the output of messages to the timecard user and could be assigned to any groups of workers via Worker Web Time Entry Time and Labor Setup Profile.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:45:29'),(6504,'Feature',1459,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Messaging Section - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:29:02 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:26:44 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1459\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"b.\\tMessage Section \\xE2\\x80\\x93 a section of the timecard needs to be offered to display messages to the timecard user, below the employment header section.  No more than 3 messages can be displayed in the message display area.  Global messages pertaining to the entire timecard should be displayed in this area, if there is no time entry context.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:45:46'),(6505,'Feature',1459,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Timecard - Display Messaging Section\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:29:02 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:55:08 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1459\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"Message Section \\xE2\\x80\\x93 a section of the timecard needs to be offered to display messages to the timecard user, below the employment header section.  No more than 3 messages can be displayed in the message display area.  Global messages pertaining to the entire timecard should be displayed in this area, if there is no time entry context.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:55:17'),(6506,'Feature',1458,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: TIR - Configure Messags to User\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:27:54 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:56:10 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1458\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"Messaging to User \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Allow for ability to configure and display messages to the timecard user.   This may be done via \\tthe output of Time Interaction Rules.  \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:56:15'),(6507,'Feature',1457,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: TIR - Enable \'Tip of the Day\' Messages\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:27:01 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:57:43 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1457\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"Tip of the Day \\xE2\\x80\\x93 a message type that is offered by some users, which can have different messages displayed to the timecard user on dynamic basis.  \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:57:47'),(6508,'Feature',1383,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Approval Comments  - Summarize by Attribute\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:58:38 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1383\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification:  Customer Requested Enhancement to simplify the approval information displayed to the user\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Allow for the administrator to summarize approval comments by time attributes of the timecard.  There may be many rows of entries which are rejected and it would be easier to categorize the rejection comments for the error message summary.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:59:35'),(6509,'Feature',1384,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Timecard Approval Comments  - Summarize by Assignment \"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:59:21 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1384\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification: Customer Requested Enhancement to simplify the approval information displayed to the user\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to see approval comments by worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s different assignments related to the timecard.  This could be done if the approval rules are able to differentiate by assignments and the approval rule output could then be split accordingly. The comments need to be summarized by assignment.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 19:59:38'),(6510,'BusinessArea',215,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 20:10:11'),(6511,'Feature',1499,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 20:14:01'),(6512,'Feature',1499,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: \"Default Template - Worker Defined \"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 20:14:01 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 20:14:01 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1499\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 30\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 20:14:16'),(6513,'Feature',1309,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Template Functionality\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 20:13:20 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1309\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 30\ndescription: \"Provide ability to auto populate timecard with dynamic, private or public timecard templates which are assigned to the worker.  The dynamic templates in scope for Fusion v2 (Work Schedule,  Last Timecard and Project Resource Management template).  The assignment of templates\\r\\n\\\n  will occur in the Worker Web Time Entry Setup Profile (formerly Preferences).\\r\\n\\\n  The worker will be able to change their default template on their Timecard Options in the Timecards Workarea landing page.\\r\\n      \\r\\n\\\n  In addition to the ability to choose from private, public or dynamic timecard templates, a user can also select a timecard template as a default template:\\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tSet As Default:  User can select one of his assigned timecard templates as his default template.  This action allows the user to have that template automatically prepopulate the timecard for every future timecard created, unless the default is changed or no longer selected.  The selection of the default template will be an action on the worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s Timecards Workarea landing page, in a Timecard Options portlet.  See Analytics FDD for Workarea functionality.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Rules for Populating Default Template in Timecard\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tWe will not populate a default template which does not match the current layout set of employee (timecard attributes) - we will trigger a message to user that the default template could not be populated because the timecard fields do not match their current layout.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tWe will not populate a default  template whose template category (daily, weekly, biweekly) does not match the user\\xE2\\x80\\x99s timecard period type-- we will trigger a message to user that the default template could not be populated because the period type of the template and their timecard do not match.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTemplates with template category of (No Days/or No Hours) will always be populated \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tIf Start Day of Template is different than Start Day of Timecard Period, we will still populate the timecard, matching the days accordingly \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tThese rules are the same for private, public and dynamic templates \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 20:15:09'),(6514,'Feature',1499,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1.0\"\nname: \"Default Template - Worker Defined \"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 20:14:01 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 20:14:16 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1499\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 30\ndescription: \"\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 20:15:31'),(6515,'Feature',1462,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Default Timecard Templates - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:50:09 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-08 02:33:39 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1462\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 30\ndescription: \"Provide ability to auto populate timecard with dynamic, private or public timecard templates which are assigned to the worker.  The dynamic templates in scope for Fusion v2 (Work Schedule,  Last Timecard  and Project Resource Management template).  The assignment of templates  will occur in the Worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s Web Time Entry Setup Profile (formerly Preferences).\\r\\n\\\n  The worker will be able to change their default template on their Timecard Options in the Timecards Workarea landing page.  (New for Fusion)\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 20:17:12'),(6516,'Feature',1500,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 20:19:46'),(6517,'Feature',1499,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1.0\"\nname: Timecard Template - Worker Defined Default\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 20:14:01 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 20:16:05 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1499\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 30\ndescription: \"The worker will be able to change their default template on their Timecard Options in the Timecards Workarea landing page.\\r\\n      \\r\\n\\\n  In addition to the ability to choose from private, public or dynamic timecard templates, a user can also select a timecard template as a default template:\\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tSet As Default:  User can select one of his assigned timecard templates as his default template.  This action allows the user to have that template automatically prepopulate the timecard for every future timecard created, unless the default is changed or no longer selected.  The selection of the default template will be an action on the worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s Timecards Workarea landing page, in a Timecard Options portlet.  See Analytics FDD for Workarea functionality.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Rules for Populating Default Template in Timecard\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tWe will not populate a default template which does not match the current layout set of employee (timecard attributes) - we will trigger a message to user that the default template could not be populated because the timecard fields do not match their current layout.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tWe will not populate a default  template whose template category (daily, weekly, biweekly) does not match the user\\xE2\\x80\\x99s timecard period type-- we will trigger a message to user that the default template could not be populated because the period type of the template and their timecard do not match.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTemplates with template category of (No Days/or No Hours) will always be populated \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tIf Start Day of Template is different than Start Day of Timecard Period, we will still populate the timecard, matching the days accordingly \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tThese rules are the same for private, public and dynamic templates \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 20:20:06'),(6518,'Feature',1500,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Timecard Template - Rules Applying Default Template\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 20:19:46 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 20:19:46 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1500\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 30\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 20:20:15'),(6519,'Feature',1500,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1.0\"\nname: Timecard Template - Rules Applying Default Template\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 20:19:46 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 20:20:15 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1500\nfeature_type: Business Rule\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 30\ndescription: \"\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 20:20:21'),(6520,'Feature',1398,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Private Template Page - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-08 02:32:58 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1398\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 30\ndescription: \"<pre>This page facilitates Time and Labor workers pre-populating new\\n or existing timecards with sets of commonly used timecard entries. \\n\\n\\\n  The template contains the timecard matrix information, derived from\\n the worker\'s currently assigned layout set and timecard period associated\\n to their Worker Web Time Entry Setup Profile.   The worker is also\\n able to name the template and populate the timecard matrix for reuse\\n in other timecards.\\n\\n\\\n  There are four delivered repeating period types: daily, weekly, semi-monthly\\n and monthly which can be used as timecard periods.  We will support\\n daily, weekly and biweekly timecard periods for a worker to enter\\n both hours (times) and time attribute values.  If the worker is creating\\n a private template for a semi-monthly or monthly timecard period,\\n the template will just show attributes as editable with no display\\n of days , with a business message displayed  upon creation that \\\"Only\\n attribute values can be defined for this timecard period type.\\\"\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  A. Create Template page\\n\\n\\\n  The following are the fields to be displayed when creating a new private\\n template:\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Section: Template Detail\\n\\n\\\n  o     Template Name: user defined name for the private template\\n\\n\\\n  o     Status:  Active/Inactive  \\n\\n\\\n  A worker can inactivate a private template if it is no longer usable\\n for their current layout or timecard period.  The default value is\\n active.\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Section: Template Entry\\n\\n\\\n  o     Timecard matrix for entering hours/ Start/Stop Times and additional\\n time attribution such as  Hours Type, Work Location, Cost Center.\\n\\n\\\n  o     Days of the week will be displayed without dates for those timecard\\n periods which can have pre-populated hours (daily, weekly, biweekly).\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Page Actions:   Save  - user saves the page and remains on page\\n\\n\\\n  Save and Close - user saves the page and page closes\\n\\n\\\n  Cancel - user cancels out of the page\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  B. Edit Template page\\n\\n\\\n  All template entry fields are editable on the private template as\\n well as the page name.\\n\\n \\n\\n\\\n  Page Actions:   Save \\n\\n\\\n  Save and Close\\n\\n\\\n  Cancel</pre>\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 20:21:06'),(6521,'FunctionalWorkUnit',172,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 20:21:25'),(6522,'Feature',1501,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 20:21:41'),(6523,'Feature',1502,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 20:22:07'),(6524,'Feature',1501,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Page Display\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 20:21:41 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 20:21:41 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1501\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 172\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 20:22:21'),(6525,'Feature',1398,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Private Template Page - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 20:21:06 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1398\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_