'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Header Displays Message - Based on Primary Asg\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 22:42:40 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 22:42:51 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1509\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 173\ndescription: \"\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:43:28'),(6573,'Feature',1510,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 22:46:25'),(6574,'Feature',1510,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Primary Asg used for Setup Profile Evaluation\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 22:46:25 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 22:46:25 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1510\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 167\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:46:41'),(6575,'BusinessArea',216,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 22:49:57'),(6576,'FunctionalWorkUnit',34,'update','3','--- \nname: Timecard Display Accrual Information\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 18:02:56 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 21:30:10 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 206\nid: 34\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:50:07'),(6577,'FunctionalWorkUnit',173,'update','3','--- \nname: Header\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 22:38:04 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 22:38:04 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 206\nid: 173\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:50:13'),(6578,'FunctionalWorkUnit',174,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 22:52:27'),(6579,'Feature',1305,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Display Timecard Status on Timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 22:48:27 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1305\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 31\ndescription: \"A derived status to display to user on the Timecard Entry data section, below the timecard period display, to show what status their timecard is in.   This is a read-only status which is not editable.  The status would not change if the user is in the timecard until they take an action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9Csaving\\xE2\\x80\\x9D or \\xE2\\x80\\x9CSubmitting\\xE2\\x80\\x9D the timecard.  This would be displayed in the same section as Timecard Comments and View Accrual Balances link.  The status is currently displayed in the Recent Timecards results table in EBS OTL R12, but not in the actual timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Saved and Submitted are the timestore statuses, but there are additional derived statuses which can be used for providing additional data to the user:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\tNew -  Upon entering into a newly created timecard, the status would be displayed\\r\\n\\\n  \\tDraft \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Upon save of the timecard, the status would be displayed.\\r\\n\\\n  \\tSubmitted- Upon submitting of the timecard, the status would be submitted\\r\\n\\\n  \\tPending Resolution \\xE2\\x80\\x93 new status to denote administrator intervention is needed to resolve errors before timecard can be routed for approval\\r\\n\\\n  \\tApproved \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Upon approval of all time entries in the timecard, the status would be approved\\r\\n\\\n  \\tRejected \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Upon rejection of 1 time entry, the status would be rejected\\r\\n\\\n  \\tIn Error \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Upon 1 hard error in timecard, the status would be in error.  This would occur if there is an offline batch processing of time rules in Group Time Entry or import processing.  Otherwise, for all application validations and time rules, the timecard errors need to be resolved before saving or submitting the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\t \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue 1:  To be determined in Time Entry LBA, if will implement the \\xE2\\x80\\x9CTransfer To\\xE2\\x80\\x9D column information which was implemented in EBS OTL R12.1.2. which states if the timecard has been transferred to \\xE2\\x80\\x9CProjects, Payroll, None\\xE2\\x80\\x9D.  This would separate the Transfer information out of the Timecard Status field into its own Transfer To field.   We will also look at a separate Time Consumer Status which can reflect the state of transfer for a timecard to a time consumer .\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue 2:  To be determined if we will add another timecard status of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CPending Resolution\\xE2\\x80\\x9D which denote timecards which have errors needing resolution by an administrator or timekeeper before they can be routed for approval.  This is incorporated into the Validations of Processed Time design section.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:52:44'),(6580,'Feature',1305,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Display Timecard Status on Timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 22:52:44 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1305\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 174\ndescription: \"A derived status to display to user on the Timecard Entry data section, below the timecard period display, to show what status their timecard is in.   This is a read-only status which is not editable.  The status would not change if the user is in the timecard until they take an action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9Csaving\\xE2\\x80\\x9D or \\xE2\\x80\\x9CSubmitting\\xE2\\x80\\x9D the timecard.  This would be displayed in the same section as Timecard Comments and View Accrual Balances link.  The status is currently displayed in the Recent Timecards results table in EBS OTL R12, but not in the actual timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Saved and Submitted are the timestore statuses, but there are additional derived statuses which can be used for providing additional data to the user:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\tNew -  Upon entering into a newly created timecard, the status would be displayed\\r\\n\\\n  \\tDraft \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Upon save of the timecard, the status would be displayed.\\r\\n\\\n  \\tSubmitted- Upon submitting of the timecard, the status would be submitted\\r\\n\\\n  \\tPending Resolution \\xE2\\x80\\x93 new status to denote administrator intervention is needed to resolve errors before timecard can be routed for approval\\r\\n\\\n  \\tApproved \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Upon approval of all time entries in the timecard, the status would be approved\\r\\n\\\n  \\tRejected \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Upon rejection of 1 time entry, the status would be rejected\\r\\n\\\n  \\tIn Error \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Upon 1 hard error in timecard, the status would be in error.  This would occur if there is an offline batch processing of time rules in Group Time Entry or import processing.  Otherwise, for all application validations and time rules, the timecard errors need to be resolved before saving or submitting the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\t \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue 1:  To be determined in Time Entry LBA, if will implement the \\xE2\\x80\\x9CTransfer To\\xE2\\x80\\x9D column information which was implemented in EBS OTL R12.1.2. which states if the timecard has been transferred to \\xE2\\x80\\x9CProjects, Payroll, None\\xE2\\x80\\x9D.  This would separate the Transfer information out of the Timecard Status field into its own Transfer To field.   We will also look at a separate Time Consumer Status which can reflect the state of transfer for a timecard to a time consumer .\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Open Design Issue 2:  To be determined if we will add another timecard status of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CPending Resolution\\xE2\\x80\\x9D which denote timecards which have errors needing resolution by an administrator or timekeeper before they can be routed for approval.  This is incorporated into the Validations of Processed Time design section.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:53:00'),(6581,'Feature',1511,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 22:54:42'),(6582,'Feature',1511,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Display Timecard Due Date on Timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 22:54:42 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 22:54:42 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1511\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 174\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:54:51'),(6583,'Feature',1314,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Submission Due Date - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-04 20:20:55 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1314\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 31\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification:  Increase efficiency in timecard submission; added BI intelligence on late timecards\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Allow for the association of a timecard submission due date and time  to a timecard, so users can be made aware of when they need to submit their timecards.  These due dates can be attached to the repeating period definitions which are associated to the worker in their Setup Options Profile.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  This Due Date can be used to display in the timecard header.  It can also be used for reminder notifications to workers or timekeepers, and can be used for analytics to determine who are repeatedly late in submitting timecards.  Some users just use timecard due dates, some also associate a time to that date, to ensure that the payroll processing department can plan on when to begin their payroll processes.  If a time is defined along with the date, a time zone may need to be supplied, unless the time is assumed to be the local time or the time zone is derived from the user\\xE2\\x80\\x99s regional Preferences.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Please Refer to Timecard Submission Due Date Document for further design details\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:55:14'),(6584,'Feature',1511,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Display Timecard Due Date on Timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 22:54:42 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 22:54:51 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1511\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 174\ndescription: \"\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:55:41'),(6585,'Feature',1314,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Submission Due Date - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 22:55:14 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1314\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 31\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification:  Increase efficiency in timecard submission; added BI intelligence on late timecards\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Allow for the association of a timecard submission due date and time  to a timecard, so users can be made aware of when they need to submit their timecards.  These due dates can be attached to the repeating period definitions which are associated to the worker in their Setup Options Profile.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:56:12'),(6586,'Feature',1314,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Submission Due Date - Feature / Use\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 22:56:56 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1314\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 167\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification:  Increase efficiency in timecard submission; added BI intelligence on late timecards\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Allow for the association of a timecard submission due date and time  to a timecard, so users can be made aware of when they need to submit their timecards.  These due dates can be attached to the repeating period definitions which are associated to the worker in their Setup Options Profile.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 22:57:19'),(6587,'Feature',1315,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Display Primary Asg changes during the Timecard Period\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 23:00:06 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1315\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 31\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification: Customer Requested Enhancement during Customer Feedback Sessions \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to see different person information for mid timecard period changes.   This would cover changes that can occur as a result of workers changing paygroups, departments jobs or positions which can occur during a time period .  The user wants to see the old and new data for this change.  \\r\\n\\\n  As we are only displaying employment header data from Primary Assignment in Fusion v2, this would only be applicable for changes to the primary assignment during the timecard period. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Since we are displaying the employment header data as of a specific date, we can do two things:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  1.\\tDisplay the \\xE2\\x80\\x9CAs of Date\\xE2\\x80\\x9D for the Employment Header display, so the user knows from when we are deriving the displayed data\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  2.\\tOffer a \\xE2\\x80\\x9CEmployment Changes\\xE2\\x80\\x9D link to see the changed data for the primary assignment within the timecard period in a pop-up page with a table of field changes within the timecard period.  This would be similar to seeing a \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cchange history\\xE2\\x80\\x9D in an effective date history table.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 23:00:11'),(6588,'Feature',1315,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Display Primary Asg changes during the Timecard Period\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 23:00:11 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1315\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 174\ndescription: \"Should Have Justification: Customer Requested Enhancement during Customer Feedback Sessions \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to see different person information for mid timecard period changes.   This would cover changes that can occur as a result of workers changing paygroups, departments jobs or positions which can occur during a time period .  The user wants to see the old and new data for this change.  \\r\\n\\\n  As we are only displaying employment header data from Primary Assignment in Fusion v2, this would only be applicable for changes to the primary assignment during the timecard period. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Since we are displaying the employment header data as of a specific date, we can do two things:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  1.\\tDisplay the \\xE2\\x80\\x9CAs of Date\\xE2\\x80\\x9D for the Employment Header display, so the user knows from when we are deriving the displayed data\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  2.\\tOffer a \\xE2\\x80\\x9CEmployment Changes\\xE2\\x80\\x9D link to see the changed data for the primary assignment within the timecard period in a pop-up page with a table of field changes within the timecard period.  This would be similar to seeing a \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cchange history\\xE2\\x80\\x9D in an effective date history table.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 23:00:18'),(6589,'Feature',1465,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Employment Header - Contextual Data - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 20:57:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 21:24:54 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1465\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 31\ndescription: \"Contextual Data - Time and Labor Data fields: display additional fields\\r\\n which are relevant to the timecard for the worker, below the existing\\r\\n employment header fields.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  1.     Timecard period name\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  2.     Layout Set\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Reference:  HCM Person Header TUD - http://files.oraclecorp.com/content/AllPu\\r\\n\\\n  blic/SharedFolders/Fusion%20Deliverables-Public/HCM/Core%20HR/TUD/HCM_PER_Pe\\r\\n\\\n  rsonHeader_TUD.doc<pre>\\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 23:01:05'),(6590,'Feature',1465,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Display T&L Contextual Data in Employment Header Region\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 20:57:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 23:01:37 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1465\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 31\ndescription: \"Contextual Data - Time and Labor Data fields: display additional fields which are relevant to the timecard for the worker, below the existing employment header fields.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  1.     Timecard period name\\r\\n\\\n  2.     Layout Set\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Reference:  HCM Person Header TUD - http://files.oraclecorp.com/content/AllPu\\r\\n\\\n  blic/SharedFolders/Fusion%20Deliverables-Public/HCM/Core%20HR/TUD/HCM_PER_Pe\\r\\n\\\n  rsonHeader_TUD.doc<pre>\\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 23:01:50'),(6591,'Feature',1465,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Display T&L Contextual Data in Employment Header Region\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 20:57:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 23:01:50 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1465\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 31\ndescription: \"Contextual Data - Time and Labor Data fields: display additional fields which are relevant to the timecard for the worker, below the existing employment header fields.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  1.     Timecard period name\\r\\n\\\n  2.     Layout Set\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Reference:  HCM Person Header TUD - http://files.oraclecorp.com/content/AllPu\\r\\n\\\n  blic/SharedFolders/Fusion%20Deliverables-Public/HCM/Core%20HR/TUD/HCM_PER_Pe\\r\\n\\\n  rsonHeader_TUD.doc<pre>\\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 23:01:55'),(6592,'Feature',1468,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Display Message if TC Period is not current period\ncreated_at: 2011-05-04 20:18:38 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 23:03:46 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1468\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 31\ndescription: |\n  Should Have Justification:  Customer Feedback Requirement and Enterprise TL Feature\r\n  \r\n  Provide indication or message to timecard user they are in a prior or future time period.  This needs to be offered in the central messaging section in the Timecard header.  This is a reminder to the user in case they are updating the wrong timecard period.\r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 23:03:52'),(6593,'Feature',1468,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Display Message if TC Period is not current period\ncreated_at: 2011-05-04 20:18:38 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 23:03:52 Z\npriority: Should Have\nid: 1468\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 31\ndescription: |\n  Should Have Justification:  Customer Feedback Requirement and Enterprise TL Feature\r\n  \r\n  Provide indication or message to timecard user they are in a prior or future time period.  This needs to be offered in the central messaging section in the Timecard header.  This is a reminder to the user in case they are updating the wrong timecard period.\r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 23:04:03'),(6594,'FunctionalWorkUnit',175,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 23:08:34'),(6595,'Feature',1512,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-26 23:08:44'),(6596,'Feature',1346,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Project Portfolio Management Progress Fields for Time Entry\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 23:08:09 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1346\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 28\ndescription: \"Nice to Have Justification:  PPM Request for enhanced integration\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  In addition to the use of the Project Portfolio Management Descriptive Flexfield for time entry, there are additional fields which Project Portfolio Management would like to be available for timecard entry, such as the following Progress fields which are related to a combination of reported Project and Task.  The uptake of these fields are listed in priority order below:\\r\\n\\\n  High Priority:     \\r\\n\\\n  Estimated Time to Complete (remaining work) \\r\\n\\\n  Progress notes (per Task) \\xE2\\x80\\x93 use the Common Notes component delivered by CRM to record Progress Notes per Task\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Medium Priority:            \\t\\r\\n\\\n  Estimated finish date\\r\\n\\\n  Physical Percent % complete\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Low Priority\\r\\n\\\n  Progress status\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  These fields may be more relevant for manager entry than worker or timekeeper entry, so may need to be marked as \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cmanager\\xE2\\x80\\x9D only timecard layout components.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 23:08:53'),(6597,'FunctionalWorkUnit',28,'update','3','--- \nname: Timecard Summary\ncreated_at: 2011-04-08 00:26:27 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-08 00:26:27 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 171\nid: 28\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 23:09:31'),(6598,'Feature',1377,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Time Summary - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-04 20:17:30 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1377\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 28\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification:    Support  Tier 1 Timecard UI Display shown to customers \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Display a configurable Time Summary section as a collapsible section below the timecard matrix.   There would be two views for this summary, table and pie chart view., with the user being able to toggle between the two. This section would allow the user to see summaries of time specific to the attributes that are important to them, such as per project or task. \\r\\n \\r\\n\\\n  \\tOverall Requirements\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTable and alternate pie chart views \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tAbility to summarize hours by one or more time attributes \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tAbility to configure the summarization labels for the choice list options\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tAbility to use abstract or physical attributes to summarize time: \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tAbstract = Example would be \\\"Worked\\\" and \\\"Non-Worked Time\\\" - in which different hours types would add to each type of time \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tPhysical Attributes = Example would be actual attributes which appear on the timecard such as Project, Task, Hours Type\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tAbility to show a \\\"View By\\xE2\\x80\\x9D field which offers a choice list  for the user to select different options to summarize the time entries by, defined in the Time Entry Page Composer.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tAbility for total hours not to equal timecard total hours (as the way time is summarized, it may not equal all worked time) \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tDisplay message if Time Summary Hours do not equal Timecard Totals \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tDefine a \\\"default\\\" summarization for the Choice List Options \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tPie Chart Slices Hover Over - can define the \\\"number of hours\\\" that make up that pie slice, if pie slices are broken down by percentage\\r\\n\\\n  The time summarizations could be comprised of just one time attribute, or a combination of time attributes.  The attributes which are selected for the time category need to be \\xE2\\x80\\x9Csummarizable\\xE2\\x80\\x9D and will be defined as such in the layout set definition.  For example, a comments field would not be included in a time summary section.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  This would also save the user from having to navigate to the timecard review page to see Time Summary.  There should be a Refresh Icon on Timecard Summary toolbar, to update totals by Time Summarization, as the totals cannot dynamically be updated as time is entered, as the time category totals need to be derived from their definitions.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  The default format for the summary would be in a pie chart format, with a hover over of number of hours for each pie section in lieu of percentages.\\r\\n \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n  An alternate view for the summary would be in a table, to show how the time is broken down by the main attribute, such as by Project:\\r\\n                    \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Examples of time summarization:\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tRegular Time and Premium Time\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tProject, Task, Expenditure Type\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tBillable and Non-Billable Hours\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tTotal Hours/ Work Hours/ Absence Hours\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tWorked Time/ Non-Worked Time\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tCustomer\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tWork Order\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-26 23:10:07'),(6599,'Feature',1377,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Time Summary - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 23:10:07 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1377\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 28\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification:    Support  Tier 1 Timecard UI Displa