3 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 21:02:00 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1320\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Application  of online timecard configuration in timecard layout sets, supporting existing EBS OTL R12 functionality\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to display appropriate fields in timecard matrix based on delivered layout.  The use of delivered layouts will depend on the configurability offered in the Layout Editor FDD for Timecard.  ( See Appendix A for existing delivered layouts from R12.)  The ability to configure the display of each section of the timecard online is new for Fusion.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 05:08:08'),(6685,'Feature',1369,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Retain entry order of time entries - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 22:56:43 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1369\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Strong customer feedback, noted in \\tHCM_Time&Labor_Usability_Feedback_Report_FINAL.doc (3/26/2010)\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to save all time entries in the same order as they were entered.  This is critical for the individual timecard and for group time entry.  If the user wants to see the data in a different order, he should be able to highlight the column to sort by that column and have all data in the table resort according to that column (ascending or descending order).\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 05:20:42'),(6686,'Feature',1369,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Retain entry order of time entries\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 05:20:53 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1369\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Provide ability to save all time entries in the same order as they were entered.  This is critical for the individual timecard and for group time entry.  If the user wants to see the data in a different order, he should be able to highlight the column to sort by that column and have all data in the table resort according to that column (ascending or descending order).\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 05:21:03'),(6687,'Feature',1346,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Project Portfolio Management Progress Fields for Time Entry\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 23:08:53 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1346\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 175\ndescription: \"Nice to Have Justification:  PPM Request for enhanced integration\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  In addition to the use of the Project Portfolio Management Descriptive Flexfield for time entry, there are additional fields which Project Portfolio Management would like to be available for timecard entry, such as the following Progress fields which are related to a combination of reported Project and Task.  The uptake of these fields are listed in priority order below:\\r\\n\\\n  High Priority:     \\r\\n\\\n  Estimated Time to Complete (remaining work) \\r\\n\\\n  Progress notes (per Task) \\xE2\\x80\\x93 use the Common Notes component delivered by CRM to record Progress Notes per Task\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Medium Priority:            \\t\\r\\n\\\n  Estimated finish date\\r\\n\\\n  Physical Percent % complete\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Low Priority\\r\\n\\\n  Progress status\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  These fields may be more relevant for manager entry than worker or timekeeper entry, so may need to be marked as \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cmanager\\xE2\\x80\\x9D only timecard layout components.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 05:21:32'),(6688,'Feature',1514,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 05:24:09'),(6689,'Feature',1370,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Admin Define Freeze Column in Composerator \"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 05:23:39 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1370\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: |\n  Must Have Justification :  Customer Requested Requirement during Customer Feedback Sessions \r\n  \r\n  Provide ability to configure the freezing of the timecard matrix at a certain column by the administrator in the Time Entry Page Composer.  If set by the administrator in the Time Entry Page Composer, each employee does not need to individually set the correct column to be frozen.  The freezing of the columns should persist for each user session.  \r\n  \r\n  This is in addition to the standard Freeze action in the View menu for tables, as a standard feature in ADF tables.   Also, want to ensure that the top row (column headers)  of the timecard matrix will always be frozen for vertical display of timecard.  The freezing of the columns would behave as noted in Requirement #20, the user will highlight the column he wants to freeze on, and selects the Freeze action from the toolbar or menu action.  All columns to the right of that frozen column can be scrolled across horizontally, while the columns to the left  of the frozen column will remain static. \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 05:24:25'),(6690,'Feature',1514,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Freeze Action in Table\ncreated_at: 2011-05-30 05:24:09 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 05:24:09 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1514\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 05:25:05'),(6691,'Feature',1514,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Freeze Action in Table\ncreated_at: 2011-05-30 05:24:09 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 05:25:05 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1514\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: |\n  Standard Freeze action in the View menu for tables, as a standard feature in ADF tables.   Also, want to ensure that the top row (column headers)  of the timecard matrix will always be frozen for vertical display of timecard.  The freezing of the columns would behave as noted in Requirement #20, the user will highlight the column he wants to freeze on, and selects the Freeze action from the toolbar or menu action.  All columns to the right of that frozen column can be scrolled across horizontally, while the columns to the left  of the frozen column will remain static. \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 05:25:21'),(6692,'Feature',1370,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Admin Define Freeze Column in Composerator \"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 05:24:25 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1370\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Provide ability to configure the freezing of the timecard matrix at a certain column by the administrator in the Time Entry Page Composer.  If set by the administrator in the Time Entry Page Composer, each employee does not need to individually set the correct column to be frozen.  The freezing of the columns should persist for each user session.  \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 05:25:24'),(6693,'Feature',1357,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Filtering Data\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 05:59:28 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1357\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Nice to Have Justification: Support Fusion functionality of QBE, helpful for Project Timecard users with many rows against different Project/Task combinations \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Allow for the use of the Query By Example Bar at the top of the timecard matrix, configured in the Time Entry Page Composer, as not all users will find this helpful in their time entry process.  This may be more helpful to Project Portfolio Management users who are searching for specific Project time entries.  There will be an icon on the Timecard Matrix toolbar to hide or show the QBE bar.  The bar will be hidden by default.   When data is filtered in the timecard matrix, there are other interactions that need to be accounted for on the timecard such as :\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tRow and column totals \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Row and column totals would be changed with filtered data, as the user is no longer seeing all time stored on the timecard.   To lessen confusion to the user of having to adjust the totals to \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cfiltered totals\\xE2\\x80\\x9D, it would be better to hide the column, row and Timecard Totals when filters are in use.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tLine Numbers with Error Message Display Dialog (Show Messages) \\xE2\\x80\\x93 If the Error Message Dialog is open when the QBE field is used, the dialog should close.  The line numbers will change based on the rows brought back from the QBE filtering.  The change in line numbers need to be reflected if the user opens the Error Message Dialog while QBE is enabled.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tLine Numbers with Approval Comments Dialog (View Approval Comments) - If the Approval Comments Dialog is open when the QBE field is used, the dialog should close.  The line numbers will change based on the rows brought back from the QBE filtering.  The change in line numbers need to be reflected if the user opens the Approval Comments Dialog while QBE is enabled.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tShow Time Entry Summary \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Since this dialog shows totals for the timecard, this dialog should be disabled if the QBE filters are in effect, as the timecard totals would not be valid.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tAdd Line \\xE2\\x80\\x93 If the user decides to add a line when the data has been filtered and not all rows are showing, the row should be displayed without filters next to the row it was added to.  This will alter the line numbers for the timecard matrix, to allow for the insertion of the row.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tDelete Line \\xE2\\x80\\x93 If the user decides to delete a line when the data has been filtered, the line numbers will be altered to account for the removed line.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tApply Template \\xE2\\x80\\x93 The timecard action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CApply Template\\xE2\\x80\\x9D should be inactivated when data is filtered, as not all rows will be visible for the user to decide whether to \\xE2\\x80\\x9Creplace\\xE2\\x80\\x9D or \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cadd\\xE2\\x80\\x9D to the existing timecard data. A business message should be displayed to the user that this action cannot be processed with filtered data.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tSave as Template -   The timecard action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CSave as Template\\xE2\\x80\\x9D should be inactivated when data is filtered, as not all rows are visible for the saving of timecard data as a template.  A business message should be displayed to the user that this action cannot be processed with filtered data.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tImport Time - The timecard action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CImport Time\\xE2\\x80\\x9D should be inactivated when data is filtered, as not all rows are visible for the additional import of time.  A business message should be displayed to the user that this action cannot be processed with filtered data.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tDuplicate Line- If the user decides to duplicate a line, the line number will follow the line that is duplicated.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tClear Hours \\xE2\\x80\\x93 The user can still use the timecard action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cclear hours\\xE2\\x80\\x9D for any rows that are displayed, during filtering of rows\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 05:59:36'),(6694,'Feature',1357,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Filtering Data\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 05:59:36 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1357\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Allow for the use of the Query By Example Bar at the top of the timecard matrix, configured in the Time Entry Page Composer, as not all users will find this helpful in their time entry process.  This may be more helpful to Project Portfolio Management users who are searching for specific Project time entrie