\\n\\\n  >>\\tDelete Line \\xE2\\x80\\x93 If the user decides to delete a line when the data has been filtered, the line numbers will be altered to account for the removed line.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tApply Template \\xE2\\x80\\x93 The timecard action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CApply Template\\xE2\\x80\\x9D should be inactivated when data is filtered, as not all rows will be visible for the user to decide whether to \\xE2\\x80\\x9Creplace\\xE2\\x80\\x9D or \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cadd\\xE2\\x80\\x9D to the existing timecard data. A business message should be displayed to the user that this action cannot be processed with filtered data.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tSave as Template -   The timecard action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CSave as Template\\xE2\\x80\\x9D should be inactivated when data is filtered, as not all rows are visible for the saving of timecard data as a template.  A business message should be displayed to the user that this action cannot be processed with filtered data.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tImport Time - The timecard action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CImport Time\\xE2\\x80\\x9D should be inactivated when data is filtered, as not all rows are visible for the additional import of time.  A business message should be displayed to the user that this action cannot be processed with filtered data.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tDuplicate Line- If the user decides to duplicate a line, the line number will follow the line that is duplicated.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tClear Hours \\xE2\\x80\\x93 The user can still use the timecard action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cclear hours\\xE2\\x80\\x9D for any rows that are displayed, during filtering of rows\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 05:59:42'),(6695,'Feature',1356,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Clock Times Duration Display - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 19:53:38 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1356\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Nice to Have Justification:  Enhanced summarization of clock time and can be used for \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cexception\\xE2\\x80\\x9D display for managers reviewing clock time\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Display the duration of hours for a set of clock times or Start and Stop Times.  This allows the user to see a running total of hours for each set of times or punches.  This is also important when rounding rules are used to round punches or durations between punches which are being entered online or imported from time clocks.\\r\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tPunch Duration\\r\\n\\\n  \\t8:00  am\\tSTART    \\t10:00  am\\tSTOP\\t\\t2 hours\\r\\n\\\n  \\t10:00  am\\tSTART    \\t1:00   pm\\tSTOP\\t\\t3 hours\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:00:23'),(6696,'Feature',1356,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Display Clock Times Duration\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:00:46 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1356\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Display the duration of hours for a set of clock times or Start and Stop Times.  This allows the user to see a running total of hours for each set of times or punches.  This is also important when rounding rules are used to round punches or durations between punches which are being entered online or imported from time clocks.\\r\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tPunch Duration\\r\\n\\\n  \\t8:00  am\\tSTART    \\t10:00  am\\tSTOP\\t\\t2 hours\\r\\n\\\n  \\t10:00  am\\tSTART    \\t1:00   pm\\tSTOP\\t\\t3 hours\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:00:51'),(6697,'Feature',1355,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Different Shortcut Entry Methods in the Timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:02:45 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1355\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Nice to Have Justification:  Improve efficiency of task intensive timecard reporting\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  For the purpose of users who enter  sets of related time attributes, it would improve the efficiency of time entry to offer shortcuts for the population of related fields.  A set of  related values may be entered often by the user, so it would be helpful to allow the user to string them together with a shortcut or combination code.  For the business, there may be a set of related attribute values which are valid for the worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s entry.  In this scenario, the administrator could setup a list of the related attribute values which are relevant for the user and associate them to a shortcut or combination code. This scenario is often true for customers with Project Portfolio Management, who have multiple Project Attributes which are related to each other.  In either scenario, the combination codes which are created have to be unique to the set of attribute values to which they are associated to.  There also has to be a way of refreshing the list of combination codes, as the related values may no longer be valid, as they may have been closed or inactivated.   Additionally, the related attributes may be display only or may be editable by the user.   Below are a few different design options for allowing for the creation of the combination or shortcut code.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tCombination Code Self-Entry on Template \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Add an optional field on the Public and Private Templates within the timecard matrix, to let the user enter a short code that would label the set of attributes they are entering on that line.  Then that code can be used later by the user in timecard entry.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tCombination Code Self-Entry on Timecard \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Add an optional field for \\xE2\\x80\\x9Ccombination code\\xE2\\x80\\x9D to the left of the time attributes in the timecard matrix, so the user can enter a code for that set of attributes and then use it later.   In future use of the \\xE2\\x80\\x9Ccombination code\\xE2\\x80\\x9D field, all the values that the user entered would be available for his entry.  Once he selected a combination code, the other related time attributes would automatically be populated.  There would need to be some business rules set in place for the saved combination codes, that they were unique, for the set of values being entered.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tDynamic Alternate Name Set \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Enhance the Alternate Name Set so that an administrator can enter a simple code when setting up the Alternate Name values, which can be associated to a set of time attribute values, which can be displayed or not displayed on the timecard matrix.  In the Timecard, the Combination Code can be displayed as the \\xE2\\x80\\x9Ceditable\\xE2\\x80\\x9D field for entry, using the alternate name set as the choice list, and the related fields would be displayed or not, as per the setup of the Alternate Name.\\r\\n\\\n  There may be a long list of related values which require combination codes to be associated to them.  In this case, there might need to be a batch process to auto-generate unique combination codes for a long list of combinations of values.  There will also need to be a validation process to ensure each value in the combinations is still valid for use.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tMost Frequently Used \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Allow for user configuration of time attributes to link together to reference for \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cmost frequently used\\xE2\\x80\\x9D values.  The display of these values can be auto-generated by the system based on previous usage.  This combination of values can be accessed by the user to apply to new rows of data.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\t\\xE2\\x80\\x9CMy Favorites\\xE2\\x80\\x9D Values \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Allow for user configuration of time attributes to link together for reference for favorites.  As the user enters a combination of values, they should be able to mark them as \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cfavorite combinations\\xE2\\x80\\x9D and have them available for future time entry.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:02:48'),(6698,'Feature',1355,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Different Shortcut Entry Methods in the Timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:02:48 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1355\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"For the purpose of users who enter  sets of related time attributes, it would improve the efficiency of time entry to offer shortcuts for the population of related fields.  A set of  related values may be entered often by the user, so it would be helpful to allow the user to string them together with a shortcut or combination code.  For the business, there may be a set of related attribute values which are valid for the worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s entry.  In this scenario, the administrator could setup a list of the related attribute values which are relevant for the user and associate them to a shortcut or combination code. This scenario is often true for customers with Project Portfolio Management, who have multiple Project Attributes which are related to each other.  In either scenario, the combination codes which are created have to be unique to the set of attribute values to which they are associated to.  There also has to be a way of refreshing the list of combination codes, as the related values may no longer be valid, as they may have been closed or inactivated.   Additionally, the related attributes may be display only or may be editable by the user.   Below are a few different design options for allowing for the creation of the combination or shortcut code.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tCombination Code Self-Entry on Template \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Add an optional field on the Public and Private Templates within the timecard matrix, to let the user enter a short code that would label the set of attributes they are entering on that line.  Then that code can be used later by the user in timecard entry.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tCombination Code Self-Entry on Timecard \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Add an optional field for \\xE2\\x80\\x9Ccombination code\\xE2\\x80\\x9D to the left of the time attributes in the timecard matrix, so the user can enter a code for that set of attributes and then use it later.   In future use of the \\xE2\\x80\\x9Ccombination code\\xE2\\x80\\x9D field, all the values that the user entered would be available for his entry.  Once he selected a combination code, the other related time attributes would automatically be populated.  There would need to be some business rules set in place for the saved combination codes, that they were unique, for the set of values being entered.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tDynamic Alternate Name Set \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Enhance the Alternate Name Set so that an administrator can enter a simple code when setting up the Alternate Name values, which can be associated to a set of time attribute values, which can be displayed or not displayed on the timecard matrix.  In the Timecard, the Combination Code can be displayed as the \\xE2\\x80\\x9Ceditable\\xE2\\x80\\x9D field for entry, using the alternate name set as the choice list, and the related fields would be displayed or not, as per the setup of the Alternate Name.\\r\\n\\\n  There may be a long list of related values which require combination codes to be associated to them.  In this case, there might need to be a batch process to auto-generate unique combination codes for a long list of combinations of values.  There will also need to be a validation process to ensure each value in the combinations is still valid for use.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tMost Frequently Used \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Allow for user configuration of time attributes to link together to reference for \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cmost frequently used\\xE2\\x80\\x9D values.  The display of these values can be auto-generated by the system based on previous usage.  This combination of values can be accessed by the user to apply to new rows of data.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\t\\xE2\\x80\\x9CMy Favorites\\xE2\\x80\\x9D Values \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Allow for user configuration of time attributes to link together for reference for favorites.  As the user enters a combination of values, they should be able to mark them as \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cfavorite combinations\\xE2\\x80\\x9D and have them available for future time entry.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:02:57'),(6699,'Feature',1354,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Auto Formating - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 19:49:08 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1354\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Nice to Have Justification:  GSI Requested Enhancement during Customer Feedback Sessions\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Offer ability to enter a limited or shorthand format for time or hours field and let the field auto format.  For example:  allow for entry of 9 in Start Time and let 9:00 get populated in the Start Time field, based on the defined format for that field.   The format of the field still needs to be in sync with the attribute it is stored against. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:03:32'),(6700,'Feature',1354,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Auto Fill / Formating of Time / Hours Entries\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:05:04 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1354\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Offer ability to enter a limited or shorthand format for time or hours field and let the field auto format.  For example:  allow for entry of 9 in Start Time and let 9:00 get populated in the Start Time field, based on the defined format for that field.   The format of the field still needs to be in sync with the attribute it is stored against. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:05:08'),(6701,'Feature',1353,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Disabling Fields - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 19:48:37 Z\npriority: Nic