ture_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Absence Entries:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  If not integrating with Absence Management, should be able to report an absence by using Hours Types of Absence values and enter a number of hours against that absence in the Timecard Matrix.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  If integrating with Fusion Absence Management, the absence display, entry, validation,  approval  and retrieval of absences will be determined further in Time & Labor and Absence Integration FDD.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:30:09'),(6733,'Feature',1336,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Work Location Attribute - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 20:16:53 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1336\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support existing Core Payroll and Localization requirements for work location data\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  For Payroll use, we will offer a Work Location layout component, which will offer a smart choice listing of concatenated values: city, state, county and zip code.  The reason for the concatenated values is for easy entry, so that the user does not need to enter 4 separate fields.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Additionally, we should see if we can add \\\"smart filtering\\\" in which not all work location combinations have to be shown to each employee, if there is a way to filter that list per person.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  These values will be stored separately as City, State, County and Zip Code in Time and Labor.  When they are transferred to Fusion Payroll, they will be transferred into the appropriate fields: Area1, Area2, Area3 and Area4. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  This combination of values  is specifically for use by the US Localization for Payroll.  Other localizations will use this functionality as well, with ability to use different input values based on the localization, but always utilizing Area1 \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Area4 fields.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:30:16'),(6734,'Feature',1336,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Work Location Attribute - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:30:16 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1336\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support existing Core Payroll and Localization requirements for work location data\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  For Payroll use, we will offer a Work Location layout component, which will offer a smart choice listing of concatenated values: city, state, county and zip code.  The reason for the concatenated values is for easy entry, so that the user does not need to enter 4 separate fields.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Additionally, we should see if we can add \\\"smart filtering\\\" in which not all work location combinations have to be shown to each employee, if there is a way to filter that list per person.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  These values will be stored separately as City, State, County and Zip Code in Time and Labor.  When they are transferred to Fusion Payroll, they will be transferred into the appropriate fields: Area1, Area2, Area3 and Area4. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  This combination of values  is specifically for use by the US Localization for Payroll.  Other localizations will use this functionality as well, with ability to use different input values based on the localization, but always utilizing Area1 \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Area4 fields.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:30:34'),(6735,'Feature',1336,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Work Location - Added Functionality of entry\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:31:44 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1336\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"For Payroll use, we will offer a Work Location layout component, which will offer a smart choice listing of concatenated values: city, state, county and zip code.  The reason for the concatenated values is for easy entry, so that the user does not need to enter 4 separate fields.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Additionally, we should see if we can add \\\"smart filtering\\\" in which not all work location combinations have to be shown to each employee, if there is a way to filter that list per person.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  These values will be stored separately as City, State, County and Zip Code in Time and Labor.  When they are transferred to Fusion Payroll, they will be transferred into the appropriate fields: Area1, Area2, Area3 and Area4. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  This combination of values  is specifically for use by the US Localization for Payroll.  Other localizations will use this functionality as well, with ability to use different input values based on the localization, but always utilizing Area1 \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Area4 fields.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:31:50'),(6736,'Feature',1335,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Additional Attributes Icon and Pop Up Page - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 20:16:02 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1335\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support Tier 1 Timecard UI Display shown to customers\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Allow for configurable option to display one  pop-up page in the matrix to display dependent fields of a previously entered time attribute or additional optional attributes which the user did not want placed on the main timecard matrix.  This information is at a row level, pertaining to all hours entered on that row.  Examples of dependent fields are input types for Elements or \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cestimate to complete\\xE2\\x80\\x9D for a Project ID.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Additionally, there should be a hover over the icon for the user to see the attributes which are contained inside the pop-up page for entry as an easy reference.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Finally, so the user or approver knows if there is data contained in this pop-up page, there should be different modes of the icon, one to display when the pop-up page has no data entered, and another to display when the pop-up page does contain data.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:33:58'),(6737,'Feature',1335,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Additional Attributes Icon and Pop Up Page\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:34:07 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1335\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Allow for configurable option to display one  pop-up page in the matrix to display dependent fields of a previously entered time attribute or additional optional attributes which the user did not want placed on the main timecard matrix.  This information is at a row level, pertaining to all hours entered on that row.  Examples of dependent fields are input types for Elements or \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cestimate to complete\\xE2\\x80\\x9D for a Project ID.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:34:11'),(6738,'Feature',1516,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 06:34:33'),(6739,'Feature',1516,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Add Attributes Page\ncreated_at: 2011-05-30 06:34:33 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:34:33 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1516\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 175\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:35:10'),(6740,'Feature',1517,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 06:36:00'),(6741,'Feature',1517,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Additionla Attributes Icon - Approver Actions\ncreated_at: 2011-05-30 06:36:00 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:36:00 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1517\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 175\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:36:32'),(6742,'Feature',1334,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Daily Details  Icon and Pop Up Page - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 20:14:38 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1334\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: |\n  Must Have Justification :  Support Tier 1 Timecard UI Display shown to customers\r\n  \r\n  Provide ability to drill down into daily details for the Timecard to enter additional fields required by retrieving applications (DFFs).  The display will be on a daily basis, to allow the user to have different entries for each day listed on the timecard matrix row.  This can be done with a Daily Details icon at the end of each row.   Only the days which contain hours or time entries should be displayed on the Daily Details pop-up for display.  That will make it easier for the user to only enter detail for the days which are required. \r\n  \r\n  In the Daily Details, we will also have a Comments field for each day for daily comments as well.  Initial prototypes tested at customer feedback sessions in January 2010 had separate icons for Daily Comments and Daily Details, to easily differentiate the two areas of entry.  To consolidate columns, the two areas are being combined into the Daily Details icon.\r\n  \r\n  Additionally, there should be a hover over the icon for the user to see the attributes which are contained inside the pop-up page for entry as an easy reference.  \r\n  \r\n  Finally, so the user or approver knows if there is data contained in this pop-up page, there should be different modes of the icon, one to display when the pop-up page has no data entered, and another to display when the pop-up page does contain data.\r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:38:42'),(6743,'Feature',1334,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Daily Details  Icon and Pop Up Page - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:38:42 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1334\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: |\n  Provide ability to drill down into daily details for the Timecard to enter additional fields required by retrieving applications (DFFs).  \r\n  \r\n  The display will be on a daily basis, to allow the user to have different entries for each day listed on the timecard matrix row.  This can be done with a Daily Details icon at the end of each row.   Only the days which contain hours or time entries should be displayed on the Daily Details pop-up for display.  That will make it easier for the user to only enter detail for the days which are required. \r\n  \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:38:48'),(6744,'Feature',1518,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 06:39:38'),(6745,'Feature',1519,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 06:39:57'),(6746,'Feature',1520,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 06:40:28'),(6747,'Feature',1518,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Daily Details Icon - Hover Over Display\ncreated_at: 2011-05-30 06:39:38 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:39:38 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1518\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 175\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:40:55'),(6748,'Feature',1520,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Daily Details Icon Changes to Signify existing Entries\ncreated_at: 2011-05-30 06:40:28 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:40:28 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1520\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 175\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:41:16'),(6749,'Feature',1518,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Daily Details Icon - Hover Over Display\ncreated_at: 2011-05-30 06:39:38 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:40:55 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1518\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 175\ndescription: |\n  In the Daily Details, we will also have a Comments field for each day for daily comments as well.  Initial prototypes tested at customer feedback sessions in January 2010 had separate icons for Daily Comments and Daily Details, to easily differentiate the two areas of entry.  To consolidate columns, the two areas are being combined into the Daily Details icon.\r\n  \r\n  Additionally, there should be a hover over the icon for the user to see the attributes which are contained inside the pop-up page for entry as an easy reference.  \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:41:41'),(6750,'Feature',1519,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Daily Details Comment Entries\ncreated_at: 2011-05-30 06:39:57 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:39:57 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1519\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 175\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:41:49'),(6751,'Feature',1332,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Matrix - Line Numbers - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 20:13:12 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1332\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support Fusion error messaging UX guidelines\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Display line numbers in the timecard matrix which would assist in identifying lines for error messages, as well as easy reference to a line in question for review or troubleshooting.  If a user inserts a new row in between existing rows, then the new row and subsequent rows would need to be renumbered accordingly\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:42:09'),(6752,'Feature',1332,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Matrix - Display Line Numbers\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:42:24 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1332\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Display line numbers in the timecard matrix which would assist in identifying lines for error messages, as well as easy reference to a line in question for review or troubleshooting.  If a user inserts a new row in between existing rows, then the new row and subsequent rows would need to be renumbered accordingly\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:42:28'),(6753,'Feature',1331,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Matrix - View Menu Options - Freeze, Sort, Detach - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 20:13:23 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1331\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"         Must Have Justification :  Support Fusion Table View Options\\r\\n Enable the following view menu actions for the timecard matrix- \\r\\n\\\n  Freeze \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Allow the user the ability to freeze columns within the timecard matrix and for that display to persist from session to session.  There would be a menu action and toolbar action to allow the user to enable the freezing of columns.  The user will highlight the column he wants to freeze on, and selects the Freeze action from the toolbar or menu action.  All columns to the right of that frozen column can be scrolled across horizontally, while the columns to the left  of the frozen column will remain static.  This is the same concept if you used \\xE2\\x80\\x9CWindow, Freeze Panes\\xE2\\x80\\x9D action in an excel spreadsheet.\\r\\n\\\n  For this timecard example below, the user could freeze the Hours Type column, so that all the days to the right of the Hours Type column could be scrolled to the left, while the user could still see the Project, Task, Expenditure Type and Hours Type he entered on that row.  This functionality would allow the user to keep the context of what he is entering for each day.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n \\r\\n\\\n  \\tSort \\xE2\\x80\\x93Allow user to sort the columns in the timecard matrix in ascending or descending manner.  Each column heading would have a sort indicator to note that the column can be sorted in an ascending or descending manner.  Example of sort display can be seen in the display of the column \\xE2\\x80\\x9CContract Number\\xE2\\x80\\x9D below, in which when the column is highlighted, a black arrow pointing down is displayed, and 2 white arrows are shown to the right of the column header to allow the user to sort ascending (up arrow) or descending order (Down arrow).  Note: Not all fields will be sortable in the timecard, the ability to sort the field will be configured in the layout component and  layout set in the Time Entry Page Composer.\\r\\n \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  The Advanced Sort option is offered from the View Menu Option:\\r\\n \\r\\n \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Detach \\xE2\\x80\\x93 this viewing function supports the ADF table component to allow a user to click on a Detach action from the Timecard Matrix toolbar.  This will maximize the table display to enhance the viewing of the timecard columns.  This action is available from the View drop down menu as well as the toolbar.  This table action is formerly known as Maximize.\\r\\n \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Here is an example of a Detached Table, which is a \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cmaximized\\xE2\\x80\\x9D view which takes up a full page, allowing for easier visibility:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:43:53'),(6754,'Feature',1331,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Matrix - Freeze / Sort / Detach Functionality\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:45:08 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1331\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Enable the following view menu actions for the timecard matrix- \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Freeze \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Allow the user the ability to freeze columns within the timecard matrix and for that display to persist from session to session.  There would be a menu action and toolbar action to allow the user to enable the freezing of columns.  The user will highlight the column he wants to freeze on, and selects the Freeze action from the toolbar or menu action.  All columns to the right of that frozen column can be scrolled across horizontally, while the columns to the left  of the frozen column will remain static.  This is the same concept if you used \\xE2\\x80\\x9CWindow, Freeze Panes\\xE2\\x80\\x9D action in an excel spreadsheet.\\r\\n\\\n  For this timecard example below, the user could freeze the Hours Type column, so that all the days to the right of the Hours Type column could be scrolled to the left, while the user could still see the Project, Task, Expenditure Type and Hours Type he entered on that row.  This functionality would allow the user to keep the context of what he is entering for each day.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n \\r\\n\\\n  Sort \\xE2\\x80\\x93Allow user to sort the columns in the timecard matrix in ascending or descending manner.  Each column heading would have a sort indicator to note that the column can be sorted in an ascending or descending manner.  Example of sort display can be seen in the display of the column \\xE2\\x80\\x9CContract Number\\xE2\\x80\\x9D below, in which when the column is highlighted, a black arrow pointing down is displayed, and 2 white arrows are shown to the right of the column header to allow the user to sort ascending (up arrow) or descending order (Down arrow).  Note: Not all fields will be sortable in the timecard, the ability to sort the field will be configured in the layout component and  layout set in the Time Entry Page Composer.\\r\\n \\r\\n\\\n  The Advanced Sort option is offered from the View Menu Option:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Detach \\xE2\\x80\\x93 this viewing function supports the ADF table component to allow a user to click on a Detach action from the Timecard Matrix toolbar.  This will maximize the table display to enhance the viewing of the timecard columns.  This action is available from the View drop down menu as well as the toolbar.  This table action is formerly known as Maximize.\\r\\n \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Here is an example of a Detached Table, which is a \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cmaximized\\xE2\\x80\\x9D view which takes up a full page, allowing for easier visibility:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:45:16'),(6755,'Feature',1328,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Matrix Actions - Duplicate Row\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:45:36 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1328\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"\\xE2\\x80\\x93(New for Fusion)   to allow the user to select a line to copy.  The user selects the line to duplicate, and selects the action of duplicate.  A line will be inserted below the selected line, with the same attributes and hours and a new line number.  Would also like to be able to highlight multiple rows and select duplicate to be able to copy down multiple rows.\\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:45:41'),(6756,'Feature',1327,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Matrix Actions - Clear Hours - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 21:02:30 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1327\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"(New for Fusion)   This new timecard action was tested with customers and accepted in the HCM_Time&Labor_Usability_Feedback_Report_FINAL.doc.  This allows the user to select any or all rows in the timecard and clear out the hours.  The usefulness of this action is the user can retain attributes from prior timecards and just change the hours.  \\r\\n\\\n  For the user who wants to clear one row, he should select the row and use the timecard menu action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CClear Hours\\xE2\\x80\\x9D, or use the toolbar icon.  If the user wants to clear all hours for the timecard,  he should be able to select all rows of the timecard and use the Clear Hours action.  A message should pop-up to the user to alert them to the fact that all hour entries will be reset to zero.  Please refer to the Select All Fusion Guideline for selecting all rows whether visible or not:\\r\\n\\\n  http://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines4/tblInteraction.html#selectAll\\r\\n\\\n  From the Guideline:  When both row and column selection are implemented, clicking the intersection of the row and column headers selects all rows in the table\'s entire data set, regardless of whether they are in view or not. However, there may be a design limitation if the number of rows in the timecard exceed 300 rows: Note: In order to turn on the Select All functionality, the SQL statement must include an OrderBy and the table must have less than 300 rows.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:46:27'),(6757,'Feature',1327,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Matrix Actions - Clear Hours - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:46:27 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1327\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"This allows the user to select any or all rows in the timecard and clear out the hours.  \\r\\n\\\n  The usefulness of this action is the user can retain attributes from prior timecards and just change the hours.  \\r\\n\\\n  For the user who wants to clear one row, he should select the row and use the timecard menu action of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CClear Hours\\xE2\\x80\\x9D, or use the toolbar icon.  If the user wants to clear all hours for the timecard,  he should be able to select all rows of the timecard and use the Clear Hours action.  A message should pop-up to the user to alert them to the fact that all hour entries will be reset to zero.  Please refer to the Select All Fusion Guideline for selecting all rows whether visible or not:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  http://stux.us.oracle.com/blaf/guidelines4/tblInteraction.html#selectAll\\r\\n\\\n  From the Guideline:  When both row and column selection are implemented, clicking the intersection of the row and column headers selects all rows in the table\'s entire data set, regardless of whether they are in view or not. However, there may be a design limitation if the number of rows in the timecard exceed 300 rows: Note: In order to turn on the Select All functionality, the SQL statement must include an OrderBy and the table must have less than 300 rows.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:46:30'),(6758,'Feature',1326,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Timecard Matrix Actions - Delete Row \"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:46:39 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1326\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Provide ability to select a row in the timecard matrix and select the action of deleting a line to delete highlighted row.  User should be able to delete one or more rows at once, based on rows selected.  Once the user selects the action to delete, a warning message will be issued to the user: \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:46:51'),(6759,'Feature',1325,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Matrix Actions - Add Row - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 21:02:18 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1325\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"o\\tAdd Row \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Provide ability to add  one or more rows in timecard matrix for time entry.  The rows may need to be inserted between existing rows or would be new rows for additional entry.   The row needs to be added where the user expects, either in between existing rows or as the last row.   \\r\\n\\\n  In prior versions of Enterprise Time and Labor and EBS Time and Labor, new rows were added at the end of existing rows.  Rows could also be inserted between existing rows.  Additionally, users could tab to a \\xE2\\x80\\x9C+\\xE2\\x80\\x9D (plus) sign on existing row to add a new row below it.  This action worked well for users who are used to tabbing through their timecard fields for quick entry of time.\\r\\n\\\n  The Fusion table design pattern is to add a new row at the top of a table using the add action button.  To allow flexibility for users, we need to offer configuration which allows \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cadd row\\xE2\\x80\\x9D to add to the bottom of the table, or to the top of the table.  This should be offered as a configuration option in the layout set defined in the Time Entry Page Composer.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Adding a row to the bottom of the table is important for clock time users to see the clock times displayed in ascending order.  It is also a general expectation of timecard users to add rows to the bottom of their timecard.  Additionally, we need to allow for an add row icon at the row level, for users to tab to the field and click enter to add a new row below.  This is important for those reporting many rows in a single timecard or timekeepers entering many entries per worker or workers.   The need for this flexibility arose from strong customer feedback,  registered in the HCM_Time&Labor_Usability_Feedback_Report_FINAL.doc (3/26/2010)\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:47:26'),(6760,'Feature',1325,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Matrix Actions - Add Row\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:47:35 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1325\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Add Row \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Provide ability to add  one or more rows in timecard matrix for time entry.  The rows may need to be inserted between existing rows or would be new rows for additional entry.   The row needs to be added where the user expects, either in between existing rows or as the last row.   \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  In prior versions of Enterprise Time and Labor and EBS Time and Labor, new rows were added at the end of existing rows.  Rows could also be inserted between existing rows.  Additionally, users could tab to a \\xE2\\x80\\x9C+\\xE2\\x80\\x9D (plus) sign on existing row to add a new row below it.  This action worked well for users who are used to tabbing through their timecard fields for quick entry of time.\\r\\n\\\n  The Fusion table design pattern is to add a new row at the top of a table using the add action button.  To allow flexibility for users, we need to offer configuration which allows \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cadd row\\xE2\\x80\\x9D to add to the bottom of the table, or to the top of the table.  This should be offered as a configuration option in the layout set defined in the Time Entry Page Composer.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Adding a row to the bottom of the table is important for clock time users to see the clock times displayed in ascending order.  It is also a general expectation of timecard users to add rows to the bottom of their timecard.  Additionally, we need to allow for an add row icon at the row level, for users to tab to the field and click enter to add a new row below.  This is important for those reporting many rows in a single timecard or timekeepers entering many entries per worker or workers.   The need for this flexibility arose from strong customer feedback,  registered in the HCM_Time&Labor_Usability_Feedback_Report_FINAL.doc (3/26/2010)\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:47:39'),(6761,'Feature',1324,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Display hours and clock times - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 21:02:12 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1324\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support Existing EBS OTL R12 functionality of clock and hours display\\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to support a mixture of reporting hours and start/stop times with the correct related totals for the day.  For each entry there should either be a set of times or hours displayed.  Format of time should support military or civilian display.\\r\\n\\\n  If the set of times (Start and Stop Time) is entered, then we need to allow that entry of time,  can be used as a Stop Time for a Start Time as well as be used as a Start time for the next set of Start and Stop Times.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  For example: \\r\\n\\\n  8:00 am\\t\\tStart\\r\\n\\\n  10:00 am\\tStop\\r\\n\\\n  10:00 am\\tStart\\r\\n\\\n  12:00 pm\\tStop\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  In this example, 10:00am is used as a Stop time for one set of times, and a Start time for the next set of times reported..\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  If the user does enter Start and Stop Time for a time entry, they should not be entering hours for that same entry.  The entry of hours or times are mutually exclusive.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  We need to ensure we have time entry rules to generate an error message when a user enters both times and hours for the same time entry.  The graying out of fields would be an issue if the user changed their mind on what they wanted to enter, times or hours.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:48:16'),(6762,'Feature',1324,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Display hours and clock times\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:48:24 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1324\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Provide ability to support a mixture of reporting hours and start/stop times with the correct related totals for the day.  For each entry there should either be a set of times or hours displayed.  Format of time should support military or civilian display.\\r\\n\\\n  If the set of times (Start and Stop Time) is entered, then we need to allow that entry of time,  can be used as a Stop Time for a Start Time as well as be used as a Start time for the next set of Start and Stop Times.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  For example: \\r\\n\\\n  8:00 am\\t\\tStart\\r\\n\\\n  10:00 am\\tStop\\r\\n\\\n  10:00 am\\tStart\\r\\n\\\n  12:00 pm\\tStop\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  In this example, 10:00am is used as a Stop time for one set of times, and a Start time for the next set of times reported..\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  If the user does enter Start and Stop Time for a time entry, they should not be entering hours for that same entry.  The entry of hours or times are mutually exclusive.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  We need to ensure we have time entry rules to generate an error message when a user enters both times and hours for the same time entry.  The graying out of fields would be an issue if the user changed their mind on what they wanted to enter, times or hours.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:48:28'),(6763,'Feature',1323,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Smart choice lists - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 21:02:06 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1323\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Core Fusion Architecture Uptake \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  All time attributes which previously used LOVs must have values displayed with smart choice lists, including all descriptive flexfields.  This is a Fusion requirement for UI.  These smart choice lists will list values such as Most Recently Used values before showing a search link to search for more entries. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:48:43'),(6764,'Feature',1323,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard allows for Smart choice lists\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:48:59 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1323\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"All time attributes which previously used LOVs must have values displayed with smart choice lists, including all descriptive flexfields.  This is a Fusion requirement for UI.  These smart choice lists will list values such as Most Recently Used values before showing a search link to search for more entries. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:49:04'),(6765,'Feature',1320,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Configurable fields in timecard - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 05:08:08 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1320\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"Provide ability to display appropriate fields in timecard matrix based on delivered layout.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  The use of delivered layouts will depend on the configurability offered in the Layout Editor FDD for Timecard.  ( See Appendix A for existing delivered layouts from R12.)  The ability to configure the display of each section of the timecard online is new for Fusion.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:49:18'),(6766,'Feature',1320,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Enable Configurable Attribute fields on the timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 06:49:48 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1320\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 27\ndescription: \"The use of delivered layouts will depend on the configurability offered in the Layout Editor FDD for Timecard.  ( See Appendix A for existing delivered layouts from R12.)  The ability to configure the display of each section of the timecard online is new for Fusion.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:49:53'),(6767,'FunctionalWorkUnit',27,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Timecard Matrix\ncreated_at: 2011-04-08 00:26:16 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-08 00:26:16 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 171\nid: 27\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:50:00'),(6768,'Feature',1333,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Inline Error Messages - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 18:05:16 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1333\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 144\ndescription: |\n  Must Have Justification :  Support Fusion error messaging UX guidelines\r\n  \r\n  Allow for easy inline error messages for invalid time, with indications on the reported cells.  The inline error messaging should allow for the highlighting of any field in the timecard matrix, including a particular entry of hours or Start/Stop times.  \r\n  \r\n  Offer a \"Show Messages\" button as a way to get the \"error message list\" dialog . Also, the user will have the dialog box open when they access the timecard entry page if there are existing errors.   We may not need the Show Messages button, if user clicks on each highlighted field the message display will pop-up again.   Will also have the dialog expanded when selecting the  Next button, if error messages still exist.\r\n  \r\n  If the user clicks on the message link and is taken to the line in error, he should always be able to access the error message listing dialog, to view all messages again.\r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 06:53:07'),(6769,'FunctionalWorkUnit',143,'update','3','--- \nname: Timecard - General Features - JF\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:10:03 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 07:15:30 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 171\nid: 143\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:15:52'),(6770,'Feature',1316,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Review Page - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:27:21 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1316\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 145\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Of two options offered to customers, this option can be delivered within our technical \\tconstraints of use of Descriptive Flexfields\\r\\n\\\n  Provide a table display view of one week at a time.  The days will be displayed vertically on the left hand column and all attributes will be displayed to the right of the days.  Daily detail and comments will be separate columns in the grid.  All data from pop-up pages on attributes and details will be concatenated in an Attributes and Details column.\\r\\n\\\n  If there is more than one week in the review, there should be the ability to collapse each week display, so the vertical scroll of the page is lessened and the user an focus on the detail of one week at a time.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:19:28'),(6771,'Feature',1316,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Layout of Review Page\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 07:20:02 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1316\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 145\ndescription: \"Provide a table display view of one week at a time.  The days will be displayed vertically on the left hand column and all attributes will be displayed to the right of the days.  Daily detail and comments will be separate columns in the grid.  All data from pop-up pages on attributes and details will be concatenated in an Attributes and Details column.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  If there is more than one week in the review, there should be the ability to collapse each week display, so the vertical scroll of the page is lessened and the user an focus on the detail of one week at a time.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:20:20'),(6772,'FunctionalWorkUnit',145,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Review Page\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:57:41 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 12:57:41 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 190\nid: 145\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:20:31'),(6773,'Feature',1317,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Change and Late Audit Timecard Flow - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-05 21:27:31 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1317\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 146\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Uptake of existing EBS OTL R12 functionality\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to enter change and late audit reasons in the defined Audit Entry page for a Change and Late Audit Layout Set, as well as incorporate all of the change and late audit reasons and comments, and show changed time in the Audit Review page.  The flow would be Timecard Entry page, the Audit Entry page, the Timecard Review page, with ability to submit the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:20:58'),(6774,'Feature',1317,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Process Flow when CLA is enabled\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 07:21:24 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1317\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 146\ndescription: \"Provide ability to enter change and late audit reasons in the defined Audit Entry page for a Change and Late Audit Layout Set, as well as incorporate all of the change and late audit reasons and comments, and show changed time in the Audit Review page.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  The flow would be Timecard Entry page, the Audit Entry page, the Timecard Review page, with ability to submit the timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:21:30'),(6775,'Feature',1361,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Approval Flow - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 21:39:48 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1361\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 149\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support Existing EBS OTL R12 Approval functionality\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Provide ability to trigger Approval flows upon timecard submission via the AMX approvals engine.  The flow \\ttriggered will be based on the approval transaction type associated to the timecard, based on the worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s time consumer set.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:22:00'),(6776,'Feature',1361,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Enable AMX Approvals upon Submission of the Timecard\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 07:22:37 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1361\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 149\ndescription: \"Provide ability to trigger Approval flows upon timecard submission via the AMX approvals engine.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  The flow triggered will be based on the approval transaction type associated to the timecard, based on the worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s time consumer set.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:22:41'),(6777,'FunctionalWorkUnit',149,'destroy','3','--- \nname: AMX Process Flows\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 16:25:09 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 22:49:15 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 190\nid: 149\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:22:47'),(6778,'FunctionalWorkUnit',146,'destroy','3','--- \nname: CLA Reason Page\ncreated_at: 2011-05-02 12:57:52 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-02 12:57:52 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 190\nid: 146\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:22:50'),(6779,'BusinessArea',190,'destroy','3','--- \nname: Timecard Flows - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 21:36:14 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 16:41:08 Z\nid: 190\nparent_id: 205\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 07:22:53'),(6780,'BusinessArea',221,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 12:43:04'),(6781,'BusinessArea',222,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 12:44:06'),(6782,'BusinessArea',223,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 12:45:48'),(6783,'Feature',1306,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Enable HRs Person Contextual Action from Person Name\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 12:58:14 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1306\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \"Uptake the use of the HR Person Contextual Action for any display of the worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s name, especially in the Person Header section of the timecard.  Upon clicking on the orange icon to the left of the person\\xE2\\x80\\x99s name, a pop up dialog box will offer additional information about Leslie for further communication.  Upon clicking the Close button, the dialog box will close.\\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 12:58:28'),(6784,'Feature',1310,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Additional Information Sections - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 20:20:51 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1310\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \"Provide more real estate in the timecard page so the user can\\r\\n\\\n  focus on the timecard matrix for time entry.  As a result, there\\r\\n\\\n  will be additional pieces of information that a user may want to\\r\\n\\\n  reference, but not view at all times. These sections should be \\\"information\\r\\n\\\n  on demand\\\", available to the user when needed.  Such sections include:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  a.\\tTimecard Comments \\xE2\\x80\\x93 comments for the overall timecard.  This section is currently displayed in the prototype as an open text field above the timecard matrix, so it is always open.\\r\\n\\\n  b.\\tAccrual Balances \\xE2\\x80\\x93 listing balances for all leave plans the worker is associated to.  The two options agreed upon were either show:\\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tAccrual Balance display open in the contextual section of the timecard, balance display provided by Absence Management\\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tOpen section in local area of the timecard, showing just 2 accrual balances, with a MORE link, to view all accrual balances in a pop-up page.\\r\\n\\\n  d.\\tApproval Comments \\xE2\\x80\\x93 comments from each timecard approver. This section should only be displayed if data exists.  If the timecard has not been routed for approval as of yet, the Approval Comments section or dialog box should not be displayed.  If there are Approval Comments, as the user enters the page, the Approval Comments message listing should pop-up like the Error Message listing does.  It should always be available to the user to re-access if they close the approval comments.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 17:08:56'),(6785,'Feature',1385,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Calendar Time Entry - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 16:37:15 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1385\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 169\ndescription: \"Nice to Have Justification:  Enhanced calendar ability to update time \\r\\n Provide ability to report time via the use of a calendar.  The calendar can be used to display reported hours, scheduled hours, calculated hours (results from time calculation rules), as well as a method to report time.  The calendar could be color-coded to show the different types of time or the user could change the display type by a choice list.  A user could report time in a variety of ways:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tClick on a day, a pop-up page is display, enter hours and time attributes and upon close of the pop-up, the time will be saved for the day\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tHighlight a range of dates in the calendar, and enter number of hours and time attributes which should be associated to each day in that highlighted range, via a pop up page.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 20:39:11'),(6786,'Feature',1471,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Calendar Display of Missing Time  - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-05-05 21:45:43 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 16:37:38 Z\npriority: Nice to Have\nid: 1471\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 169\ndescription: |\n  Nice to Have Justification:  Recurring Feature in Competitor Functionality\r\n  \r\n  Provide the ability to highlight a calendar view of which days within a timecard period are missing time entry.  This will be helpful to compare for workers who are required to enter time daily on scheduled days, in order to get paid.\r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 20:39:30'),(6787,'Feature',1368,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Workflow Notifications - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 16:38:31 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1368\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 170\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support Existing EBS OTL R12 notification functionality and add notifications to complete proper processing of timecards\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  There are various notifications which revolve around the reporting of time.  Below are some of the notifications.  Additional notifications are noted in Item #20 in Section 2.3.1.1. Should Have Functionality for the Worker Timecard.  These notifications would be triggered by different events of the timecard and would trigger workflow tasks.  The output of the workflow notifications could be email notifications, worklist items or both.  Worklist items would display in the main Worklist on the general Welcome tab as well as the on the Timecards Workarea overview page for Time and Labor.  The configuration of which notification types occurs would be in the workflow setup. \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Currently in EBS R12, there is a notification to the manager or employee if a timekeeper has made changes to a timecard or has entered late time.  This notification relates to users who are using the Change and Late Audit functionality for tracking changes to time or late time entries.  There is configuration in Time and Labor to determine which role gets the notification and if the worklist item is actionable or just for their information.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  In Fusion, the determination of who gets the notifications should be handled in the AMX or workflow setup, assuming that roles are supported for routing rules.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Another option for worklist or email notifications are alerts.  One method for online alerts, are the use of  Watchlist items, which are summaries of items which require attention.  The resulting displays for Watchlists are saved searches.  Watchlist items will be explored further in the Time and Labor Dashboard FDD.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  1.\\tRequireApproval Notifications -   Deliver worklist notifications for timecards requiring approval via AMX Approvals Engine to approvers.  Approvers of timecards (who may be managers) would need to be notified of any timecards requiring their approval.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  2.\\tRejected Timecards Notifications -   Deliver worklist notifications for timecards which have been rejected in the approval process via the AMX Approvals Engine to those who need to resolve or correct the rejected timecards, such as workers or timekeepers.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  3.\\tTime change Notifications \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Provide an option to trigger email notifications when a timecard is modified.  This notification should only be triggered on a submit of  a timecard, not on Save.  Options would include notification to worker, to timekeeper or manager.  The notification would need to communicate to the recipient if the timecard was modified, including  the fields of  \\xE2\\x80\\x9CLast Modified By\\xE2\\x80\\x9D and \\xE2\\x80\\x9CDate of Action\\xE2\\x80\\x9D.  Development would need to seed a worklist notification to display for a modified timecard.  Would be beneficial if it can be defined what changes had occurred in the timecard.  If this is not possible, there should be a link to the timecard to view the modified timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  4.\\tTimecard for Resolution Notification \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Provide a worklist notification to the timekeeper or administrator of timecards which need error resolution which a worker cannot resolve.  This is normally due to setup object changes which are needed such as rules.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 20:41:02'),(6788,'Feature',1368,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: \"Workflow Notifications - CLA TK / Mgr Entries \"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 20:41:59 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1368\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 170\ndescription: \"Currently in EBS R12, there is a notification to the manager or employee if a timekeeper has made changes to a timecard or has entered late time.  This notification relates to users who are using the Change and Late Audit functionality for tracking changes to time or late time entries.  There is configuration in Time and Labor to determine which role gets the notification and if the worklist item is actionable or just for their information.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  In Fusion, the determination of who gets the notifications should be handled in the AMX or workflow setup, assuming that roles are supported for routing rules.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Another option for worklist or email notifications are alerts.  One method for online alerts, are the use of  Watchlist items, which are summaries of items which require attention.  The resulting displays for Watchlists are saved searches.  Watchlist items will be explored further in the Time and Labor Dashboard FDD.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  1.\\tRequireApproval Notifications -   Deliver worklist notifications for timecards requiring approval via AMX Approvals Engine to approvers.  Approvers of timecards (who may be managers) would need to be notified of any timecards requiring their approval.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  2.\\tRejected Timecards Notifications -   Deliver worklist notifications for timecards which have been rejected in the approval process via the AMX Approvals Engine to those who need to resolve or correct the rejected timecards, such as workers or timekeepers.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  3.\\tTime change Notifications \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Provide an option to trigger email notifications when a timecard is modified.  This notification should only be triggered on a submit of  a timecard, not on Save.  Options would include notification to worker, to timekeeper or manager.  The notification would need to communicate to the recipient if the timecard was modified, including  the fields of  \\xE2\\x80\\x9CLast Modified By\\xE2\\x80\\x9D and \\xE2\\x80\\x9CDate of Action\\xE2\\x80\\x9D.  Development would need to seed a worklist notification to display for a modified timecard.  Would be beneficial if it can be defined what changes had occurred in the timecard.  If this is not possible, there should be a link to the timecard to view the modified timecard.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  4.\\tTimecard for Resolution Notification \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Provide a worklist notification to the timekeeper or administrator of timecards which need error resolution which a worker cannot resolve.  This is normally due to setup object changes which are needed such as rules.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  There are various notifications which revolve around the reporting of time.  Below are some of the notifications.  Additional notifications are noted in Item #20 in Section 2.3.1.1. Should Have Functionality for the Worker Timecard.  These notifications would be triggered by different events of the timecard and would trigger workflow tasks.  The output of the workflow notifications could be email notifications, worklist items or both.  Worklist items would display in t