 should allow for the highlighting of any field in the timecard matrix, including a particular entry of hours or Start/Stop times.\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:10:19'),(6803,'Feature',1497,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"1.0\"\nname: Display Message Dialog - Button or Selection\ncreated_at: 2011-05-26 18:38:37 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-26 19:35:33 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1497\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 171\ndescription: |\n  Must Have Justification :  Support Fusion error messaging UX guidelines\r\n  \r\n  Offer a \"Show Messages\" button as a way to get the \"error message list\" dialog . Also, the user will have the dialog box open when they access the timecard entry page if there are existing errors.   We may not need the Show Messages button, if user clicks on each highlighted field the message display will pop-up again.   Will also have the dialog expanded when selecting the  Next button, if error messages still exist.\r\n  \r\n  If the user clicks on the message link and is taken to the line in error, he should always be able to access the error message listing dialog, to view all messages again.\r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:10:49'),(6804,'Feature',1312,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Timecard Populated By - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 20:20:57 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1312\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: |\n  Must Have Justification :  In Current Tier 1 Timecard UX presented by UX\r\n  This field will be displayed above the timecard matrix to alert the user if a default template has pre-populated a new timecard.  The field will be populated with a read-only text of the Template name.  If the default template could not be used to populate the timecard because the layout set or timecard period of the current timecard do not match the template, next to the template name, there should be an icon (!), with a hover over explaining the default template does not match the current layout set and timecard period.  There should also be a global message displayed to the user in the Message section of the timecard to alert the user that the default template ccould not be used and to select an alternate default Template on Timecard Options of their Workarea.\r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:14:28'),(6805,'Feature',1318,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Configurable Sections for Timecard Entry, Review and Confirmation Pages - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 20:21:04 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1318\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Uptake of Fusion Page Action Guidelines \\r\\n\\\n  Refer to Time Entry Page Composer FDD for full details.  Some of the requested configurations include:\\r\\n\\\n  a.\\tAbility to collapse by default some sections\\r\\n\\\n  b.\\tAbility to retain order of rows entered by line number in Time Detail section \\r\\n\\\n  c.\\tRule Results \\xE2\\x80\\x93 ability to show the hours type against the correct rows \\r\\n\\\n  d.\\tRule Results \\xE2\\x80\\x93 ability to have flexibility to show any hour types \\r\\n\\\n  e.\\tTime Summary - would like to see this section on top of the page for Review page\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:14:33'),(6806,'FunctionalWorkUnit',177,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 21:17:14'),(6807,'Feature',1526,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 21:18:24'),(6808,'Feature',1527,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 21:18:59'),(6809,'Feature',1528,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-30 21:19:34'),(6810,'Feature',1526,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Info on Demand - Timecard Level Comments\ncreated_at: 2011-05-30 21:18:24 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 21:18:43 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1526\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 177\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:19:42'),(6811,'Feature',1527,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Info on Demand - Accrual Balances\ncreated_at: 2011-0