.  This design is for users who want the data displayed all the time.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:35:56'),(6834,'Feature',1533,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Timecard Add\'l Info Sections Design - Pop up Sections\ncreated_at: 2011-05-30 21:34:41 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 21:35:30 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1533\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \"Configuration Options:   These configuration options were previously discussed for Time Entry Page Composer, please see above options for latest recommendations from UX.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tPop Up Information sections \\xE2\\x80\\x93 These sections of data can be presented via pop up pages from hyperlinks above the timecard matrix.  When the user clicks on the hyperlink, the related section will be in a pop-up page, which should be modeless, so the user can move the pop-up to another part of the timecard page, while being able to edit the timecard matrix.  This is especially important for the Approval Comment section, as the details of this pop-up will guide the user on what to address in the timecard matrix\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:36:02'),(6835,'Feature',1321,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Time Attribute Storage and Pre-population of values - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 20:21:19 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1321\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \"We will have the ability to offer entry in the timecard to perform\\r\\n any of the following functions:\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tcontain a single attribute with a related value set, which contains\\r\\n a where clause to filter the displayed values as needed\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tcan link a single attribute to another single attribute on a layout\\r\\n set (these linked attributes can be displayed or hidden on the timecard).\\r\\n  As these attributes are linked, the entry of one attribute value\\r\\n can default the value of the 2nd or related attribute\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tcontain an attribute which is displayed on the timecard, which can\\r\\n store but not display values for related attributes \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tcan have an attribute automatically populated with a default value,\\r\\n upon entry into the timecard based on the person\'s information\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:40:20'),(6836,'Feature',1321,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Time Attribute Selection and Storage Features / Functionality\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 21:41:00 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1321\nfeature_type: Business Rule\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \"We will have the ability to offer entry in the timecard to perform any of the following functions:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tcontain a single attribute with a related value set, which contains a where clause to filter the displayed values as needed\\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tcan link a single attribute to another single attribute on a layout set (these linked attributes can be displayed or hidden on the timecard).\\r\\n\\\n  As these attributes are linked, the entry of one attribute value can default the value of the 2nd or related attribute\\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tcontain an attribute which is displayed on the timecard, which can store but not display values for related attributes \\r\\n\\\n  >>\\tcan have an attribute automatically populated with a default value,\\r\\n\\\n  upon entry into the timecard based on the person\'s information\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:41:15'),(6837,'Feature',1322,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Worker Pref to Override Default field formats (decimal, date, etc)\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 21:42:31 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1322\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Application  of online timecard configuration in timecard layout sets, supporting existing EBS OTL R12 functionality\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  As per setup in the Timecard Layout Sets, allow for users to be able to enter time in different formats  and decimal precisions for dates, time, numbers, timezone and currencies.  The default regional preferences are delivered by ApplCore from the main Preferences menu link.  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n      \"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:42:42'),(6838,'Feature',1338,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Default Timecard Period Display - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-03 20:23:03 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1338\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \"Must Have Justification :  Support EBS OTL R12.1 Enhancement\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  A user will be brought into a worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s timecard via the timecard period predefined for the user.  Based on Time and Labor Setup Profile Options, the worker, manager and timekeeper can have different default time periods associated to them.   This is currently described as a feature of Worker Core Processing Setup Profile.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  EBS OTL R12.1 Enhancement Options: \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tPeriod On or After System Date- Sets the open timecard period from current date for a new timecard\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tEarlier Period Prior to System Date-Sets the earliest not entered timecard period prior to system date for a new timecard.  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tClosest Period Prior to System date-Sets the closest not entered timecard period prior to system date for a new timecard. We may need to offer a window of how far back to go, as the last timecard period may be very far in the past.  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tExample of each of these options:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Assuming the system date is 15-Mar-2008\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tPeriod on or after System Date: Current timecard for March 17-March 23 would be opened as Timecard for March 15 is already entered.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tClosest Period Prior to System Date:  Would backtrack from system date and open the timecard period which is not yet entered, like Feb 11 to Feb 17.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tEarliest Period Prior to System Date: Would start from the first timecard period and open the timecard period which is not entered. In this case assuming all timecards for year 2007 have been entered excepting the last period, it would default to Dev 31 to Jan 06 period.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:43:21'),(6839,'Feature',1338,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Default Timecard Period Display - jf\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 21:43:21 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1338\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 143\ndescription: \"A user will be brought into a worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s timecard via the timecard period predefined for the user.  Based on Time and Labor Setup Profile Options, the worker, manager and timekeeper can have different default time periods associated to them.   This is currently described as a feature of Worker Core Processing Setup Profile.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  EBS OTL R12.1 Enhancement Options: \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tPeriod On or After System Date- Sets the open timecard period from current date for a new timecard\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tEarlier Period Prior to System Date-Sets the earliest not entered timecard period prior to system date for a new timecard.  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tClosest Period Prior to System date-Sets the closest not entered timecard period prior to system date for a new timecard. We may need to offer a window of how far back to go, as the last timecard period may be very far in the past.  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tExample of each of these options:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Assuming the system date is 15-Mar-2008\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tPeriod on or after System Date: Current timecard for March 17-March 23 would be opened as Timecard for March 15 is already entered.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tClosest Period Prior to System Date:  Would backtrack from system date and open the timecard period which is not yet entered, like Feb 11 to Feb 17.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tEarliest Period Prior to System Date: Would start from the first timecard period and open the timecard period which is not entered. In this case assuming all timecards for year 2007 have been entered excepting the last period, it would default to Dev 31 to Jan 06 period.\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-30 21:44:44'),(6840,'Feature',1338,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Worker Timecard Period\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:23 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-30 21:45:08 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1338\nfeature_type: \"\"\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 166\ndescription: \"A user will be brought into a worker\\xE2\\x80\\x99s timecard via the timecard period predefined for the user.  Based on Time and Labor Setup Profile Options, the worker, manager and timekeeper can have different default time periods associated to them.   This is currently described as a feature of Worker Core Processing Setup Profile.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  EBS OTL R12.1 Enhancement Options: \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tPeriod On or After System Date- Sets the open timecard period from current date for a new timecard\\r\\n\\\n  o\\tEarlier Period Prior to System Date-Sets the earliest not entered timecard period prior to system date for a new timecard.  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tClosest Period Prior to System date-Sets the closest not entered timecard period prior to system date for a new timecard. We may need to offer a window of how far back to go, as the last timecard period may be very far in the past.  \\r\\n\\\n  o\\tExample of each of these options:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Assuming the system date is 15-Mar-2008\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tPeriod on or after System Date: Current timecard for March 17-March 23 would be opened as Timecard for March 15 is already entered.\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2\\tClosest Period Prior to System Date:  Would backtrack from system date and open the timecard period which is not yet entered, like Feb 11 to Feb 17.\\r\\n\\\