eration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:04:41'),(6954,'Feature',1256,'destroy','8','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Basic Search page for Time Consumer Set\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1256\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 130\ndescription: \"\\n        <p>User can search Time Consumer Sets using this feature </p>\\n        <p>Basic search is performed using \'Consumer Set Name\' or \'Description\' search fields of the Consumer Sets.  Based on the user input system will run a query to the tables and \\n        display the information in search restuls grid.</p> \\n        \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-31 21:05:59'),(6955,'Feature',1257,'destroy','8','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Advanced Search page for Time Consumer Sets\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1257\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 130\ndescription: \"\\n                    <p>Lets the user execute advanced queries based on logical operators and wildcards.</p>                     \\n                    <dt>Search can be executed using the following parameters</dt>\\n                    <dd>Time Consumer Name : Name of the Consumer Set, Choice list of consumers</dd>\\n                    <dd>Time Category Name : smart choicelist of all time categories, with a default of \\\"All Time Entry\\\".</dd>\\n                    <dd>Validation on Save : Yes/No Choicelist <dd>\\n                    <dd>Time Required : Yes/No Choicelist <dd>\\n                    <dd>Approval Period : Choice list of all repeating time periods</dd>  \\n                   \\n        \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-31 21:05:59'),(6956,'Feature',1258,'destroy','8','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Search Grid Results for Time Consumer Sets\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1258\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 130\ndescription: \"\\n                  <p>Results grid displays repeating consumer set details </p>\\n                  <p>Create, Edit, Delete and Duplicate buttons and Actions are included in the grid</p>\\n                  <p>Columns of the Search Results Grid are Name, Description of the Consumer Sets.</p>  \\n                  <p>The search results will initially defaults 10 last Consumer Sets created.  It also inculdes seed data.</p>\\n                  \\n                  \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-31 21:05:59'),(6957,'Feature',1259,'destroy','8','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Create Time Consumer Set\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1259\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 130\ndescription: \"\\n                  \'Create\' action or \'Create\' button from the Search Results grid are used to create new time consumer set. \\n                  \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-31 21:05:59'),(6958,'Feature',1260,'destroy','8','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Edit Time Consumer Set\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1260\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 130\ndescription: \"\\n                  Can edit Time consumer set deatils.\\n                  \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-31 21:05:59'),(6959,'Feature',1261,'destroy','8','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Delete Time Consumer Set\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1261\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 130\ndescription: \"\\n                  Can delete Time consumer set if it is not in use(\\\"In use\\\" is defined as being assigned to an employee via Time and Labor Setup Options,\\n                  or attached to a timecard).\\n                  \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-31 21:05:59'),(6960,'Feature',1262,'destroy','8','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Duplicate Time Consumer Set\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1262\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 130\ndescription: \"\\n                  Can duplicate Time consumer set deatils if it is not in use(\\\"In use\\\" is defined as being assigned to an employee via Time and Labor Setup Options,\\n                  or attached to a timecard).\\n                  \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-31 21:05:59'),(6961,'Feature',1263,'destroy','8','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Default values for Time Consumer Set\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1263\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 130\ndescription: \"\\n                   <p>\'Time Required\' = \'Yes\' default value</p>\\n                   <p>\'Validate on Save\'= \'No\' default value </p>\\n                   <p>\'Payroll\' and \'Project Status\' = Approved </>\\n                    \\n                  \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-05-31 21:05:59'),(6962,'FunctionalWorkUnit',130,'destroy','8','--- \nname: \"Time and Labor Setup Changes: Time Consumers\"\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-27 23:10:25 Z\nbusiness_area_id: 219\nid: 130\nparent_id: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:05:59'),(6963,'FunctionalWorkUnit',186,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 21:06:22'),(6964,'Feature',1546,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: Action Menu\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:00:33 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:00:33 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1546\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 180\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:06:37'),(6965,'FunctionalWorkUnit',187,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 21:06:56'),(6966,'FunctionalWorkUnit',188,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 21:07:07'),(6967,'Feature',1546,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Action Menu\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:00:33 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:06:37 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1546\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 180\ndescription: |\n  Action Menu - Create New (w/Icon), Update (w/Icon), Duplicate (w/Icon), Details (w/Icon),  Delete (w/Icon) \r\n  \r\n  Create (New) Icon- to Questionaire \r\n  \r\n  Update (Edit) Icon - to Task List - to Questionnaire (read-only mode)  \r\n  >> If not highlighting a line - then message to select layout\r\n  \r\n  Duplicate - to Questionaire then on to task list and other pages \r\n  >> If not highlighting a line - then message to select layout to duplicate the flow is: Duplicate - to Questionnaire (editable) - to Task List\r\n  \r\n  Delete Icon\r\n  >> If not highlighting a line - then message to select layout \r\n  >> If not linked \r\n  \r\n  View Details \r\n  >> Icon / Action item to display additional information for the Layout Set selected.  Information to include:\r\n  \r\n      List of Layout Components used\r\n      Applications selected when adding attributes \r\n      Setup Option Profiles that use the Layout Set\r\n      Currently deployed\r\n      DIfferent Page configurations (Modified CLA page, Manager Page differences, Override of rules attribute) |\r\n  \r\n  	(Button) - Navigate to Layout Components\r\n  >> 	Maybe a good option would be to provide a navigation from the Time Entry Matrix setup, when the user is adding layout component to the matrix, we could offer to create a new component from the matrix setup, depending on privilege assigned to the users. \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:07:50'),(6968,'BusinessArea',238,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-31 21:11:20'),(6969,'Feature',1548,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 21:13:28'),(6970,'Feature',1548,'update','8','--- \nscope: \nname: Page Actions\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:13:28 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:13:28 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1548\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 186\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:21:39'),(6971,'Feature',1549,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 21:23:14'),(6972,'Feature',1540,'update','8','--- \nscope: \nname: Search Section\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 20:37:01 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 20:37:01 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1540\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 132\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:27:14'),(6973,'Feature',1540,'update','8','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Search Section\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 20:37:01 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:27:14 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1540\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 132\ndescription: \"The 3 columns displaying in the Search Results Grid are:\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Name - User name for time period\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Period Type - Daily, Weekly, Monthly, Semi-Monthly are the delivered types\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Period Description\\xE2\\x80\\x93 User entered description for the period\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:38:55'),(6974,'Feature',1550,'create','3',NULL,'2011-05-31 21:42:50'),(6975,'Feature',1549,'update','8','--- \nscope: \nname: Basic and Advanced Search\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:23:14 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:23:14 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1549\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 186\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:43:25'),(6976,'Feature',1550,'update','3','--- \nscope: \nname: \"Rule when Attributes Seen / Updated differ from Ind and Mgr \"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:42:50 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:42:50 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1550\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 167\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:43:54'),(6977,'Feature',1549,'update','8','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Basic and Advanced Search\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:23:14 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:43:25 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1549\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 186\ndescription: \"Basic Search fields:\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2 Time Consumer Set Name\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2 Description  - user defined description of the time consumer set\\r\\n\\\n  \\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\\n  Advanced Search Fields:\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2 Time Category Name \\xE2\\x80\\x93 smart choicelist of all time categories, with a default of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CAll Time Entry\\xE2\\x80\\x9D\\t\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2 Validate on Save - Yes/No choicelist\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2 Time Required \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Yes/No choicelist\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2 Approval Period- choice list of all repeating time periods\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2 Approval Transaction Type-  different AMX approval transaction types associated to the Timecard\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:45:13'),(6978,'Feature',1551,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 21:46:05'),(6979,'Feature',1551,'update','8','--- \nscope: \nname: \"Search Grid Results \"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:46:05 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:46:31 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1551\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 186\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:48:29'),(6980,'Feature',1551,'update','8','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: \"Search Grid Results \"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:46:05 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:48:29 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1551\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 186\ndescription: |-\n  The 2 columns for the search results grid are :\r\n  Name\r\n  Description\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  o  The search results should initially default to the last 10 time consumer sets created.  There will be seeded sets which will also be listed\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 21:51:29'),(6981,'Feature',1548,'update','8','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Menu and Toolbar Actions\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:13:28 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:21:51 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1548\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 186\ndescription: \"For Menubar and Toolbar Actions\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Create - ability to add a new time consumer set, action also triggered from Create button\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Edit - ability to update an existing time consumer set\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Delete - ability to delete a time consumer configuration set (if it is not \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cin use\\xE2\\x80\\x9D i.e. assigned to an employee via Time and Labor Setup Options or attached to a timecard.)\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Duplicate - ability to duplicate or copy an existing time consumer set and rename it, as well as change the attributes.   Once user selects a time consumer set and selects the Duplicate function, a new \\xE2\\x80\\x9CCreate Time Consumer Set\\xE2\\x80\\x9D  page appears copying all values over from the selected time consumer set.  The user is required to complete or change these values before saving the page. If no required fields are unique, all values can be replicated.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:09:36'),(6982,'Feature',1539,'update','8','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Menu and Toolbar Actions\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 20:20:40 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:22:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1539\nfeature_type: Business Rule\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 132\ndescription: \"Create and Edit -  Toolbar Actions\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Create - When using the \\xE2\\x80\\x9Ccreate\\xE2\\x80\\x9D action or \\xE2\\x80\\x9Ccreate\\xE2\\x80\\x9D button from the Search Results grid, a user will be able to add a new repeating period\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Edit - Only the name of a repeating period can be edited, the other fields will be grayed out in read only mode, to protect the period.  This is because the period is \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  NO DELETE ACTION - repeating periods cannot be deleted.\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:10:04'),(6983,'BusinessProcess',22,'update','2','--- \nname: Setup Layout Composer\ncreated_at: 2011-05-11 18:25:05 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-11 18:25:05 Z\npriority: \nid: 22\nbpmn_content_type: application/octet-stream\niteration_id: 1\nbpmn_updated_at: 2011-05-11 18:25:05 Z\nbpmn_file_size: 47436\nbpmn_file_name: SetupLayoutComposer.bpmn\n','2011-05-31 22:21:36'),(6984,'BusinessProcessElement',570,'create','2',NULL,'2011-05-31 22:21:37'),(6985,'Flow',594,'create','2',NULL,'2011-05