\t\\t\\r\\n\\\n  \\xE2\\x80\\xA2 Contains  - searches for records that contain the given text string.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  - Saved Searches Box\\r\\n - Buttons for Search: Search/ Reset/ Save/ Add Fields\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:27:18'),(7068,'Feature',1551,'update','8','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: \"Search Grid Results \"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:46:05 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:51:29 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1551\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 186\ndescription: |\n  The 2 columns for the search results grid are :\r\n  Name\r\n  Description\r\n  \r\n  \r\n  o  The search results should initially default to the last 10 time consumer sets created.  There will be seeded sets which will also be listed\r\n  \r\n  Columns should be sortable\r\n  \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:28:58'),(7069,'Feature',1539,'update','8','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Menu and Toolbar Actions\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 20:20:40 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 22:10:04 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1539\nfeature_type: Business Rule\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 132\ndescription: \"Create and Edit -  Toolbar and Menubar Actions\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Create - When using the \\xE2\\x80\\x9Ccreate\\xE2\\x80\\x9D action or \\xE2\\x80\\x9Ccreate\\xE2\\x80\\x9D button from the Search Results grid, a user will be able to add a new repeating period\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Edit - Only the name of a repeating period can be edited, the other fields will be grayed out in read only mode, to protect the period.  This is because the period is \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  NO DELETE ACTION - repeating periods cannot be deleted.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  2. View Menu : Always Allow for Freeze/Unfreeze for our tables\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  3. Use Auto-Sizing on all tables, to eliminate white space below data\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:36:08'),(7070,'Feature',1548,'update','8','--- \nscope: \"1\"\nname: Menu and Toolbar Actions\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:13:28 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 22:09:36 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1548\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 186\ndescription: \"For Menubar and Toolbar Actions\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Actions:\\r\\n\\\n  Create - ability to add a new time consumer set, action also triggered from Create button\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Edit - ability to update an existing time consumer set\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Delete - ability to delete a time consumer configuration set (if it is not \\xE2\\x80\\x9Cin use\\xE2\\x80\\x9D i.e. assigned to an employee via Time and Labor Setup Options or attached to a timecard.)\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  Duplicate - ability to duplicate or copy an existing time consumer set and rename it, as well as change the attributes.   Once user selects a time consumer set and selects the Duplicate function, a new \\xE2\\x80\\x9CCreate Time Consumer Set\\xE2\\x80\\x9D  page appears copying all values over from the selected time consumer set.  The user is required to complete or change these values before saving the page. If no required fields are unique, all values can be replicated.\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  2. View Menu : Always Allow for Freeze/Unfreeze for our tables\\r\\n\\\n  \\r\\n\\\n  3. Use Auto-Sizing on all tables, to eliminate white space below data\\r\\n\"\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:36:47'),(7071,'Feature',1552,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 22:38:46'),(7072,'Feature',1553,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 22:38:56'),(7073,'Feature',1554,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 22:39:14'),(7074,'Feature',1555,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 22:40:03'),(7075,'Feature',1556,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 22:40:18'),(7076,'Feature',1554,'destroy','8','--- \nscope: \nname: \"Payroll \"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 22:39:14 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 22:39:14 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1554\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 187\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:40:36'),(7077,'Feature',1552,'update','8','--- \nscope: \nname: Set Definition\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 22:38:46 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 22:39:40 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1552\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 187\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:41:25'),(7078,'Feature',1553,'update','8','--- \nscope: \nname: Select Time Consumers\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 22:38:56 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 22:39:52 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1553\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 187\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:43:04'),(7079,'Feature',1546,'update','3','--- \nscope: \"\"\nname: Action Menu\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 21:00:33 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 21:07:50 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1546\nfeature_type: UI\nfunctional_work_unit_id: 180\ndescription: |\n  Action Menu - Create New (w/Icon), Update (w/Icon), Duplicate (w/Icon), Details (w/Icon),  Delete (w/Icon) \r\n  \r\n  Create (New) Icon- to Questionaire \r\n  \r\n  Update (Edit) Icon - to Task List - to Questionnaire (read-only mode)  \r\n  >> If not highlighting a line - then message to select layout\r\n  \r\n  Duplicate - to Questionaire then on to task list and other pages \r\n  >> If not highlighting a line - then message to select layout to duplicate the flow is: Duplicate - to Questionnaire (editable) - to Task List\r\n  \r\n  Delete Icon\r\n  >> If not highlighting a line - then message to select layout \r\n  >> If not linked \r\n  \r\n  View Details \r\n  >> Icon / Action item to display additional information for the Layout Set selected.  Information to include:\r\n  >> List of Layout Components used\r\n  >> Applications selected when adding attributes \r\n  >> Setup Option Profiles that use the Layout Set\r\n  >> Currently deployed\r\n  >> Different Page configurations (Modified CLA page, Manager Page differences, Override of rules attribute) |\r\n  \r\n  (Button) - Navigate to Layout Components\r\n  >> Maybe a good option would be to provide a navigation from the Time Entry Matrix setup, when the user is adding layout component to the matrix, we could offer to create a new component from the matrix setup, depending on privilege assigned to the users. \r\n\niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:52:11'),(7080,'Feature',1555,'update','8','--- \nscope: \nname: \"Time Consumer: Payroll\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 22:40:03 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 22:40:29 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1555\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 187\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:54:24'),(7081,'Feature',1556,'update','8','--- \nscope: \nname: \"Time Consumer: Projects\"\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 22:40:18 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 22:40:18 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1556\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 187\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-05-31 22:56:30'),(7082,'Feature',1557,'create','8',NULL,'2011-05-31 23:19:06'),(7083,'Feature',1557,'update','8','--- \nscope: \nname: Search Grid Results\ncreated_at: 2011-05-31 23:19:06 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-05-31 23:19:06 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1557\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 132\ndescription: \niteration_id: 1\n','2011-06-01 06:22:46'),(7084,'Feature',1267,'destroy','8','--- \nscope: \"2.0\"\nname: Search Grid Results\ncreated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\nupdated_at: 2011-04-13 22:38:22 Z\npriority: Must Have\nid: 1267\nfeature_type: \nfunctional_work_unit_id: 132\ndescription: \"\\n                  <p>Results grid displays repeating period details </p>\\n                  <p>Create/Update buttons and Actions are included in the grid</p>\\n                  <p>Columns of the Search Results Grid are Name, poeriod Type and Description of the Peirod.</p>  \\n                  <p>The search results will initially defaults 10 last repeating periods created.  It also inculdes seed data.</p>\\n                  \\n                  \"\niteration_id: \n','2011-06-01 06:22:57'),(7085,'Feature',1558,'create','8',NULL,'2011-06-01 06:25:45'),(7086,'Feature',1559,'create','8',NULL,'2011-06-01 06:28:04'),(7087,'Feature',1559,'update','8','--- \nscope: 